39 static inline bool IsZero(const Operand& rt) {
40  if (rt.is_reg()) {
41  return rt.rm() == zero_reg;
42  } else {
43  return rt.immediate() == 0;
44  }
45 }
46 
47 int MacroAssembler::RequiredStackSizeForCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
48  Register exclusion1,
49  Register exclusion2,
50  Register exclusion3) const {
51  int bytes = 0;
52 
53  RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
54  RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
55  bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
56 
57  if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
58  bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
59  }
60 
61  return bytes;
62 }
63 
64 int MacroAssembler::PushCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion1,
65  Register exclusion2, Register exclusion3) {
66  int bytes = 0;
67 
68  RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
69  RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
70  MultiPush(list);
71  bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
72 
73  if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
74  MultiPushFPU(kCallerSavedFPU);
75  bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
76  }
77 
78  return bytes;
79 }
80 
81 int MacroAssembler::PopCallerSaved(SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, Register exclusion1,
82  Register exclusion2, Register exclusion3) {
83  int bytes = 0;
84  if (fp_mode == SaveFPRegsMode::kSave) {
85  MultiPopFPU(kCallerSavedFPU);
86  bytes += kCallerSavedFPU.Count() * kDoubleSize;
87  }
88 
89  RegList exclusions = {exclusion1, exclusion2, exclusion3};
90  RegList list = kJSCallerSaved - exclusions;
91  MultiPop(list);
92  bytes += list.Count() * kSystemPointerSize;
93 
94  return bytes;
95 }

97 #define __ ACCESS_MASM(masm)
98 namespace {
99 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
100 // Only used when leaptiering is disabled.
101 static void TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(MacroAssembler* masm,
102  Register optimized_code_entry,
103  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
104  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
105  // -- a0 : actual argument count
106  // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
107  // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee if needed, and caller)
108  // -----------------------------------
109  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
110  DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code_entry, a1, a3, scratch1, scratch2));
111 
112  Label heal_optimized_code_slot;
113 
114  // If the optimized code is cleared, go to runtime to update the optimization
115  // marker field.
116  __ LoadWeakValue(optimized_code_entry, optimized_code_entry,
117  &heal_optimized_code_slot);
118 
119  // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
120  __ LoadCodePointerField(
121  optimized_code_entry,
122  FieldMemOperand(optimized_code_entry, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
123 
124  // Check if the optimized code is marked for deopt. If it is, call the
125  // runtime to clear it.
126  __ JumpIfCodeIsMarkedForDeoptimization(optimized_code_entry, scratch1,
127  &heal_optimized_code_slot);
128 
129  // Optimized code is good, get it into the closure and link the closure into
130  // the optimized functions list, then tail call the optimized code.
131  // The feedback vector is no longer used, so reuse it as a scratch
132  // register.
133  __ ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(optimized_code_entry, a1);
134 
135  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
136  __ LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, optimized_code_entry, kJSEntrypointTag);
137  __ Jump(a2);
138 
139  // Optimized code slot contains deoptimized code or code is cleared and
140  // optimized code marker isn't updated. Evict the code, update the marker
141  // and re-enter the closure's code.
142  __ bind(&heal_optimized_code_slot);
143  __ GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kHealOptimizedCodeSlot);
144 }
145 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
146 
147 } // namespace

149 void MacroAssembler::AssertFeedbackCell(Register object, Register scratch) {
150  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
151  GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
152  Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackCell, scratch,
153  Operand(FEEDBACK_CELL_TYPE));
154  }
155 }
156 void MacroAssembler::AssertFeedbackVector(Register object, Register scratch) {
157  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
158  GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
159  Assert(eq, AbortReason::kExpectedFeedbackVector, scratch,
160  Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
161  }
162 }
163 void MacroAssembler::AssertUnreachable(AbortReason reason) {
164  if (v8_flags.debug_code) Abort(reason);
165 }
166 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE

168 void MacroAssembler::ReplaceClosureCodeWithOptimizedCode(
169  Register optimized_code, Register closure) {
170  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
171  DCHECK(!AreAliased(optimized_code, closure));
172 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
173  UNREACHABLE();
174 #else
175  StoreCodePointerField(optimized_code,
176  FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
177  RecordWriteField(closure, JSFunction::kCodeOffset, optimized_code,
178  kRAHasNotBeenSaved, SaveFPRegsMode::kIgnore, SmiCheck::kOmit,
179  ReadOnlyCheck::kOmit, SlotDescriptor::ForCodePointerSlot());
180 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
181 }
182 
183 void MacroAssembler::GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(
184  Runtime::FunctionId function_id) {
185  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
186  // ----------- S t a t e -------------
187  // -- a0 : actual argument count (preserved for callee)
188  // -- a1 : target function (preserved for callee)
189  // -- a3 : new target (preserved for callee)
190  // -- a4 : dispatch handle (preserved for callee)
191  // -----------------------------------
192  {
193  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::INTERNAL);
194  // Push a copy of the target function, the new target, the actual
195  // argument count, and the dispatch handle.
196  // Push function as parameter to the runtime call.
197  SmiTag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
198  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
199  kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
200 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
201  // No need to SmiTag since dispatch handles always look like Smis.
202  static_assert(kJSDispatchHandleShift > 0);
203  AssertSmi(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
204  Push(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
205 #endif
206  // Function is also the parameter to the runtime call.
207  Push(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister);
208 
209  CallRuntime(function_id, 1);
210  LoadCodeInstructionStart(a2, a0, kJSEntrypointTag);
211 
212  // Restore target function, new target, actual argument count and dispatch
213  // handle.
214 #ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
215  Pop(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister);
216 #endif
217  Pop(kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister, kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister,
218  kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
219  SmiUntag(kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
220  }
221 
222  static_assert(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister == a2, "ABI mismatch");
223  Jump(a2);
224 }

226 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
227 // Read off the flags in the feedback vector and check if there
228 // is optimized code or a tiering state that needs to be processed.
229 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVectorFlagsAndJumpIfNeedsProcessing(
230  Register flags, Register feedback_vector, CodeKind current_code_kind,
231  Label* flags_need_processing) {
232  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
233  DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
234  DCHECK(CodeKindCanTierUp(current_code_kind));
235  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
236  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
237  Lhu(flags, FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector, FeedbackVector::kFlagsOffset));
238  uint32_t flag_mask =
239  FeedbackVector::FlagMaskForNeedsProcessingCheckFrom(current_code_kind);
240  And(scratch, flags, Operand(flag_mask));
241  Branch(flags_need_processing, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
242 }
243 
244 void MacroAssembler::OptimizeCodeOrTailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(
245  Register flags, Register feedback_vector) {
246  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
247  DCHECK(!AreAliased(flags, feedback_vector));
248  Label maybe_has_optimized_code, maybe_needs_logging;
249  // Check if optimized code is available.
250  {
251  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
252  temps.Include(t0, t1);
253  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
254  And(scratch, flags,
255  Operand(FeedbackVector::kFlagsTieringStateIsAnyRequested));
256  Branch(&maybe_needs_logging, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
257  Label::Distance::kNear);
258  }
259  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kCompileOptimized);
260 
261  bind(&maybe_needs_logging);
262  {
263  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
264  temps.Include(t0, t1);
265  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
266  And(scratch, flags, Operand(FeedbackVector::LogNextExecutionBit::kMask));
267  Branch(&maybe_has_optimized_code, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
268  Label::Distance::kNear);
269  }
270 
271  GenerateTailCallToReturnedCode(Runtime::kFunctionLogNextExecution);
272 
273  bind(&maybe_has_optimized_code);
274  Register optimized_code_entry = flags;
275  LoadTaggedField(optimized_code_entry,
276  FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
277  FeedbackVector::kMaybeOptimizedCodeOffset));
278  {
279  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
280  temps.Include(t0, t1);
281  Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
282  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
283  TailCallOptimizedCodeSlot(this, optimized_code_entry, scratch1, scratch2);
284  }
285 }
286 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING

288 void MacroAssembler::LoadIsolateField(const Register& rd, IsolateFieldId id) {
289  li(rd, ExternalReference::Create(id));
290 }

292 void MacroAssembler::LoadRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
293 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
294  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
295  is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
296  DecompressTagged(destination, ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
297  return;
298  }
299 #endif
300  // Many roots have addresses that are too large to fit into addition immediate
301  // operands. Evidence suggests that the extra instruction for decompression
302  // costs us more than the load.
303  LoadWord(destination,
304  MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
305 }
306 
307 void MacroAssembler::LoadTaggedRoot(Register destination, RootIndex index) {
308  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
309  is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
310  li(destination, (int32_t)ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
311  return;
312  }
313  LoadWord(destination,
314  MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
315 }
316 void MacroAssembler::LoadCompressedTaggedRoot(Register destination,
317  RootIndex index) {
318 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
319  Lwu(destination,
320  MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
321 #else
322  LoadWord(destination,
323  MemOperand(kRootRegister, RootRegisterOffsetForRootIndex(index)));
324 #endif
325 }
326 
327 void MacroAssembler::PushCommonFrame(Register marker_reg) {
328  if (marker_reg.is_valid()) {
329  Push(ra, fp, marker_reg);
330  AddWord(fp, sp, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
331  } else {
332  Push(ra, fp);
333  Mv(fp, sp);
334  }
335 }
336 
337 void MacroAssembler::PushStandardFrame(Register function_reg) {
338  int offset = -StandardFrameConstants::kContextOffset;
339  if (function_reg.is_valid()) {
340  Push(ra, fp, cp, function_reg, kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
341  offset += 2 * kSystemPointerSize;
342  } else {
343  Push(ra, fp, cp, kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister);
344  offset += kSystemPointerSize;
345  }
346  AddWord(fp, sp, Operand(offset));
347 }
348 
349 int MacroAssembler::SafepointRegisterStackIndex(int reg_code) {
350  // The registers are pushed starting with the highest encoding,
351  // which means that lowest encodings are closest to the stack pointer.
352  return kSafepointRegisterStackIndexMap[reg_code];
353 }
354 
355 // Clobbers object, dst, value, and ra, if (ra_status == kRAHasBeenSaved)
356 // The register 'object' contains a heap object pointer. The heap object
357 // tag is shifted away.
358 void MacroAssembler::RecordWriteField(Register object, int offset,
359  Register value, RAStatus ra_status,
360  SaveFPRegsMode save_fp,
361  SmiCheck smi_check,
362  ReadOnlyCheck ro_check,
363  SlotDescriptor slot) {
364  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value));
365  // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
366  // catch stores of smisand read-only objects, as well as stores into the
367  // young generation.
368  Label done;
369 
370  // #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
371  // if (ro_check == ReadOnlyCheck::kInline) {
372  // // Quick check for Read-only and small Smi values.
373  // static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kLastAllocatedRoot <
374  // kRegularPageSize); JumpIfUnsignedLessThan(value, kRegularPageSize,
375  // &done);
376  // }
377  // #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
378 
379  // Skip the barrier if writing a smi.
380  if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
381  JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
382  }
383 
384  // Although the object register is tagged, the offset is relative to the start
385  // of the object, so offset must be a multiple of kTaggedSize.
386  DCHECK(IsAligned(offset, kTaggedSize));
387 
388  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
389  Label ok;
390  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
391  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
392  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, scratch));
393  AddWord(scratch, object, offset - kHeapObjectTag);
394  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(kTaggedSize - 1));
395  BranchShort(&ok, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
396  Abort(AbortReason::kUnalignedCellInWriteBarrier);
397  bind(&ok);
398  }
399 
400  RecordWrite(object, Operand(offset - kHeapObjectTag), value, ra_status,
401  save_fp, SmiCheck::kOmit, ReadOnlyCheck::kOmit, slot);
402 
403  bind(&done);
404 }

406 void MacroAssembler::LoadTrustedPointerField(Register destination,
407  MemOperand field_operand,
408  IndirectPointerTag tag) {

411 #else
412  LoadTaggedField(destination, field_operand);
413 #endif
414 }

416 void MacroAssembler::StoreTrustedPointerField(Register value,
417  MemOperand dst_field_operand) {
418 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
419  StoreIndirectPointerField(value, dst_field_operand);
420 #else
421  StoreTaggedField(value, dst_field_operand);
422 #endif
423 }

425 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
426 void MacroAssembler::ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(Register destination,
427  Register handle,
428  IndirectPointerTag tag) {
429  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
430  // The tag implies which pointer table to use.
431  if (tag == kUnknownIndirectPointerTag) {
432  // In this case we have to rely on the handle marking to determine which
433  // pointer table to use.
434  Label is_trusted_pointer_handle, done;
435  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, handle));
436  And(destination, handle, kCodePointerHandleMarker);
437  Branch(&is_trusted_pointer_handle, eq, destination, Operand(zero_reg));
438  ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
439  Branch(&done);
440  bind(&is_trusted_pointer_handle);
441  ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle,
442  kUnknownIndirectPointerTag);
443  bind(&done);
444  } else if (tag == kCodeIndirectPointerTag) {
445  ResolveCodePointerHandle(destination, handle);
446  } else {
447  ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
448  }
449 }
450 
451 void MacroAssembler::ResolveTrustedPointerHandle(Register destination,
452  Register handle,
453  IndirectPointerTag tag) {
454  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
455  DCHECK_NE(tag, kCodeIndirectPointerTag);
456  DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
457 
458  Register table = destination;
459  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
460  LoadWord(table, MemOperand{kRootRegister,
461  IsolateData::trusted_pointer_table_offset()});
462  SrlWord(handle, handle, kTrustedPointerHandleShift);
463  CalcScaledAddress(destination, table, handle,
464  kTrustedPointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
465  LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(destination, 0));
466  // The LSB is used as marking bit by the trusted pointer table, so here we
467  // have to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
468  // Untag the pointer and remove the marking bit in one operation.
469  Register tag_reg = handle;
470  li(tag_reg, Operand(~(tag | kTrustedPointerTableMarkBit)));
471  And(destination, destination, tag_reg);
472 }
473 
474 void MacroAssembler::ResolveCodePointerHandle(Register destination,
475  Register handle) {
476  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
477  DCHECK(!AreAliased(handle, destination));
478 
479  Register table = destination;
480  LoadCodePointerTableBase(table);
481  SrlWord(handle, handle, kCodePointerHandleShift);
482  CalcScaledAddress(destination, table, handle, kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
483  LoadWord(destination,
484  MemOperand(destination, kCodePointerTableEntryCodeObjectOffset));
485  // The LSB is used as marking bit by the code pointer table, so here we have
486  // to set it using a bitwise OR as it may or may not be set.
487  Or(destination, destination, Operand(kHeapObjectTag));
488 }
489 
490 void MacroAssembler::LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(Register destination,
491  MemOperand field_operand,
492  CodeEntrypointTag tag) {
493  DCHECK_NE(tag, kInvalidEntrypointTag);
494  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
495  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
496  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
497  LoadCodePointerTableBase(scratch);
498  Lwu(destination, field_operand);
499  SrlWord(destination, destination, kCodePointerHandleShift);
500  SllWord(destination, destination, kCodePointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
501  AddWord(scratch, scratch, destination);
502  LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
503  if (tag != 0) {
504  li(scratch, Operand(tag));
505  Xor(destination, destination, scratch);
506  }
507 }
508 
509 void MacroAssembler::LoadCodePointerTableBase(Register destination) {
510 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES
511  if (!options().isolate_independent_code && isolate()) {
512  // Embed the code pointer table address into the code.
513  li(destination,
514  ExternalReference::code_pointer_table_base_address(isolate()));
515  } else {
516  // Force indirect load via root register as a workaround for
517  // isolate-independent code (for example, for Wasm).
518  LoadWord(
519  destination,
520  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
521  ExternalReference::address_of_code_pointer_table_base_address(),
522  destination));
523  }
524 #else
525  // Embed the code pointer table address into the code.
526  li(destination, ExternalReference::global_code_pointer_table_base_address());
527 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES
528 }
529 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
530 
531 void MacroAssembler::LoadExternalPointerField(Register destination,
532  MemOperand field_operand,
533  ExternalPointerTagRange tag_range,
534  Register isolate_root) {
535  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, isolate_root));
536  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
537 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
538  DCHECK(!tag_range.IsEmpty());
539  DCHECK(!IsSharedExternalPointerType(tag_range));
540  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
541  Register external_table = temps.Acquire();
542  if (isolate_root == no_reg) {
543  DCHECK(root_array_available_);
544  isolate_root = kRootRegister;
545  }
546  LoadWord(external_table,
547  MemOperand(isolate_root,
548  IsolateData::external_pointer_table_offset() +
549  Internals::kExternalPointerTableBasePointerOffset));
550  Lwu(destination, field_operand);
551  srli(destination, destination, kExternalPointerIndexShift);
552  slli(destination, destination, kExternalPointerTableEntrySizeLog2);
553  LoaWord(destination, MemOperand(external_table, destination));
554 
555  // We don't expect to see empty fields here. If this is ever needed, consider
556  // using an dedicated empty value entry for those tags instead (i.e. an entry
557  // with the right tag and nullptr payload).
558  DCHECK(!ExternalPointerCanBeEmpty(tag_range));
559  // We need another scratch register for the 64-bit tag constant. Instead of
560  // forcing the `And` to allocate a new temp register (which we may not have),
561  // reuse the temp register that we used for the external pointer table base.
562  Register scratch = external_table;
563  Register scratch = external_table;
564  if (tag_range.Size() == 1) {
565  // The common and simple case: we expect exactly one tag.
566  And(scratch, destination, Operand(kExternalPointerTagMask));
567  srli(destination, Operand(destination), kExternalPointerPayloadShift);
568  SbxCheck(eq, AbortReason::kExternalPointerTagMismatch, scratch,
569  Operand(tag_range.first << kExternalPointerTagShift));
570  } else {
571  // Not currently supported. Implement once needed.
572  DCHECK_NE(tag_range, kAnyExternalPointerTagRange);
573  UNREACHABLE();
574  }
575 #else
576  LoadWord(destination, field_operand);
577 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
578 }
579 
580 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
581 void MacroAssembler::LoadIndirectPointerField(Register destination,
582  MemOperand field_operand,
583  IndirectPointerTag tag) {
584 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
585  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
586  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
587  Register handle = t6;
588  DCHECK_NE(handle, destination);
589  Lwu(handle, field_operand);
590 
591  ResolveIndirectPointerHandle(destination, handle, tag);
592 #else
593  UNREACHABLE();
594 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
595 }
596 
597 void MacroAssembler::StoreIndirectPointerField(Register value,
598  MemOperand dst_field_operand,
599  Trapper&& trapper) {
600 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
601  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
602  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
603  Lw(scratch,
604  FieldMemOperand(value, ExposedTrustedObject::kSelfIndirectPointerOffset));
605  Sw(scratch, dst_field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
606 #else
607  UNREACHABLE();
608 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
609 }
610 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
611 
612 void MacroAssembler::MaybeSaveRegisters(RegList registers) {
613  if (registers.is_empty()) return;
614  MultiPush(registers);
615 }
616 
617 void MacroAssembler::MaybeRestoreRegisters(RegList registers) {
618  if (registers.is_empty()) return;
619  MultiPop(registers);
620 }
621 
622 void MacroAssembler::CallEphemeronKeyBarrier(Register object, Operand offset,
623  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode) {
624  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
625  RegList registers = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object);
626  MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
627 
628  Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
629  Register slot_address_parameter =
630  WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
631 
632  MoveObjectAndSlot(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, object, offset);
633 
634  CallBuiltin(Builtins::EphemeronKeyBarrier(fp_mode));
635  MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
636 }
637 
638 void MacroAssembler::CallIndirectPointerBarrier(Register object, Operand offset,
639  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
640  IndirectPointerTag tag) {
641  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
642  RegList registers =
643  IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object);
644  MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
645 
646  MoveObjectAndSlot(
647  IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister(),
648  IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(), object,
649  offset);
650  li(IndirectPointerWriteBarrierDescriptor::IndirectPointerTagRegister(),
651  Operand(tag));
652 
653  CallBuiltin(Builtins::IndirectPointerBarrier(fp_mode));
654  MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
655 }
656 
657 void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters(Register object,
658  Operand offset,
659  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
660  StubCallMode mode) {
661  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
662  RegList registers = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ComputeSavedRegisters(object);
663  MaybeSaveRegisters(registers);
664 
665  Register object_parameter = WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister();
666  Register slot_address_parameter =
667  WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
668 
669  MoveObjectAndSlot(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, object, offset);
670 
671  CallRecordWriteStub(object_parameter, slot_address_parameter, fp_mode, mode);
672 
673  MaybeRestoreRegisters(registers);
674 }
675 
676 void MacroAssembler::CallRecordWriteStub(Register object, Register slot_address,
677  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode,
678  StubCallMode mode) {
679  // Use CallRecordWriteStubSaveRegisters if the object and slot registers
680  // need to be caller saved.
681  DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::ObjectRegister(), object);
682  DCHECK_EQ(WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister(), slot_address);
683  if (mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
684  auto wasm_target =
685  static_cast<Address>(wasm::WasmCode::GetRecordWriteBuiltin(fp_mode));
686  Call(wasm_target, RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
687  } else {
688  CallBuiltin(Builtins::RecordWrite(fp_mode));
689  }
690 }
691 
692 void MacroAssembler::MoveObjectAndSlot(Register dst_object, Register dst_slot,
693  Register object, Operand offset) {
694  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
695  DCHECK_NE(dst_object, dst_slot);
696  // If `offset` is a register, it cannot overlap with `object`.
697  DCHECK_IMPLIES(!offset.IsImmediate(), offset.rm() != object);
698 
699  // If the slot register does not overlap with the object register, we can
700  // overwrite it.
701  if (dst_slot != object) {
702  AddWord(dst_slot, object, offset);
703  Mv(dst_object, object);
704  return;
705  }
706 
707  DCHECK_EQ(dst_slot, object);
708 
709  // If the destination object register does not overlap with the offset
710  // register, we can overwrite it.
711  if (offset.IsImmediate() || (offset.rm() != dst_object)) {
712  Mv(dst_object, dst_slot);
713  AddWord(dst_slot, dst_slot, offset);
714  return;
715  }
716 
717  DCHECK_EQ(dst_object, offset.rm());
718 
719  // We only have `dst_slot` and `dst_object` left as distinct registers so we
720  // have to swap them. We write this as a add+sub sequence to avoid using a
721  // scratch register.
722  AddWord(dst_slot, dst_slot, dst_object);
723  SubWord(dst_object, dst_slot, dst_object);
724 }
725 
726 // Clobbers object, address, value, and ra, if (ra_status == kRAHasBeenSaved)
727 // The register 'object' contains a heap object pointer. The heap object
728 // tag is shifted away.
729 void MacroAssembler::RecordWrite(Register object, Operand offset,
730  Register value, RAStatus ra_status,
731  SaveFPRegsMode fp_mode, SmiCheck smi_check,
732  ReadOnlyCheck ro_check, SlotDescriptor slot) {
733  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value));
734 
735  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
736  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
737  Register temp = temps.Acquire();
738  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, value, temp));
739  AddWord(temp, object, offset);
740 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
741  if (slot.contains_indirect_pointer()) {
742  LoadIndirectPointerField(temp, MemOperand(temp, 0),
743  slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
744  } else {
745  DCHECK(slot.contains_direct_pointer());
746  LoadTaggedField(temp, MemOperand(temp, 0));
747  }
748 #else
749  LoadTaggedField(temp, MemOperand(temp));
750 #endif
751  Assert(eq, AbortReason::kWrongAddressOrValuePassedToRecordWrite, temp,
752  Operand(value));
753  }
754 
755  if (v8_flags.disable_write_barriers) {
756  return;
757  }
758 
759  // First, check if a write barrier is even needed. The tests below
760  // catch stores of smisand read-only objects, as well as stores into the
761  // young generation.
762  Label done;
763  // #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
764  // if (ro_check == ReadOnlyCheck::kInline) {
765  // // Quick check for Read-only and small Smi values.
766  // static_assert(StaticReadOnlyRoot::kLastAllocatedRoot <
767  // kRegularPageSize); JumpIfUnsignedLessThan(value, kRegularPageSize,
768  // &done);
769  // }
770  // #endif // V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
771 
772  if (smi_check == SmiCheck::kInline) {
773  DCHECK_EQ(0, kSmiTag);
774  JumpIfSmi(value, &done);
775  }
776 
777  CheckPageFlag(value, MemoryChunk::kPointersToHereAreInterestingMask,
778  eq, // In RISC-V, it uses cc for a comparison with 0, so if
779  // no bits are set, and cc is eq, it will branch to done
780  &done);
781 
782  CheckPageFlag(object, MemoryChunk::kPointersFromHereAreInterestingMask,
783  eq, // In RISC-V, it uses cc for a comparison with 0, so if
784  // no bits are set, and cc is eq, it will branch to done
785  &done);
786  // Record the actual write.
787  if (ra_status == kRAHasNotBeenSaved) {
788  push(ra);
789  }
790  Register slot_address = WriteBarrierDescriptor::SlotAddressRegister();
791  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, slot_address, value));
792  // TODO(cbruni): Turn offset into int.
793  if (slot.contains_direct_pointer()) {
794  DCHECK(offset.IsImmediate());
795  AddWord(slot_address, object, offset);
796  CallRecordWriteStub(object, slot_address, fp_mode,
797  StubCallMode::kCallBuiltinPointer);
798  } else {
799  DCHECK(slot.contains_indirect_pointer());
800  CallIndirectPointerBarrier(object, offset, fp_mode,
801  slot.indirect_pointer_tag());
802  }
803  if (ra_status == kRAHasNotBeenSaved) {
804  pop(ra);
805  }
806  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) li(slot_address, Operand(kZapValue));
807 
808  bind(&done);
809 }
810

812 // Instruction macros.
813 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
814 void MacroAssembler::DecodeSandboxedPointer(Register value) {
815  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
816 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
817  SrlWord(value, value, kSandboxedPointerShift);
818  AddWord(value, value, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
819 #else
820  UNREACHABLE();
821 #endif
822 }
823 
824 void MacroAssembler::LoadSandboxedPointerField(Register destination,
825  const MemOperand& field_operand,
826  Trapper&& trapper) {
827 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
828  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
829  LoadWord(destination, field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
830  DecodeSandboxedPointer(destination);
831 #else
832  UNREACHABLE();
833 #endif
834 }
835 
836 void MacroAssembler::StoreSandboxedPointerField(
837  Register value, const MemOperand& dst_field_operand, Trapper&& trapper) {
838 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
839  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
840  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
841  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
842  SubWord(scratch, value, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister);
843  SllWord(scratch, scratch, kSandboxedPointerShift);
844  StoreWord(scratch, dst_field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
845 #else
846  UNREACHABLE();
847 #endif
848 }

850 void MacroAssembler::Add32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
851  if (rt.is_reg()) {
852  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
853  ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
854  ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
855  c_addw(rd, rt.rm());
856  } else {
857  addw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
858  }
859  } else {
860  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int6(rt.immediate()) &&
861  (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd != zero_reg) &&
862  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
863  c_addiw(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
864  } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
865  addiw(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
866  } else if ((-4096 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
867  (2048 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
868  addiw(rd, rs, rt.immediate() / 2);
869  addiw(rd, rd, rt.immediate() - (rt.immediate() / 2));
870  } else {
871  // li handles the relocation.
872  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
873  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
874  Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
875  addw(rd, rs, scratch);
876  }
877  }
878 }
879 
880 void MacroAssembler::Sub32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
881  if (rt.is_reg()) {
882  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
883  ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
884  ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
885  c_subw(rd, rt.rm());
886  } else {
887  subw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
888  }
889  } else {
890  DCHECK(is_int32(rt.immediate()));
891  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
892  (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
893  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
894  c_addiw(
895  rd,
896  static_cast<int8_t>(
897  -rt.immediate())); // No c_subiw instr, use c_addiw(x, y, -imm).
898  } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
899  addiw(rd, rs,
900  static_cast<int32_t>(
901  -rt.immediate())); // No subiw instr, use addiw(x, y, -imm).
902  } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
903  (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
904  addiw(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
905  addiw(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
906  } else {
907  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
908  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
909  if (-rt.immediate() >> 12 == 0 && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
910  // Use load -imm and addu when loading -imm generates one instruction.
911  Li(scratch, -rt.immediate());
912  addw(rd, rs, scratch);
913  } else {
914  // li handles the relocation.
915  Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
916  subw(rd, rs, scratch);
917  }
918  }
919  }
920 }
921 
922 void MacroAssembler::AddWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
923  Add64(rd, rs, rt);
924 }
925 
926 void MacroAssembler::SubWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
927  Sub64(rd, rs, rt);
928 }
929 
930 void MacroAssembler::Sub64(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
931  if (rt.is_reg()) {
932  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
933  ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
934  ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
935  c_sub(rd, rt.rm());
936  } else {
937  sub(rd, rs, rt.rm());
938  }
939  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
940  (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
941  (rt.immediate() != 0) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
942  c_addi(rd,
943  static_cast<int8_t>(
944  -rt.immediate())); // No c_subi instr, use c_addi(x, y, -imm).
945 
946  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(-rt.immediate()) &&
947  (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
948  (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
949  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
950  c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(-rt.immediate()));
951  } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
952  addi(rd, rs,
953  static_cast<int32_t>(
954  -rt.immediate())); // No subi instr, use addi(x, y, -imm).
955  } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
956  (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
957  addi(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
958  addi(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
959  } else {
960  int li_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(rt.immediate());
961  int li_neg_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(-rt.immediate());
962  if (li_neg_count < li_count && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
963  // Use load -imm and add when loading -imm generates one instruction.
964  DCHECK(rt.immediate() != std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
965  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
966  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
967  li(scratch, Operand(-rt.immediate()));
968  add(rd, rs, scratch);
969  } else {
970  // li handles the relocation.
971  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
972  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
973  li(scratch, rt);
974  sub(rd, rs, scratch);
975  }
976  }
977 }
978 
979 void MacroAssembler::Add64(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
980  if (rt.is_reg()) {
981  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
982  (rt.rm() != zero_reg) && (rs != zero_reg)) {
983  c_add(rd, rt.rm());
984  } else {
985  add(rd, rs, rt.rm());
986  }
987  } else {
988  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int6(rt.immediate()) &&
989  (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd != zero_reg) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
990  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
991  c_addi(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
992  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(rt.immediate()) &&
993  (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
994  (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
995  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
996  c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(rt.immediate()));
997  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension &&
998  ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) && (rs == sp) &&
999  is_uint10(rt.immediate()) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
1000  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1001  c_addi4spn(rd, static_cast<uint16_t>(rt.immediate()));
1002  } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1003  addi(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
1004  } else if ((-4096 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
1005  (2048 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
1006  addi(rd, rs, rt.immediate() / 2);
1007  addi(rd, rd, rt.immediate() - (rt.immediate() / 2));
1008  } else {
1009  // li handles the relocation.
1010  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1011  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1012  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1013  li(scratch, rt);
1014  add(rd, rs, scratch);
1015  }
1016  }
1017 }

1028  }

1044 void MacroAssembler::Mulhu32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt,
1045  Register rsz, Register rtz) {
1046  SllWord(rsz, rs, 32);
1047  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1048  SllWord(rtz, rt.rm(), 32);
1049  } else {
1050  Li(rtz, rt.immediate() << 32);
1051  }
1052  mulhu(rd, rsz, rtz);
1053  SraWord(rd, rd, 32);
1054 }

1176 void MacroAssembler::Modu64(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {

1190 }
1191 
1192 void MacroAssembler::Add32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1193  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1194  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1195  (rt.rm() != zero_reg) && (rs != zero_reg)) {
1196  c_add(rd, rt.rm());
1197  } else {
1198  add(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1199  }
1200  } else {
1201  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int6(rt.immediate()) &&
1202  (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd != zero_reg) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
1203  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1204  c_addi(rd, static_cast<int8_t>(rt.immediate()));
1205  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(rt.immediate()) &&
1206  (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
1207  (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
1208  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1209  c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(rt.immediate()));
1210  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension &&
1211  ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) && (rs == sp) &&
1212  is_uint10(rt.immediate()) && (rt.immediate() != 0) &&
1213  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1214  c_addi4spn(rd, static_cast<uint16_t>(rt.immediate()));
1215  } else if (is_int12(rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1216  addi(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
1217  } else if ((-4096 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
1218  (2048 <= rt.immediate() && rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
1219  addi(rd, rs, rt.immediate() / 2);
1220  addi(rd, rd, rt.immediate() - (rt.immediate() / 2));
1221  } else {
1222  // li handles the relocation.
1223  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1224  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1225  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1226  li(scratch, rt);
1227  add(rd, rs, scratch);
1228  }
1229  }
1230 }
1231 
1232 void MacroAssembler::SubWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1233  Sub32(rd, rs, rt);
1234 }
1235 
1236 void MacroAssembler::Sub32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1237  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1238  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1239  ((rd.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
1240  ((rt.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000)) {
1241  c_sub(rd, rt.rm());
1242  } else {
1243  sub(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1244  }
1245  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd.code() == rs.code()) &&
1246  (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(-rt.immediate()) &&
1247  (rt.immediate() != 0) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1248  c_addi(rd,
1249  static_cast<int8_t>(
1250  -rt.immediate())); // No c_subi instr, use c_addi(x, y, -imm).
1251 
1252  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && is_int10(-rt.immediate()) &&
1253  (rt.immediate() != 0) && ((rt.immediate() & 0xf) == 0) &&
1254  (rd.code() == rs.code()) && (rd == sp) &&
1255  !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1256  c_addi16sp(static_cast<int16_t>(-rt.immediate()));
1257  } else if (is_int12(-rt.immediate()) && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1258  addi(rd, rs,
1259  static_cast<int32_t>(
1260  -rt.immediate())); // No subi instr, use addi(x, y, -imm).
1261  } else if ((-4096 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= -2049) ||
1262  (2048 <= -rt.immediate() && -rt.immediate() <= 4094)) {
1263  addi(rd, rs, -rt.immediate() / 2);
1264  addi(rd, rd, -rt.immediate() - (-rt.immediate() / 2));
1265  } else {
1266  // RV32G todo: imm64 or imm32 here
1267  int li_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(rt.immediate());
1268  int li_neg_count = InstrCountForLi64Bit(-rt.immediate());
1269  if (li_neg_count < li_count && !MustUseReg(rt.rmode())) {
1270  // Use load -imm and add when loading -imm generates one instruction.
1271  DCHECK(rt.immediate() != std::numeric_limits<int32_t>::min());
1272  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1273  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1274  li(scratch, Operand(-rt.immediate()));
1275  add(rd, rs, scratch);
1276  } else {
1277  // li handles the relocation.
1278  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1279  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1280  li(scratch, rt);
1281  sub(rd, rs, scratch);
1282  }
1283  }
1284 }

1392  andi(rd, rs, static_cast<int32_t>(rt.immediate()));
1393  } else {
1394  // li handles the relocation.
1395  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);

1397  Li(scratch, rt.immediate());
1398  and_(rd, rs, scratch);
1399  }

1678 void MacroAssembler::Ror(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1679  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1680  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1681  rorw(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1682  } else {
1683  int64_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1684  if (ror_value < 0) {
1685  ror_value += 32;
1686  }
1687  roriw(rd, rs, ror_value);
1688  }
1689  return;
1690  }
1691  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1692  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1693  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1694  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1695  negw(scratch, rt.rm());
1696  Sll32(scratch, rs, scratch);
1697  Srl32(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1698  Or(rd, scratch, rd);
1699  sext_w(rd, rd);
1700  } else {
1701  int64_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1702  if (ror_value == 0) {
1703  Mv(rd, rs);
1704  return;
1705  } else if (ror_value < 0) {
1706  ror_value += 32;
1707  }
1708  Srl32(scratch, rs, Operand(ror_value));
1709  Sll32(rd, rs, Operand(32 - ror_value));
1710  Or(rd, scratch, rd);
1711  sext_w(rd, rd);
1712  }
1713 }
1714 
1715 void MacroAssembler::Dror(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1716  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1717  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1718  ror(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1719  } else {
1720  int64_t dror_value = rt.immediate() % 64;
1721  if (dror_value < 0) {
1722  dror_value += 64;
1723  }
1724  rori(rd, rs, dror_value);
1725  }
1726  return;
1727  }
1728  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1729  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1730  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1731  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1732  negw(scratch, rt.rm());
1733  Sll64(scratch, rs, scratch);
1734  Srl64(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1735  Or(rd, scratch, rd);
1736  } else {
1737  int64_t dror_value = rt.immediate() % 64;
1738  if (dror_value == 0) {
1739  Mv(rd, rs);
1740  return;
1741  } else if (dror_value < 0) {
1742  dror_value += 64;
1743  }
1744  SrlWord(scratch, rs, Operand(dror_value));
1745  SllWord(rd, rs, Operand(64 - dror_value));
1746  Or(rd, scratch, rd);
1747  }
1748 }
1749 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
1750 void MacroAssembler::SllWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1751  Sll32(rd, rs, rt);
1752 }
1753 
1754 void MacroAssembler::Sll32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1755  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1756  sll(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1757  } else {
1758  uint8_t shamt = static_cast<uint8_t>(rt.immediate());
1759  slli(rd, rs, shamt);
1760  }
1761 }
1762 
1763 void MacroAssembler::SraWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1764  Sra32(rd, rs, rt);
1765 }
1766

1768  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1769  sra(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1770  } else {
1771  uint8_t shamt = static_cast<uint8_t>(rt.immediate());
1772  srai(rd, rs, shamt);
1773  }
1774 }

1776 void MacroAssembler::SrlWord(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1777  Srl32(rd, rs, rt);
1778 }

1780 void MacroAssembler::Srl32(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1781  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1782  srl(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1783  } else {
1784  uint8_t shamt = static_cast<uint8_t>(rt.immediate());
1785  srli(rd, rs, shamt);
1786  }
1787 }

1789 void MacroAssembler::Ror(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
1790  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1791  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1792  ror(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1793  } else {
1794  int32_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1795  if (ror_value < 0) {
1796  ror_value += 32;
1797  }
1798  rori(rd, rs, ror_value);
1799  }
1800  return;
1801  }
1802  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1803  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
1804  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1805  if (rt.is_reg()) {
1806  neg(scratch, rt.rm());
1807  SllWord(scratch, rs, scratch);
1808  SrlWord(rd, rs, rt.rm());
1809  Or(rd, scratch, rd);
1810  } else {
1811  int32_t ror_value = rt.immediate() % 32;
1812  if (ror_value == 0) {
1813  Mv(rd, rs);
1814  return;
1815  } else if (ror_value < 0) {
1816  ror_value += 32;
1817  }
1818  SrlWord(scratch, rs, ror_value);
1819  SllWord(rd, rs, 32 - ror_value);
1820  Or(rd, scratch, rd);
1821  }
1822 }
1823 #endif

1825 void MacroAssembler::Li(Register rd, intptr_t imm) {
1826  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd != zero_reg) && is_int6(imm)) {
1827  c_li(rd, imm);
1828  } else {
1829  RV_li(rd, imm);
1830  }
1831 }

1833 void MacroAssembler::Mv(Register rd, const Operand& rt) {
1834  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (rd != zero_reg) && (rt.rm() != zero_reg)) {
1835  c_mv(rd, rt.rm());
1836  } else {
1837  mv(rd, rt.rm());
1838  }
1839 }

1841 void MacroAssembler::CalcScaledAddress(Register rd, Register rt, Register rs,
1842  uint8_t sa) {
1843  DCHECK(sa >= 1 && sa <= 31);
1844  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBA)) {
1845  switch (sa) {
1846  case 1:
1847  sh1add(rd, rs, rt);
1848  return;
1849  case 2:
1850  sh2add(rd, rs, rt);
1851  return;
1852  case 3:
1853  sh3add(rd, rs, rt);
1854  return;
1855  default:
1856  break;
1857  }
1858  }
1859  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1860  Register tmp = rd == rt ? temps.Acquire() : rd;
1861  DCHECK(tmp != rt);
1862  SllWord(tmp, rs, sa);
1863  AddWord(rd, rt, tmp);
1864  return;
1865 }
1866 
1867 // ------------Pseudo-instructions-------------
1868 // Change endianness
1869 
1870 template <int NBYTES>
1871 void MacroAssembler::ReverseBytesHelper(Register rd, Register rs, Register tmp1,
1872  Register tmp2) {
1873  DCHECK(tmp1 != tmp2);
1874  DCHECK((rs != tmp1) && (rs != tmp2));
1875  DCHECK((rd != tmp1) && (rd != tmp2));
1876 
1877  // ByteMask - maximum value, held in byte
1878  constexpr int ByteMask = (1 << kBitsPerByte) - 1;
1879  // tmp1 = rs[0]; take least byte
1880  // tmp1 = tmp1 << kBitsPerByte;
1881  // for (nbyte = 1; nbyte < NBYTES - 1; nbyte++) {
1882  // tmp2 = rs[nbyte]; take n`th byte
1883  // tmp1 = (tmp2 | tmp1) << kBitsPerByte; add n`th source byte to tmp1
1884  // }
1885  // rd[0] = rs[NBYTES-1]; take upper byte
1886  // rd[NBYTES-1 : 1] = tmp1[NBYTES-1 : 1]; fill other bytes
1887  And(tmp1, rs, ByteMask);
1888  SllWord(tmp1, tmp1, kBitsPerByte);
1889  for (int nbyte = 1; nbyte < NBYTES - 1; nbyte++) {
1890  SrlWord(tmp2, rs, nbyte * kBitsPerByte);
1891  And(tmp2, tmp2, ByteMask);
1892  Or(tmp1, tmp1, tmp2);
1893  SllWord(tmp1, tmp1, kBitsPerByte);
1894  }
1895  SrlWord(rd, rs, (NBYTES - 1) * kBitsPerByte);
1896  And(rd, rd, ByteMask);
1897  Or(rd, tmp1, rd);
1898 }
1899 
1900 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
1901 void MacroAssembler::ByteSwap(Register rd, Register rs, int operand_size,
1902  Register scratch) {
1903  DCHECK(operand_size == 4 || operand_size == 8);
1904  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1905  rev8(rd, rs);
1906  if (operand_size == 4) {
1907  SraWord(rd, rd, 32);
1908  }
1909  return;
1910  }
1911  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1912  temps.Include(t4, t6);
1913  Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1914  Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1915  DCHECK(!AreAliased(rs, rd, x0, x1, scratch));
1916  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1917  if (operand_size == 4) {
1918  DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1919  if (scratch == no_reg) {
1920  ReverseBytesHelper<8>(rd, rs, x0, x1);
1921  Sra64(rd, rd, 32);
1922  } else {
1923  // Uint32_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF;
1924  // x0 = (x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16);
1925  // x0 = (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8));
1926  Register x2 = scratch;
1927  li(x1, 0x00FF00FF);
1928  Sll32(x0, rs, 16);
1929  Srl32(rd, rs, 16);
1930  Or(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16
1931  And(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF
1932  Sll32(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1933  Sll32(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00
1934  And(rd, x0, x1); // x0 & 0xFF00FF00
1935  Srl32(rd, rd, 8);
1936  Or(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1937  }
1938  } else {
1939  DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1940  if (scratch == no_reg) {
1941  ReverseBytesHelper<8>(rd, rs, x0, x1);
1942  } else {
1943  // uinx24_t x1 = 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFl;
1944  // uinx24_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFl;
1945  // x0 = (x0 << 32 | x0 >> 32);
1946  // x0 = (x0 & x1) << 16 | (x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16;
1947  // x0 = (x0 & x1) << 8 | (x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8;
1948  Register x2 = scratch;
1949  li(x1, 0x0000FFFF0000FFFFl);
1950  SllWord(x0, rs, 32);
1951  SrlWord(rd, rs, 32);
1952  Or(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 32 | x0 >> 32
1953  And(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF
1954  SllWord(x2, x2, 16); // x2 <- (x0 & 0x0000FFFF0000FFFF) << 16
1955  SllWord(x1, x1, 16); // x1 <- 0xFFFF0000FFFF0000
1956  And(rd, x0, x1); // rd <- x0 & 0xFFFF0000FFFF0000
1957  SrlWord(rd, rd, 16); // rd <- x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16
1958  Or(x0, rd, x2); // (x0 & x1) << 16 | (x0 & (x1 << 16)) >> 16;
1959  li(x1, 0x00FF00FF00FF00FFl);
1960  And(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF00FF00FF
1961  SllWord(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1962  SllWord(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00FF00FF00
1963  And(rd, x0, x1);
1964  SrlWord(rd, rd, 8); // rd <- (x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8
1965  Or(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
1966  }
1967  }
1968 }
1969 
1970 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
1971 void MacroAssembler::ByteSwap(Register rd, Register rs, int operand_size,
1972  Register scratch) {
1973  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
1974  rev8(rd, rs);
1975  return;
1976  }
1977  DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
1978  DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
1979  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
1980  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
1981  DCHECK((rd != t6) && (rs != t6));
1982  Register x0 = temps.Acquire();
1983  Register x1 = temps.Acquire();
1984  if (scratch == no_reg) {
1985  ReverseBytesHelper<4>(rd, rs, x0, x1);
1986  } else {
1987  // Uint32_t x1 = 0x00FF00FF;
1988  // x0 = (x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16);
1989  // x0 = (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8));
1990  Register x2 = scratch;
1991  li(x1, 0x00FF00FF);
1992  SllWord(x0, rs, 16);
1993  SrlWord(rd, rs, 16);
1994  Or(x0, rd, x0); // x0 <- x0 << 16 | x0 >> 16
1995  And(x2, x0, x1); // x2 <- x0 & 0x00FF00FF
1996  SllWord(x2, x2, 8); // x2 <- (x0 & x1) << 8
1997  SllWord(x1, x1, 8); // x1 <- 0xFF00FF00
1998  And(rd, x0, x1); // x0 & 0xFF00FF00
1999  SrlWord(rd, rd, 8);
2000  Or(rd, rd, x2); // (((x0 & x1) << 8) | ((x0 & (x1 << 8)) >> 8))
2001  }
2002 }
2003 #endif

2005 template <int NBYTES, bool LOAD_SIGNED>
2006 void MacroAssembler::LoadNBytes(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs,
2007  Register scratch) {
2008  DCHECK(rd != rs.rm() && rd != scratch);
2009  DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
2010 
2011  // load the most significant byte
2012  if (LOAD_SIGNED) {
2013  lb(rd, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
2014  } else {
2015  lbu(rd, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
2016  }
2017 
2018  // load remaining (nbytes-1) bytes from higher to lower
2019  SllWord(rd, rd, 8 * (NBYTES - 1));
2020  for (int i = (NBYTES - 2); i >= 0; i--) {
2021  lbu(scratch, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + i);
2022  if (i) SllWord(scratch, scratch, i * 8);
2023  Or(rd, rd, scratch);
2024  }
2025 }
2026 
2027 template <int NBYTES, bool LOAD_SIGNED>
2028 void MacroAssembler::LoadNBytesOverwritingBaseReg(const MemOperand& rs,
2029  Register scratch0,
2030  Register scratch1) {
2031  // This function loads nbytes from memory specified by rs and into rs.rm()
2032  DCHECK(rs.rm() != scratch0 && rs.rm() != scratch1 && scratch0 != scratch1);
2033  DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
2034 
2035  // load the most significant byte
2036  if (LOAD_SIGNED) {
2037  lb(scratch0, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
2038  } else {
2039  lbu(scratch0, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + (NBYTES - 1));
2040  }
2041 
2042  // load remaining (nbytes-1) bytes from higher to lower
2043  SllWord(scratch0, scratch0, 8 * (NBYTES - 1));
2044  for (int i = (NBYTES - 2); i >= 0; i--) {
2045  lbu(scratch1, rs.rm(), rs.offset() + i);
2046  if (i) {
2047  SllWord(scratch1, scratch1, i * 8);
2048  Or(scratch0, scratch0, scratch1);
2049  } else {
2050  // write to rs.rm() when processing the last byte
2051  Or(rs.rm(), scratch0, scratch1);
2052  }
2053  }
2054 }
2055 
2056 template <int NBYTES, bool IS_SIGNED>
2057 void MacroAssembler::UnalignedLoadHelper(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
2058  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2059  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2060 
2061  if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
2062  // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2063  MemOperand source = rs;
2064  Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2065  DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
2066  AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2067  NBYTES - 1);
2068 
2069  // Since source.rm() is scratch_base, assume rd != source.rm()
2070  DCHECK(rd != source.rm());
2071  Register scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
2072  LoadNBytes<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rd, source, scratch_other);
2073  } else {
2074  // no need to adjust base-and-offset
2075  if (rd != rs.rm()) {
2076  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2077  LoadNBytes<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rd, rs, scratch);
2078  } else { // rd == rs.rm()
2079  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2080  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
2081  LoadNBytesOverwritingBaseReg<NBYTES, IS_SIGNED>(rs, scratch, scratch2);
2082  }
2083  }
2084 }

2088 void MacroAssembler::UnalignedFLoadHelper(FPURegister frd,
2089  const MemOperand& rs) {
2090  DCHECK(NBYTES == 4 || NBYTES == 8);
2091  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2092  MemOperand source = rs;
2093  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2094  Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2095  if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
2096  // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2097  DCHECK(scratch_base != rs.rm());
2098  AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2099  NBYTES - 1);
2100  }
2101  temps.Include(t4, t6);
2102  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2103  Register scratch_other = temps.Acquire();
2104  DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm() && scratch_other != scratch &&
2105  scratch_other != rs.rm());
2106  LoadNBytes<NBYTES, true>(scratch, source, scratch_other);
2107  if (NBYTES == 4)
2108  fmv_w_x(frd, scratch);
2109  else
2110  fmv_d_x(frd, scratch);
2111 }

2142  if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, 8 - 1)) {

2164 template <int NBYTES>
2165 void MacroAssembler::UnalignedStoreHelper(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs,
2166  Register scratch_other) {
2167  DCHECK(scratch_other != rs.rm());
2168  DCHECK_NE(scratch_other, no_reg);
2169  DCHECK_LE(NBYTES, 8);
2170  MemOperand source = rs;
2171  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2172  Register scratch_base = temps.Acquire();
2173  // Adjust offset for two accesses and check if offset + 3 fits into int12.
2174  if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(rs, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES, NBYTES - 1)) {
2175  DCHECK(scratch_base != rd && scratch_base != rs.rm());
2176  AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch_base, OffsetAccessType::TWO_ACCESSES,
2177  NBYTES - 1);
2178  }
2179 
2180  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2181  DCHECK(scratch_other != rd && scratch_other != rs.rm() &&
2182  scratch_other != source.rm());
2183 
2184  sb(rd, source.rm(), source.offset());
2185  for (size_t i = 1; i <= (NBYTES - 1); i++) {
2186  SrlWord(scratch_other, rd, Operand(i * 8));
2187  sb(scratch_other, source.rm(), source.offset() + i);
2188  }
2189 }

2231 template <typename Reg_T, typename Func>
2232 void MacroAssembler::AlignedLoadHelper(Reg_T target, const MemOperand& rs,
2233  Func generator) {
2234  MemOperand source = rs;
2235  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2236  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2237  if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(source)) {
2238  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2239  DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm());
2240  AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch);
2241  }
2242  generator(target, source);
2243 }

2245 template <typename Reg_T, typename Func>
2246 void MacroAssembler::AlignedStoreHelper(Reg_T value, const MemOperand& rs,
2247  Func generator) {
2248  MemOperand source = rs;
2249  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2250  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2251  if (NeedAdjustBaseAndOffset(source)) {
2252  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2253  // make sure scratch does not overwrite value
2254  if (std::is_same_v<Reg_T, Register>) {
2255  DCHECK(scratch.code() != value.code());
2256  }
2257  DCHECK(scratch != rs.rm());
2258  AdjustBaseAndOffset(&source, scratch);
2259  }
2260  generator(value, source);
2261 }

2288 void MacroAssembler::Uld(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
2289  UnalignedLoadHelper<8, true>(rd, rs);
2290 }
2291 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2292 // Load consequent 32-bit word pair in 64-bit reg. and put first word in low
2293 // bits,
2294 // second word in high bits.
2295 void MacroAssembler::LoadWordPair(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
2296  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2297  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2298  Lwu(rd, rs);
2299  Lw(scratch, MemOperand(rs.rm(), rs.offset() + kSystemPointerSize / 2));
2300  SllWord(scratch, scratch, 32);
2301  AddWord(rd, rd, scratch);
2302 }
2303 
2304 // Do 64-bit store as two consequent 32-bit stores to unaligned address.
2305 void MacroAssembler::StoreWordPair(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs) {
2306  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2307  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2308  Sw(rd, rs);
2309  SraWord(scratch, rd, 32);
2310  Sw(scratch, MemOperand(rs.rm(), rs.offset() + kSystemPointerSize / 2));
2311 }
2312 #endif

2390 void MacroAssembler::Lw(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs, Trapper&& trapper) {
2391  auto fn = [&](Register target, const MemOperand& source) {
2392  trapper(pc_offset());
2393  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && ((target.code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2394  ((source.rm().code() & 0b11000) == 0b01000) &&
2395  is_uint7(source.offset()) && ((source.offset() & 0x3) == 0)) {
2396  c_lw(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2397  } else if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension && (target != zero_reg) &&
2398  is_uint8(source.offset()) && (source.rm() == sp) &&
2399  ((source.offset() & 0x3) == 0)) {
2400  c_lwsp(target, source.offset());
2401  } else {
2402  lw(target, source.rm(), source.offset());
2403  }
2404  };
2405  AlignedLoadHelper(rd, rs, fn);
2406 }

2526 void MacroAssembler::Ll(Register rd, const MemOperand& rs, Trapper&& trapper) {

2528  if (is_one_instruction) {
2529  trapper(pc_offset());
2530  lr_w(false, false, rd, rs.rm());
2531  } else {
2532  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2533  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
2534  AddWord(scratch, rs.rm(), rs.offset());
2535  trapper(pc_offset());
2536  lr_w(false, false, rd, scratch);
2537  }
2538 }

2586 void MacroAssembler::li(Register dst, Handle<HeapObject> value,
2587  RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
2588  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2589  // TODO(jgruber,v8:8887): Also consider a root-relative load when generating
2590  // non-isolate-independent code. In many cases it might be cheaper than
2591  // embedding the relocatable value.
2592  if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
2593  IndirectLoadConstant(dst, value);
2594  return;
2595  } else {
2596  li(dst, Operand(value, rmode));
2597  }
2598 }
2599 
2600 void MacroAssembler::li(Register dst, ExternalReference reference,
2601  LiFlags mode) {
2602  if (root_array_available()) {
2603  if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
2604  AddWord(dst, kRootRegister,
2605  Operand(reference.offset_from_root_register()));
2606  return;
2607  }
2608  if (options().isolate_independent_code) {
2609  IndirectLoadExternalReference(dst, reference);
2610  return;
2611  }
2612  }
2613  // External references should not get created with IDs if
2614  // `!root_array_available()`.
2615  CHECK(!reference.IsIsolateFieldId());
2616  li(dst, Operand(reference), mode);
2617 }
2618 
2619 static inline int InstrCountForLiLower32Bit(int64_t value) {
2620  int64_t Hi20 = ((value + 0x800) >> 12);
2621  int64_t Lo12 = value << 52 >> 52;
2622  if (Hi20 == 0 || Lo12 == 0) {
2623  return 1;
2624  }
2625  return 2;
2626 }
2627 
2628 int MacroAssembler::InstrCountForLi64Bit(int64_t value) {
2629  if (is_int32(value + 0x800)) {
2630  return InstrCountForLiLower32Bit(value);
2631  } else {
2632  return RV_li_count(value);
2633  }
2634  UNREACHABLE();
2635  return INT_MAX;
2636 }
2637 
2638 void MacroAssembler::li_optimized(Register rd, Operand j, LiFlags mode) {
2639  DCHECK(!j.is_reg());
2640  DCHECK(!MustUseReg(j.rmode()));
2641  DCHECK(mode == OPTIMIZE_SIZE);
2642  Li(rd, j.immediate());
2643 }
2644 
2645 void MacroAssembler::li(Register rd, Operand j, LiFlags mode) {
2646  DCHECK(!j.is_reg());
2647  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2648  if (!MustUseReg(j.rmode()) && mode == OPTIMIZE_SIZE) {
2649  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2650  int count = RV_li_count(j.immediate(), temps.CanAcquire());
2651  int reverse_count = RV_li_count(~j.immediate(), temps.CanAcquire());
2652  if (v8_flags.riscv_constant_pool && count >= 4 && reverse_count >= 4) {
2653  // Ld/Lw an Address from a constant pool.
2654 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2655  RecordEntry((uint32_t)j.immediate(), j.rmode());
2656 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2657  RecordEntry((uint64_t)j.immediate(), j.rmode());
2658 #endif
2659  auipc(rd, 0);
2660  // Record a value into constant pool, passing 1 as the offset makes the
2661  // promise that LoadWord() generates full 32-bit instruction to be
2662  // patched with real value in the future
2663  LoadWord(rd, MemOperand(rd, 1));
2664  } else {
2665  if ((count - reverse_count) > 1) {
2666  Li(rd, ~j.immediate());
2667  not_(rd, rd);
2668  } else {
2669  Li(rd, j.immediate());
2670  }
2671  }
2672  } else if (MustUseReg(j.rmode())) {
2673  int64_t immediate;
2674  if (RelocInfo::IsWasmCanonicalSigId(j.rmode()) ||
2675  RelocInfo::IsWasmCodePointerTableEntry(j.rmode()) ||
2676  RelocInfo::IsJSDispatchHandle(j.rmode())) {
2677  // These reloc data are 32-bit values.
2678  DCHECK(is_int32(j.immediate()) || is_uint32(j.immediate()));
2679  RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2680 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2681  li_constant32(rd, int32_t(j.immediate()));
2682 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2683  li_constant(rd, int32_t(j.immediate()));
2684 #endif
2685  return;
2686  } else if (RelocInfo::IsCompressedEmbeddedObject(j.rmode())) {
2687  Handle<HeapObject> handle(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(j.immediate()));
2688  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(handle);
2689  DCHECK(is_uint32(index));
2690  RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2691 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2692  li_constant32(rd, static_cast<uint32_t>(index));
2693 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2694  li_constant(rd, index);
2695 #endif
2696  return;
2697  } else if (RelocInfo::IsFullEmbeddedObject(j.rmode())) {
2698  if (j.IsHeapNumberRequest()) {
2699  RequestHeapNumber(j.heap_number_request());
2700  immediate = j.immediate_for_heap_number_request();
2701  } else {
2702  immediate = j.immediate();
2703  }
2704 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
2705  BlockPoolsScope block_pools(this);
2706  Handle<HeapObject> handle(reinterpret_cast<Address*>(immediate));
2707  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(handle);
2708  if (RecordEntry(static_cast<uint64_t>(index), j.rmode()) ==
2709  RelocInfoStatus::kMustRecord) {
2710  RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode(), index);
2711  }
2712  DEBUG_PRINTF("\t EmbeddedObjectIndex%lu\n", index);
2713  auipc(rd, 0);
2714  // Record a value into constant pool, passing 1 as the offset makes the
2715  // promise that LoadWord() generates full 32-bit instruction to be
2716  // patched with real value in the future
2717  LoadWord(rd, MemOperand(rd, 1));
2718 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2719  RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2720  li_constant(rd, immediate);
2721 #endif
2722  return;
2723  } else {
2724  immediate = j.immediate();
2725  }
2726  RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode(), immediate);
2727  li_ptr(rd, immediate);
2728  } else if (mode == ADDRESS_LOAD) {
2729  // We always need the same number of instructions as we may need to patch
2730  // this code to load another value which may need all 6 instructions.
2731  RecordRelocInfo(j.rmode());
2732  li_ptr(rd, j.immediate());
2733  } else { // Always emit the same 48 bit instruction
2734  // sequence.
2735  li_ptr(rd, j.immediate());
2736  }
2737 }
2738 
2739 static RegList t_regs = {t0, t1, t2, t3, t4, t5, t6};
2740 static RegList a_regs = {a0, a1, a2, a3, a4, a5, a6, a7};
2741 static RegList s_regs = {s1, s2, s3, s4, s5, s6, s7, s8, s9, s10, s11};
2742 
2743 void MacroAssembler::MultiPush(RegList regs) {
2744  int16_t num_to_push = regs.Count();
2745  int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kSystemPointerSize;
2746 
2747 #define TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(reg) \
2748  if (regs.has(reg)) { \
2749  stack_offset -= kSystemPointerSize; \
2750  StoreWord(reg, MemOperand(sp, stack_offset)); \
2751  regs.clear(reg); \
2752  }
2753 
2754 #define T_REGS(V) V(t6) V(t5) V(t4) V(t3) V(t2) V(t1) V(t0)
2755 #define A_REGS(V) V(a7) V(a6) V(a5) V(a4) V(a3) V(a2) V(a1) V(a0)
2756 #define S_REGS(V) \
2757  V(s11) V(s10) V(s9) V(s8) V(s7) V(s6) V(s5) V(s4) V(s3) V(s2) V(s1)
2758 
2759  SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_offset));
2760 
2761  // Certain usage of MultiPush requires that registers are pushed onto the
2762  // stack in a particular: ra, fp, sp, gp, .... (basically in the decreasing
2763  // order of register numbers according to MIPS register numbers)
2764  TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(ra);
2765  TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(fp);
2766  TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(sp);
2767  TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(gp);
2768  TEST_AND_PUSH_REG(tp);
2769  if (!(regs & s_regs).is_empty()) {
2770  S_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2771  }
2772  if (!(regs & a_regs).is_empty()) {
2773  A_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2774  }
2775  if (!(regs & t_regs).is_empty()) {
2776  T_REGS(TEST_AND_PUSH_REG)
2777  }
2778 
2779  DCHECK(regs.is_empty());
2780 
2781 #undef TEST_AND_PUSH_REG
2782 #undef T_REGS
2783 #undef A_REGS
2784 #undef S_REGS
2785 }
2786 
2787 void MacroAssembler::MultiPop(RegList regs) {
2788  int16_t stack_offset = 0;
2789 
2790 #define TEST_AND_POP_REG(reg) \
2791  if (regs.has(reg)) { \
2792  LoadWord(reg, MemOperand(sp, stack_offset)); \
2793  stack_offset += kSystemPointerSize; \
2794  regs.clear(reg); \
2795  }
2796 
2797 #define T_REGS(V) V(t0) V(t1) V(t2) V(t3) V(t4) V(t5) V(t6)
2798 #define A_REGS(V) V(a0) V(a1) V(a2) V(a3) V(a4) V(a5) V(a6) V(a7)
2799 #define S_REGS(V) \
2800  V(s1) V(s2) V(s3) V(s4) V(s5) V(s6) V(s7) V(s8) V(s9) V(s10) V(s11)
2801 
2802  // MultiPop pops from the stack in reverse order as MultiPush
2803  if (!(regs & t_regs).is_empty()) {
2804  T_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2805  }
2806  if (!(regs & a_regs).is_empty()) {
2807  A_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2808  }
2809  if (!(regs & s_regs).is_empty()) {
2810  S_REGS(TEST_AND_POP_REG)
2811  }
2812  TEST_AND_POP_REG(tp);
2813  TEST_AND_POP_REG(gp);
2814  TEST_AND_POP_REG(sp);
2815  TEST_AND_POP_REG(fp);
2816  TEST_AND_POP_REG(ra);
2817 
2818  DCHECK(regs.is_empty());
2819 
2820  AddWord(sp, sp, stack_offset);
2821 
2822 #undef TEST_AND_POP_REG
2823 #undef T_REGS
2824 #undef S_REGS
2825 #undef A_REGS
2826 }
2827 
2828 void MacroAssembler::MultiPushFPU(DoubleRegList regs) {
2829  int16_t num_to_push = regs.Count();
2830  int16_t stack_offset = num_to_push * kDoubleSize;
2831 
2832  SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_offset));
2833  for (int16_t i = kNumRegisters - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
2834  if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
2835  stack_offset -= kDoubleSize;
2836  StoreDouble(FPURegister::from_code(i), MemOperand(sp, stack_offset));
2837  }
2838  }
2839 }
2840 
2841 void MacroAssembler::MultiPopFPU(DoubleRegList regs) {
2842  int16_t stack_offset = 0;
2843 
2844  for (int16_t i = 0; i < kNumRegisters; i++) {
2845  if ((regs.bits() & (1 << i)) != 0) {
2846  LoadDouble(FPURegister::from_code(i), MemOperand(sp, stack_offset));
2847  stack_offset += kDoubleSize;
2848  }
2849  }
2850  AddWord(sp, sp, stack_offset);
2851 }

2853 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
2854 void MacroAssembler::AddPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2855  Register left_low, Register left_high,
2856  Register right_low, Register right_high,
2857  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2858  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2859  Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2860  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2861 
2862  Add32(scratch1, left_low, right_low);
2863  // Save the carry
2864  Sltu(scratch3, scratch1, left_low);
2865  Add32(scratch2, left_high, right_high);
2866 
2867  // Output higher 32 bits + carry
2868  Add32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2869  Move(dst_low, scratch1);
2870 }
2871 
2872 void MacroAssembler::SubPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2873  Register left_low, Register left_high,
2874  Register right_low, Register right_high,
2875  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2876  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2877  Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2878  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2879 
2880  // Check if we need a borrow
2881  Sltu(scratch3, left_low, right_low);
2882  Sub32(scratch1, left_low, right_low);
2883  Sub32(scratch2, left_high, right_high);
2884 
2885  // Output higher 32 bits - borrow
2886  Sub32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2887  Move(dst_low, scratch1);
2888 }

2910 void MacroAssembler::MulPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2911  Register left_low, Register left_high,
2912  Register right_low, Register right_high,
2913  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2914  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2915  Register scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2916  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2917  if (dst_low == right_low) {
2918  Mv(scratch1, right_low);
2919  }
2920  Mul(scratch3, left_low, right_high);
2921  // NOTE: do not move these around, recommended sequence is MULH-MUL
2922  // LL * RL : higher 32 bits
2923  mulhu(scratch2, left_low, right_low);
2924  // LL * RL : lower 32 bits
2925  Mul(dst_low, left_low, right_low);
2926  // (LL * RH) + (LL * RL : higher 32 bits)
2927  Add32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch3);
2928  if (dst_low != right_low) {
2929  Mul(scratch3, left_high, right_low);
2930  } else {
2931  Mul(scratch3, left_high, scratch1);
2932  }
2933  Add32(dst_high, scratch2, scratch3);
2934 }
2935 
2936 void MacroAssembler::ShlPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2937  Register src_low, Register src_high,
2938  Register shift, Register scratch1,
2939  Register scratch2) {
2940  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
2941  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
2942  Label done;
2943  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
2944  Register scratch3 = no_reg;
2945  if (dst_low == src_low) {
2946  scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
2947  Mv(scratch3, src_low);
2948  }
2949  And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
2950  // LOW32 << shamt
2951  SllWord(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
2952  // HIGH32 << shamt
2953  SllWord(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
2954 
2955  // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
2956  Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
2957 
2958  // LOW32 >> (32 - shamt)
2959  li(scratch2, 32);
2960  Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
2961  if (dst_low == src_low) {
2962  SrlWord(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
2963  } else {
2964  SrlWord(scratch1, src_low, scratch2);
2965  }
2966 
2967  // (HIGH32 << shamt) | (LOW32 >> (32 - shamt))
2968  Or(dst_high, dst_high, scratch1);
2969 
2970  // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
2971  // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
2972  // is set
2973  And(scratch1, shift, 32);
2974  Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
2975  Move(dst_high, dst_low);
2976  Move(dst_low, zero_reg);
2977 
2978  bind(&done);
2979 }
2980 
2981 void MacroAssembler::ShlPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
2982  Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
2983  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
2984  DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
2985  DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_low);
2986  DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_low);
2987  shift &= 0x3F;
2988  if (shift == 0) {
2989  Move(dst_high, src_high);
2990  Move(dst_low, src_low);
2991  } else if (shift == 32) {
2992  Move(dst_high, src_low);
2993  li(dst_low, Operand(0));
2994  } else if (shift > 32) {
2995  shift &= 0x1F;
2996  SllWord(dst_high, src_low, shift);
2997  li(dst_low, Operand(0));
2998  } else {
2999  SllWord(dst_high, src_high, shift);
3000  SllWord(dst_low, src_low, shift);
3001  SrlWord(scratch1, src_low, 32 - shift);
3002  Or(dst_high, dst_high, scratch1);
3003  }
3004 }

3006 void MacroAssembler::ShrPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3007  Register src_low, Register src_high,
3008  Register shift, Register scratch1,
3009  Register scratch2) {
3010  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3011  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3012  Label done;
3013  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3014  Register scratch3 = no_reg;
3015  if (dst_high == src_high) {
3016  scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
3017  Mv(scratch3, src_high);
3018  }
3019  And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
3020  // HIGH32 >> shamt
3021  SrlWord(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
3022  // LOW32 >> shamt
3023  SrlWord(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
3024 
3025  // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
3026  Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
3027 
3028  // HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)
3029  li(scratch2, 32);
3030  Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
3031  if (dst_high == src_high) {
3032  SllWord(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
3033  } else {
3034  SllWord(scratch1, src_high, scratch2);
3035  }
3036 
3037  // (HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)) | (LOW32 >> shamt)
3038  Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3039 
3040  // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
3041  // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
3042  // is set
3043  And(scratch1, shift, 32);
3044  Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
3045  Move(dst_low, dst_high);
3046  Move(dst_high, zero_reg);
3047 
3048  bind(&done);
3049 }

3051 void MacroAssembler::ShrPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3052  Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
3053  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
3054  DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
3055  DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_high);
3056  DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_high);
3057  shift &= 0x3F;
3058  if (shift == 32) {
3059  Mv(dst_low, src_high);
3060  li(dst_high, Operand(0));
3061  } else if (shift > 32) {
3062  shift &= 0x1F;
3063  SrlWord(dst_low, src_high, shift);
3064  li(dst_high, Operand(0));
3065  } else if (shift == 0) {
3066  Move(dst_low, src_low);
3067  Move(dst_high, src_high);
3068  } else {
3069  SrlWord(dst_low, src_low, shift);
3070  SrlWord(dst_high, src_high, shift);
3071  SllWord(scratch1, src_high, 32 - shift);
3072  Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3073  }
3074 }

3076 void MacroAssembler::SarPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3077  Register src_low, Register src_high,
3078  Register shift, Register scratch1,
3079  Register scratch2) {
3080  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3081  Label done;
3082  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3083  Register scratch3 = no_reg;
3084  if (dst_high == src_high) {
3085  scratch3 = temps.Acquire();
3086  Mv(scratch3, src_high);
3087  }
3088  And(scratch1, shift, 0x1F);
3089  // HIGH32 >> shamt (arithmetic)
3090  Sra32(dst_high, src_high, scratch1);
3091  // LOW32 >> shamt (logical)
3092  SrlWord(dst_low, src_low, scratch1);
3093 
3094  // If the shift amount is 0, we're done
3095  Branch(&done, eq, shift, Operand(zero_reg));
3096 
3097  // HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)
3098  li(scratch2, 32);
3099  Sub32(scratch2, scratch2, scratch1);
3100  if (dst_high == src_high) {
3101  SllWord(scratch1, scratch3, scratch2);
3102  } else {
3103  SllWord(scratch1, src_high, scratch2);
3104  }
3105  // (HIGH32 << (32 - shamt)) | (LOW32 >> shamt)
3106  Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3107 
3108  // If the shift amount is < 32, we're done
3109  // Note: the shift amount is always < 64, so we can just test if the 6th bit
3110  // is set
3111  And(scratch1, shift, 32);
3112  Branch(&done, eq, scratch1, Operand(zero_reg));
3113  Move(dst_low, dst_high);
3114  Sra32(dst_high, dst_high, 31);
3115 
3116  bind(&done);
3117 }

3119 void MacroAssembler::SarPair(Register dst_low, Register dst_high,
3120  Register src_low, Register src_high, int32_t shift,
3121  Register scratch1, Register scratch2) {
3122  DCHECK_GE(63, shift);
3123  DCHECK_NE(dst_low, src_high);
3124  DCHECK_NE(dst_high, src_high);
3125  shift = shift & 0x3F;
3126  if (shift == 0) {
3127  Mv(dst_low, src_low);
3128  Mv(dst_high, src_high);
3129  } else if (shift < 32) {
3130  SrlWord(dst_low, src_low, shift);
3131  SraWord(dst_high, src_high, shift);
3132  SllWord(scratch1, src_high, 32 - shift);
3133  Or(dst_low, dst_low, scratch1);
3134  } else if (shift == 32) {
3135  SraWord(dst_high, src_high, 31);
3136  Mv(dst_low, src_high);
3137  } else {
3138  SraWord(dst_high, src_high, 31);
3139  SraWord(dst_low, src_high, shift - 32);
3140  }
3141 }

3144 void MacroAssembler::ExtractBits(Register rt, Register rs, uint16_t pos,
3145  uint16_t size, bool sign_extend) {
3146 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3147  uint16_t arch_mode = 64;
3148 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3149  uint16_t arch_mode = 32;
3150 #endif
3151  DCHECK_LT(pos, arch_mode);
3152  DCHECK_GT(size, 0);
3153  DCHECK_LE(size, arch_mode);
3154  DCHECK_GT(pos + size, 0);
3155  DCHECK_LE(pos + size, arch_mode);
3156  SllWord(rt, rs, arch_mode - (pos + size));
3157  if (sign_extend)
3158  SraWord(rt, rt, arch_mode - size);
3159  else
3160  SrlWord(rt, rt, arch_mode - size);
3161 }
3162 
3163 void MacroAssembler::InsertBits(Register dest, Register source, Register pos,
3164  int size) {
3165 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3166  DCHECK_LT(size, 64);
3167 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3168  DCHECK_LT(size, 32);
3169 #endif
3170  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3171  Register mask = temps.Acquire();
3172  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3173  Register source_ = temps.Acquire();
3174  // Create a mask of the length=size.
3175  li(mask, 1);
3176  SllWord(mask, mask, size);
3177  AddWord(mask, mask, -1);
3178  And(source_, mask, source);
3179  SllWord(source_, source_, pos);
3180  // Make a mask containing 0's. 0's start at "pos" with length=size.
3181  SllWord(mask, mask, pos);
3182  not_(mask, mask);
3183  // cut area for insertion of source.
3184  And(dest, mask, dest);
3185  // insert source
3186  Or(dest, dest, source_);
3187 }
