3223 template <typename CvtFunc>
3224 void MacroAssembler::RoundFloatingPointToInteger(Register rd, FPURegister fs,
3225  Register result,
3226  CvtFunc fcvt_generator) {
3227  if (result.is_valid()) {
3228  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3229 
3230  int exception_flags = kInvalidOperation;
3231  // clear invalid operation accrued flags, don't preserve old fflags
3232  csrrci(zero_reg, csr_fflags, exception_flags);
3233 
3234  // actual conversion instruction
3235  fcvt_generator(this, rd, fs);
3236 
3237  // check kInvalidOperation flag (out-of-range, NaN)
3238  // set result to 1 if normal, otherwise set result to 0 for abnormal
3239  frflags(result);
3240  And(result, result, exception_flags);
3241  seqz(result, result); // result <-- 1 (normal), result <-- 0 (abnormal)
3242  } else {
3243  // actual conversion instruction
3244  fcvt_generator(this, rd, fs);
3245  }
3246 }

3248 void MacroAssembler::Clear_if_nan_d(Register rd, FPURegister fs) {
3249  Label no_nan;
3250  DCHECK_NE(kScratchReg, rd);
3251  feq_d(kScratchReg, fs, fs);
3252  bnez(kScratchReg, &no_nan);
3253  Move(rd, zero_reg);
3254  bind(&no_nan);
3255 }

3273 void MacroAssembler::Trunc_w_d(Register rd, FPURegister fs, Register result) {
3274 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64 // For RV64 we can go faster csr-less approach
3275  if (result.is_valid()) {
3276  Label bad, done;
3277  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3278  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3279  // actual conversion instruction
3280  fcvt_l_d(rd, fs, RTZ);
3281  li(scratch, kMinInt);
3282  blt(rd, scratch, &bad);
3283  Sub32(scratch, scratch, 1); // converts kMinInt into kMaxInt
3284  bgt(rd, scratch, &bad);
3285  li(result, 1);
3286  j(&done);
3287  bind(&bad);
3288  // scratch still holds proper max/min value
3289  Mv(rd, scratch);
3290  li(result, 0);
3291  // set result to 1 if normal, otherwise set result to 0 for abnormal
3292  bind(&done);
3293  } else {
3294  fcvt_w_d(rd, fs, RTZ);
3295  }
3296 #else
3297  RoundFloatingPointToInteger(
3298  rd, fs, result, [](MacroAssembler* masm, Register dst, FPURegister src) {
3299  masm->fcvt_w_d(dst, src, RTZ);
3300  });
3301 #endif
3302 }

3341  rd, fs, result, [](MacroAssembler* masm, Register dst, FPURegister src) {
3342  masm->fcvt_l_s(dst, src, RTZ);
3343  });
3344 }

3387 
3388 // According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3389 // the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3390 // rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3391 // round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3392 // handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3393 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3394 template <typename F>
3395 void MacroAssembler::RoundHelper(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src,
3396  FPURegister fpu_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm) {
3397  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3398  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3399  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3400 
3401  DCHECK((std::is_same_v<float, F>) || (std::is_same_v<double, F>));
3402  // Need at least two FPRs, so check against dst == src == fpu_scratch
3403  DCHECK(!(dst == src && dst == fpu_scratch));
3404 
3405  const int kFloatMantissaBits =
3406  sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32MantissaBits : kFloat64MantissaBits;
3407  const int kFloatExponentBits =
3408  sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBits : kFloat64ExponentBits;
3409  const int kFloatExponentBias =
3410  sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBias : kFloat64ExponentBias;
3411  Label done;
3412 
3413  {
3414  UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3415  Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3416  // extract exponent value of the source floating-point to scratch
3417  if (std::is_same_v<F, double>) {
3418  fmv_x_d(scratch, src);
3419  } else {
3420  fmv_x_w(scratch, src);
3421  }
3422  ExtractBits(scratch2, scratch, kFloatMantissaBits, kFloatExponentBits);
3423  }
3424 
3425  // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3426  // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3427  // generating another branch)
3428  if (dst != src) {
3429  if (std::is_same_v<F, double>) {
3430  fmv_d(dst, src);
3431  } else {
3432  fmv_s(dst, src);
3433  }
3434  }
3435  {
3436  Label not_NaN;
3437  UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3438  Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3439  // According to the wasm spec
3440  // (https://webassembly.github.io/spec/core/exec/numerics.html#aux-nans)
3441  // if input is canonical NaN, then output is canonical NaN, and if input is
3442  // any other NaN, then output is any NaN with most significant bit of
3443  // payload is 1. In RISC-V, feq_d will set scratch to 0 if src is a NaN. If
3444  // src is not a NaN, branch to the label and do nothing, but if it is,
3445  // fmin_d will set dst to the canonical NaN.
3446  if (std::is_same_v<F, double>) {
3447  feq_d(scratch, src, src);
3448  bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3449  fmin_d(dst, src, src);
3450  } else {
3451  feq_s(scratch, src, src);
3452  bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3453  fmin_s(dst, src, src);
3454  }
3455  bind(&not_NaN);
3456  }
3457 
3458  // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3459  // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3460  // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3461  // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3462  // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3463  // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3464  // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3465  Branch(&done, greater_equal, scratch2,
3466  Operand(kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits));
3467 
3468  // Actual rounding is needed along this path
3469 
3470  // old_src holds the original input, needed for the case of src == dst
3471  FPURegister old_src = src;
3472  if (src == dst) {
3473  DCHECK(fpu_scratch != dst);
3474  Move(fpu_scratch, src);
3475  old_src = fpu_scratch;
3476  }
3477 
3478  // Since only input whose real exponent value is less than kMantissaBits
3479  // (i.e., 23 or 52-bits) falls into this path, the value range of the input
3480  // falls into that of 23- or 53-bit integers. So we round the input to integer
3481  // values, then convert them back to floating-point.
3482  {
3483  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3484  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3485  if (std::is_same_v<F, double>) {
3486  fcvt_l_d(scratch, src, frm);
3487  fcvt_d_l(dst, scratch, frm);
3488  } else {
3489  fcvt_w_s(scratch, src, frm);
3490  fcvt_s_w(dst, scratch, frm);
3491  }
3492  }
3493  // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3494  // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3495  // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3496  // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3497  // Therefore, we use sign-bit injection to produce +/-0 correctly. Instead of
3498  // testing for zero w/ a branch, we just insert sign-bit for everyone on this
3499  // path (this is where old_src is needed)
3500  if (std::is_same_v<F, double>) {
3501  fsgnj_d(dst, dst, old_src);
3502  } else {
3503  fsgnj_s(dst, dst, old_src);
3504  }
3505 
3506  bind(&done);
3507 }
3508 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3509 // According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3510 // the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3511 // rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3512 // round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3513 // handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3514 void MacroAssembler::RoundFloat(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src,
3515  FPURegister fpu_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm) {
3516  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3517  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3518  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3519 
3520  // Need at least two FPRs, so check against dst == src == fpu_scratch
3521  DCHECK(!(dst == src && dst == fpu_scratch));
3522 
3523  const int kFloatMantissaBits = kFloat32MantissaBits;
3524  const int kFloatExponentBits = kFloat32ExponentBits;
3525  const int kFloatExponentBias = kFloat32ExponentBias;
3526  Label done;
3527 
3528  {
3529  UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3530  Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3531  // extract exponent value of the source floating-point to scratch
3532  fmv_x_w(scratch, src);
3533  ExtractBits(scratch2, scratch, kFloatMantissaBits, kFloatExponentBits);
3534  }
3535 
3536  // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3537  // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3538  // generating another branch)
3539  if (dst != src) {
3540  fmv_s(dst, src);
3541  }
3542  {
3543  Label not_NaN;
3544  UseScratchRegisterScope temps2(this);
3545  Register scratch = temps2.Acquire();
3546  // According to the wasm spec
3547  // (https://webassembly.github.io/spec/core/exec/numerics.html#aux-nans)
3548  // if input is canonical NaN, then output is canonical NaN, and if input is
3549  // any other NaN, then output is any NaN with most significant bit of
3550  // payload is 1. In RISC-V, feq_d will set scratch to 0 if src is a NaN. If
3551  // src is not a NaN, branch to the label and do nothing, but if it is,
3552  // fmin_d will set dst to the canonical NaN.
3553  feq_s(scratch, src, src);
3554  bnez(scratch, &not_NaN);
3555  fmin_s(dst, src, src);
3556  bind(&not_NaN);
3557  }
3558 
3559  // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3560  // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3561  // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3562  // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3563  // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3564  // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3565  // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3566  Branch(&done, greater_equal, scratch2,
3567  Operand(kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits));
3568 
3569  // Actual rounding is needed along this path
3570 
3571  // old_src holds the original input, needed for the case of src == dst
3572  FPURegister old_src = src;
3573  if (src == dst) {
3574  DCHECK(fpu_scratch != dst);
3575  Move(fpu_scratch, src);
3576  old_src = fpu_scratch;
3577  }
3578 
3579  // Since only input whose real exponent value is less than kMantissaBits
3580  // (i.e., 23 or 52-bits) falls into this path, the value range of the input
3581  // falls into that of 23- or 53-bit integers. So we round the input to integer
3582  // values, then convert them back to floating-point.
3583  {
3584  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3585  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3586  fcvt_w_s(scratch, src, frm);
3587  fcvt_s_w(dst, scratch, frm);
3588  }
3589  // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3590  // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3591  // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3592  // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3593  // Therefore, we use sign-bit injection to produce +/-0 correctly. Instead of
3594  // testing for zero w/ a branch, we just insert sign-bit for everyone on this
3595  // path (this is where old_src is needed)
3596  fsgnj_s(dst, dst, old_src);
3597 
3598  bind(&done);
3599 }
3600 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3601 // According to JS ECMA specification, for floating-point round operations, if
3602 // the input is NaN, +/-infinity, or +/-0, the same input is returned as the
3603 // rounded result; this differs from behavior of RISCV fcvt instructions (which
3604 // round out-of-range values to the nearest max or min value), therefore special
3605 // handling is needed by NaN, +/-Infinity, +/-0
3606 template <typename F>
3607 void MacroAssembler::RoundHelper(VRegister dst, VRegister src, Register scratch,
3608  VRegister v_scratch, FPURoundingMode frm,
3609  bool keep_nan_same) {
3610  VU.set(scratch, std::is_same_v<F, float> ? E32 : E64, m1);
3611  // if src is NaN/+-Infinity/+-Zero or if the exponent is larger than # of bits
3612  // in mantissa, the result is the same as src, so move src to dest (to avoid
3613  // generating another branch)
3614 
3615  // If real exponent (i.e., scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias) is greater than
3616  // kFloat32MantissaBits, it means the floating-point value has no fractional
3617  // part, thus the input is already rounded, jump to done. Note that, NaN and
3618  // Infinity in floating-point representation sets maximal exponent value, so
3619  // they also satisfy (scratch2 - kFloatExponentBias >= kFloatMantissaBits),
3620  // and JS round semantics specify that rounding of NaN (Infinity) returns NaN
3621  // (Infinity), so NaN and Infinity are considered rounded value too.
3622  const int kFloatMantissaBits =
3623  sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32MantissaBits : kFloat64MantissaBits;
3624  const int kFloatExponentBits =
3625  sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBits : kFloat64ExponentBits;
3626  const int kFloatExponentBias =
3627  sizeof(F) == 4 ? kFloat32ExponentBias : kFloat64ExponentBias;
3628 
3629  // slli(rt, rs, 64 - (pos + size));
3630  // if (sign_extend) {
3631  // srai(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3632  // } else {
3633  // srli(rt, rt, 64 - size);
3634  // }
3635  vmv_vx(v_scratch, zero_reg);
3636  li(scratch, 64 - kFloatMantissaBits - kFloatExponentBits);
3637  vsll_vx(v_scratch, src, scratch);
3638  li(scratch, 64 - kFloatExponentBits);
3639  vsrl_vx(v_scratch, v_scratch, scratch);
3640  li(scratch, kFloatExponentBias + kFloatMantissaBits);
3641  vmslt_vx(v0, v_scratch, scratch);
3642  VU.set(frm);
3643  vmv_vv(dst, src);
3644  if (dst == src) {
3645  vmv_vv(v_scratch, src);
3646  }
3647  vfcvt_x_f_v(dst, src, MaskType::Mask);
3648  vfcvt_f_x_v(dst, dst, MaskType::Mask);
3649 
3650  // A special handling is needed if the input is a very small positive/negative
3651  // number that rounds to zero. JS semantics requires that the rounded result
3652  // retains the sign of the input, so a very small positive (negative)
3653  // floating-point number should be rounded to positive (negative) 0.
3654  if (dst == src) {
3655  vfsngj_vv(dst, dst, v_scratch);
3656  } else {
3657  vfsngj_vv(dst, dst, src);
3658  }
3659  if (!keep_nan_same) {
3660  vmfeq_vv(v0, src, src);
3661  vnot_vv(v0, v0);
3662  if (std::is_same_v<F, float>) {
3663  fmv_w_x(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3664  } else {
3665 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3666  fmv_d_x(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3667 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3668  fcvt_d_w(kScratchDoubleReg, zero_reg);
3669 #endif
3670  }
3671  vfadd_vf(dst, src, kScratchDoubleReg, MaskType::Mask);
3672  }
3673 }

3678 }

3715 void MacroAssembler::FaddS(FPURegister dst, FPURegister lhs, FPURegister rhs) {
3716  li(kScratchReg2, Operand(kSQuietNanMask));
3717  feq_s(kScratchReg, lhs, lhs);
3718  Label not_nan1, not_nan2, done;
3719  BranchShort(&not_nan1, ne, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
3720  fmv_x_w(kScratchReg, lhs);
3721  Or(kScratchReg, kScratchReg, Operand(kScratchReg2));
3722  fmv_w_x(dst, kScratchReg);
3723  Branch(&done);
3724  bind(&not_nan1);
3725  feq_s(kScratchReg, rhs, rhs);
3726  BranchShort(&not_nan2, ne, kScratchReg, Operand(zero_reg));
3727  fmv_x_w(kScratchReg, rhs);
3728  Or(kScratchReg, kScratchReg, Operand(kScratchReg2));
3729  fmv_w_x(dst, kScratchReg);
3730  Branch(&done);
3731  bind(&not_nan2);
3732  fadd_s(dst, lhs, rhs);
3733  bind(&done);
3734 }

3814 void MacroAssembler::CompareF32(Register rd, FPUCondition cc, FPURegister cmp1,
3815  FPURegister cmp2) {
3816  switch (cc) {
3817  case EQ:
3818  feq_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3819  break;
3820  case NE:
3821  feq_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3822  NegateBool(rd, rd);
3823  break;
3824  case LT:
3825  flt_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3826  break;
3827  case GE:
3828  fle_s(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3829  break;
3830  case LE:
3831  fle_s(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3832  break;
3833  case GT:
3834  flt_s(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3835  break;
3836  default:
3837  UNREACHABLE();
3838  }
3839 }
3840 
3841 void MacroAssembler::CompareF64(Register rd, FPUCondition cc, FPURegister cmp1,
3842  FPURegister cmp2) {
3843  switch (cc) {
3844  case EQ:
3845  feq_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3846  break;
3847  case NE:
3848  feq_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3849  NegateBool(rd, rd);
3850  break;
3851  case LT:
3852  flt_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3853  break;
3854  case GE:
3855  fle_d(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3856  break;
3857  case LE:
3858  fle_d(rd, cmp1, cmp2);
3859  break;
3860  case GT:
3861  flt_d(rd, cmp2, cmp1);
3862  break;
3863  default:
3864  UNREACHABLE();
3865  }
3866 }
3867 
3868 void MacroAssembler::CompareIsNotNanF32(Register rd, FPURegister cmp1,
3869  FPURegister cmp2) {
3870  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3871  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3872  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3873 
3874  feq_s(rd, cmp1, cmp1); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1)
3875  feq_s(scratch, cmp2, cmp2); // scratch <- !isNaN(cmp2)
3876  And(rd, rd, scratch); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1) && !isNan(cmp2)
3877 }
3878 
3879 void MacroAssembler::CompareIsNotNanF64(Register rd, FPURegister cmp1,
3880  FPURegister cmp2) {
3881  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3882  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3883  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3884 
3885  feq_d(rd, cmp1, cmp1); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1)
3886  feq_d(scratch, cmp2, cmp2); // scratch <- !isNaN(cmp2)
3887  And(rd, rd, scratch); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1) && !isNan(cmp2)
3888 }

3890 void MacroAssembler::CompareIsNanF32(Register rd, FPURegister cmp1,
3891  FPURegister cmp2) {
3892  CompareIsNotNanF32(rd, cmp1, cmp2); // rd <- !isNan(cmp1) && !isNan(cmp2)
3893  Xor(rd, rd, 1); // rd <- isNan(cmp1) || isNan(cmp2)
3894 }

3897  FPURegister cmp2) {

3899  Xor(rd, rd, 1); // rd <- isNan(cmp1) || isNan(cmp2)

3902 void MacroAssembler::BranchTrueShortF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3903  Branch(target, not_equal, rs, Operand(zero_reg));
3904 }
3905 
3906 void MacroAssembler::BranchFalseShortF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3907  Branch(target, equal, rs, Operand(zero_reg));
3908 }
3909 
3910 void MacroAssembler::BranchTrueF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3911  bool long_branch =
3912  target->is_bound() ? !is_near(target) : is_trampoline_emitted();
3913  if (long_branch) {
3914  Label skip;
3915  BranchFalseShortF(rs, &skip);
3916  BranchLong(target);
3917  bind(&skip);
3918  } else {
3919  BranchTrueShortF(rs, target);
3920  }
3921 }
3922 
3923 void MacroAssembler::BranchFalseF(Register rs, Label* target) {
3924  bool long_branch =
3925  target->is_bound() ? !is_near(target) : is_trampoline_emitted();
3926  if (long_branch) {
3927  Label skip;
3928  BranchTrueShortF(rs, &skip);
3929  BranchLong(target);
3930  bind(&skip);
3931  } else {
3932  BranchFalseShortF(rs, target);
3933  }
3934 }

3936 void MacroAssembler::InsertHighWordF64(FPURegister dst, Register src_high) {
3937 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
3938  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
3939  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
3940  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
3941  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3942 
3943  DCHECK(src_high != scratch2 && src_high != scratch);
3944 
3945  fmv_x_d(scratch, dst);
3946  SllWord(scratch2, src_high, 32);
3947  SllWord(scratch, scratch, 32);
3948  SrlWord(scratch, scratch, 32);
3949  Or(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
3950  fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);
3951 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
3952  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
3953  Add32(sp, sp, Operand(-8));
3954  StoreDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3955  Sw(src_high, MemOperand(sp, 4));
3956  LoadDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
3957  Add32(sp, sp, Operand(8));
3958 #endif
3959 }

3972  SrlWord(scratch, scratch, 32);
3973  SllWord(scratch, scratch, 32);
3974  Or(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
3975  fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);

3986 void MacroAssembler::LoadFPRImmediate(FPURegister dst, uint32_t src) {
3987  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
3988  // Handle special values first.
3989  if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f) && has_single_zero_reg_set_) {
3990  if (dst != kSingleRegZero) fmv_s(dst, kSingleRegZero);
3991  } else if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(-0.0f) &&
3992  has_single_zero_reg_set_) {
3993  Neg_s(dst, kSingleRegZero);
3994  } else {
3995  if (dst == kSingleRegZero) {
3996  DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f));
3997  fcvt_s_w(dst, zero_reg);
3998  has_single_zero_reg_set_ = true;
3999  } else {
4000  if (src == base::bit_cast<uint32_t>(0.0f)) {
4001  fcvt_s_w(dst, zero_reg);
4002  } else {
4003  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4004  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4005  li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(src)));
4006  fmv_w_x(dst, scratch);
4007  }
4008  }
4009  }
4010 }
4011 
4012 void MacroAssembler::LoadFPRImmediate(FPURegister dst, uint64_t src) {
4013  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
4014  // Handle special values first.
4015  if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0) && has_double_zero_reg_set_) {
4016  if (dst != kDoubleRegZero) fmv_d(dst, kDoubleRegZero);
4017  } else if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(-0.0) &&
4018  has_double_zero_reg_set_) {
4019  Neg_d(dst, kDoubleRegZero);
4020  } else {
4021 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4022  if (dst == kDoubleRegZero) {
4023  DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0));
4024  fcvt_d_l(dst, zero_reg);
4025  has_double_zero_reg_set_ = true;
4026  } else {
4027  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4028  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4029  if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0)) {
4030  fcvt_d_l(dst, zero_reg);
4031  } else {
4032  li(scratch, Operand(src));
4033  fmv_d_x(dst, scratch);
4034  }
4035  }
4036 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
4037  if (dst == kDoubleRegZero) {
4038  DCHECK(src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0));
4039  fcvt_d_w(dst, zero_reg);
4040  has_double_zero_reg_set_ = true;
4041  } else {
4042  // Todo: need to clear the stack content?
4043  if (src == base::bit_cast<uint64_t>(0.0)) {
4044  fcvt_d_w(dst, zero_reg);
4045  } else {
4046  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4047  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4048  uint32_t low_32 = src & 0xffffffffull;
4049  uint32_t up_32 = src >> 32;
4050  AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(-8));
4051  li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(low_32)));
4052  Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 0));
4053  li(scratch, Operand(static_cast<int32_t>(up_32)));
4054  Sw(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 4));
4055  LoadDouble(dst, MemOperand(sp, 0));
4056  AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(8));
4057  }
4058  }
4059 #endif
4060  }
4061 }
4062 
4063 void MacroAssembler::CompareI(Register rd, Register rs, const Operand& rt,
4064  Condition cond) {
4065  switch (cond) {
4066  case eq:
4067  Seq(rd, rs, rt);
4068  break;
4069  case ne:
4070  Sne(rd, rs, rt);
4071  break;
4072 
4073  // Signed comparison.
4074  case greater:
4075  Sgt(rd, rs, rt);
4076  break;
4077  case greater_equal:
4078  Sge(rd, rs, rt); // rs >= rt
4079  break;
4080  case less:
4081  Slt(rd, rs, rt); // rs < rt
4082  break;
4083  case less_equal:
4084  Sle(rd, rs, rt); // rs <= rt
4085  break;
4086 
4087  // Unsigned comparison.
4088  case Ugreater:
4089  Sgtu(rd, rs, rt); // rs > rt
4090  break;
4091  case Ugreater_equal:
4092  Sgeu(rd, rs, rt); // rs >= rt
4093  break;
4094  case Uless:
4095  Sltu(rd, rs, rt); // rs < rt
4096  break;
4097  case Uless_equal:
4098  Sleu(rd, rs, rt); // rs <= rt
4099  break;
4100  case cc_always:
4101  UNREACHABLE();
4102  default:
4103  UNREACHABLE();
4104  }
4105 }
4106 
4107 // dest <- (condition != 0 ? zero : dest)
4108 void MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfConditionNotZero(Register dest,
4109  Register condition) {
4110  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZICOND)) {
4111  czero_nez(dest, dest, condition);
4112  } else {
4113  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4114  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4115  seqz(scratch, condition);
4116  // neg + and may be more efficient than mul(dest, dest, scratch)
4117  neg(scratch, scratch); // 0 is still 0, 1 becomes all 1s
4118  And(dest, dest, scratch);
4119  }
4120 }
4121 
4122 // dest <- (condition == 0 ? 0 : dest)
4123 void MacroAssembler::LoadZeroIfConditionZero(Register dest,
4124  Register condition) {
4125  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZICOND)) {
4126  czero_eqz(dest, dest, condition);
4127  } else {
4128  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4129  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4130  snez(scratch, condition);
4131  // neg + and may be more efficient than mul(dest, dest, scratch);
4132  neg(scratch, scratch); // 0 is still 0, 1 becomes all 1s
4133  And(dest, dest, scratch);
4134  }
4135 }

4137 void MacroAssembler::Clz32(Register rd, Register xx) {
4138  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4139 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4140  clzw(rd, xx);
4141 #else
4142  clz(rd, xx);
4143 #endif
4144  } else {
4145  // 32 bit unsigned in lower word: count number of leading zeros.
4146  // int n = 32;
4147  // unsigned y;
4148 
4149  // y = x >>16; if (y != 0) { n = n -16; x = y; }
4150  // y = x >> 8; if (y != 0) { n = n - 8; x = y; }
4151  // y = x >> 4; if (y != 0) { n = n - 4; x = y; }
4152  // y = x >> 2; if (y != 0) { n = n - 2; x = y; }
4153  // y = x >> 1; if (y != 0) {rd = n - 2; return;}
4154  // rd = n - x;
4155 
4156  Label L0, L1, L2, L3, L4;
4157  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4158  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4159  Register x = rd;
4160  Register y = temps.Acquire();
4161  Register n = temps.Acquire();
4162  DCHECK(xx != y && xx != n);
4163  Move(x, xx);
4164  li(n, Operand(32));
4165 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4166  Srl32(y, x, 16);
4167  BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4168  Move(x, y);
4169  Add32(n, n, -16);
4170  bind(&L0);
4171  Srl32(y, x, 8);
4172  BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4173  Add32(n, n, -8);
4174  Move(x, y);
4175  bind(&L1);
4176  Srl32(y, x, 4);
4177  BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4178  Add32(n, n, -4);
4179  Move(x, y);
4180  bind(&L2);
4181  Srl32(y, x, 2);
4182  BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4183  Add32(n, n, -2);
4184  Move(x, y);
4185  bind(&L3);
4186  Srl32(y, x, 1);
4187  Sub32(rd, n, x);
4188  BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4189  Add32(rd, n, -2);
4190  bind(&L4);
4191 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
4192  SrlWord(y, x, 16);
4193  BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4194  Move(x, y);
4195  AddWord(n, n, -16);
4196  bind(&L0);
4197  SrlWord(y, x, 8);
4198  BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4199  AddWord(n, n, -8);
4200  Move(x, y);
4201  bind(&L1);
4202  SrlWord(y, x, 4);
4203  BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4204  AddWord(n, n, -4);
4205  Move(x, y);
4206  bind(&L2);
4207  SrlWord(y, x, 2);
4208  BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4209  AddWord(n, n, -2);
4210  Move(x, y);
4211  bind(&L3);
4212  SrlWord(y, x, 1);
4213  SubWord(rd, n, x);
4214  BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4215  AddWord(rd, n, -2);
4216  bind(&L4);
4217 #endif
4218  }
4219 }
4220 
4221 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4222 void MacroAssembler::Clz64(Register rd, Register xx) {
4223  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4224  clz(rd, xx);
4225  } else {
4226  // 64 bit: count number of leading zeros.
4227  // int n = 64;
4228  // unsigned y;
4229 
4230  // y = x >>32; if (y != 0) { n = n - 32; x = y; }
4231  // y = x >>16; if (y != 0) { n = n - 16; x = y; }
4232  // y = x >> 8; if (y != 0) { n = n - 8; x = y; }
4233  // y = x >> 4; if (y != 0) { n = n - 4; x = y; }
4234  // y = x >> 2; if (y != 0) { n = n - 2; x = y; }
4235  // y = x >> 1; if (y != 0) {rd = n - 2; return;}
4236  // rd = n - x;
4237 
4238  Label L0, L1, L2, L3, L4, L5;
4239  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4240  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4241  Register x = rd;
4242  Register y = temps.Acquire();
4243  Register n = temps.Acquire();
4244  DCHECK(xx != y && xx != n);
4245  Move(x, xx);
4246  li(n, Operand(64));
4247  SrlWord(y, x, 32);
4248  BranchShort(&L0, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4249  Add32(n, n, -32);
4250  Move(x, y);
4251  bind(&L0);
4252  SrlWord(y, x, 16);
4253  BranchShort(&L1, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4254  Add32(n, n, -16);
4255  Move(x, y);
4256  bind(&L1);
4257  SrlWord(y, x, 8);
4258  BranchShort(&L2, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4259  Add32(n, n, -8);
4260  Move(x, y);
4261  bind(&L2);
4262  SrlWord(y, x, 4);
4263  BranchShort(&L3, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4264  Add32(n, n, -4);
4265  Move(x, y);
4266  bind(&L3);
4267  SrlWord(y, x, 2);
4268  BranchShort(&L4, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4269  Add32(n, n, -2);
4270  Move(x, y);
4271  bind(&L4);
4272  SrlWord(y, x, 1);
4273  Sub32(rd, n, x);
4274  BranchShort(&L5, eq, y, Operand(zero_reg));
4275  Add32(rd, n, -2);
4276  bind(&L5);
4277  }
4278 }
4279 #endif
4280 
4281 void MacroAssembler::Ctz32(Register rd, Register rs) {
4282  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4283 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4284  ctzw(rd, rs);
4285 #else
4286  ctz(rd, rs);
4287 #endif
4288  } else {
4289  // Convert trailing zeroes to trailing ones, and bits to their left
4290  // to zeroes.
4291  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4292  {
4293  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4294  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4295  AddWord(scratch, rs, -1);
4296  Xor(rd, scratch, rs);
4297  And(rd, rd, scratch);
4298  // Count number of leading zeroes.
4299  }
4300  Clz32(rd, rd);
4301  {
4302  // Subtract number of leading zeroes from 32 to get number of trailing
4303  // ones. Remember that the trailing ones were formerly trailing zeroes.
4304  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4305  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4306  li(scratch, 32);
4307  Sub32(rd, scratch, rd);
4308  }
4309  }
4310 }
4311 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4312 void MacroAssembler::Ctz64(Register rd, Register rs) {
4313  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4314  ctz(rd, rs);
4315  } else {
4316  // Convert trailing zeroes to trailing ones, and bits to their left
4317  // to zeroes.
4318  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4319  {
4320  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4321  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4322  AddWord(scratch, rs, -1);
4323  Xor(rd, scratch, rs);
4324  And(rd, rd, scratch);
4325  // Count number of leading zeroes.
4326  }
4327  Clz64(rd, rd);
4328  {
4329  // Subtract number of leading zeroes from 64 to get number of trailing
4330  // ones. Remember that the trailing ones were formerly trailing zeroes.
4331  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4332  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4333  li(scratch, 64);
4334  SubWord(rd, scratch, rd);
4335  }
4336  }
4337 }
4338 #endif
4339 void MacroAssembler::Popcnt32(Register rd, Register rs, Register scratch) {
4340  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4341 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4342  cpopw(rd, rs);
4343 #else
4344  cpop(rd, rs);
4345 #endif
4346  } else {
4347  DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
4348  DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
4349  // https://graphics.stanford.edu/~seander/bithacks.html#CountBitsSetParallel
4350  //
4351  // A generalization of the best bit counting method to integers of
4352  // bit-widths up to 128 (parameterized by type T) is this:
4353  //
4354  // v = v - ((v >> 1) & (T)~(T)0/3); // temp
4355  // v = (v & (T)~(T)0/15*3) + ((v >> 2) & (T)~(T)0/15*3); // temp
4356  // v = (v + (v >> 4)) & (T)~(T)0/255*15; // temp
4357  // c = (T)(v * ((T)~(T)0/255)) >> (sizeof(T) - 1) * BITS_PER_BYTE; //count
4358  //
4359  // There are algorithms which are faster in the cases where very few
4360  // bits are set but the algorithm here attempts to minimize the total
4361  // number of instructions executed even when a large number of bits
4362  // are set.
4363  // The number of instruction is 20.
4364  // uint32_t B0 = 0x55555555; // (T)~(T)0/3
4365  // uint32_t B1 = 0x33333333; // (T)~(T)0/15*3
4366  // uint32_t B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F; // (T)~(T)0/255*15
4367  // uint32_t value = 0x01010101; // (T)~(T)0/255
4368  uint32_t shift = 24;
4369  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4370  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4371  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
4372  Register value = temps.Acquire();
4373  DCHECK((rd != value) && (rs != value));
4374  li(value, 0x01010101); // value = 0x01010101;
4375  li(scratch2, 0x55555555); // B0 = 0x55555555;
4376  Srl32(scratch, rs, 1);
4377  And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4378  Sub32(scratch, rs, scratch);
4379  li(scratch2, 0x33333333); // B1 = 0x33333333;
4380  SllWord(rd, scratch2, 4);
4381  Or(scratch2, scratch2, rd);
4382  And(rd, scratch, scratch2);
4383  Srl32(scratch, scratch, 2);
4384  And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4385  Add32(scratch, rd, scratch);
4386  Srl32(rd, scratch, 4);
4387  Add32(rd, rd, scratch);
4388  li(scratch2, 0xF);
4389  Mul32(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F;
4390  And(rd, rd, scratch2);
4391  Mul32(rd, rd, value);
4392  Srl32(rd, rd, shift);
4393  }
4394 }
4395 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
4396 void MacroAssembler::Popcnt64(Register rd, Register rs, Register scratch) {
4397  if (CpuFeatures::IsSupported(ZBB)) {
4398  cpop(rd, rs);
4399  } else {
4400  DCHECK_NE(scratch, rs);
4401  DCHECK_NE(scratch, rd);
4402  // uint64_t B0 = 0x5555555555555555l; // (T)~(T)0/3
4403  // uint64_t B1 = 0x3333333333333333l; // (T)~(T)0/15*3
4404  // uint64_t B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fl; // (T)~(T)0/255*15
4405  // uint64_t value = 0x0101010101010101l; // (T)~(T)0/255
4406  // uint64_t shift = 24; // (sizeof(T) - 1) * BITS_PER_BYTE
4407  uint64_t shift = 24;
4408  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4409  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4410  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
4411  Register value = temps.Acquire();
4412  DCHECK((rd != value) && (rs != value));
4413  li(value, 0x1111111111111111l); // value = 0x1111111111111111l;
4414  li(scratch2, 5);
4415  Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B0 = 0x5555555555555555l;
4416  Srl64(scratch, rs, 1);
4417  And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4418  SubWord(scratch, rs, scratch);
4419  li(scratch2, 3);
4420  Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B1 = 0x3333333333333333l;
4421  And(rd, scratch, scratch2);
4422  Srl64(scratch, scratch, 2);
4423  And(scratch, scratch, scratch2);
4424  AddWord(scratch, rd, scratch);
4425  Srl64(rd, scratch, 4);
4426  AddWord(rd, rd, scratch);
4427  li(scratch2, 0xF);
4428  li(value, 0x0101010101010101l); // value = 0x0101010101010101l;
4429  Mul64(scratch2, value, scratch2); // B2 = 0x0F0F0F0F0F0F0F0Fl;
4430  And(rd, rd, scratch2);
4431  Mul64(rd, rd, value);
4432  SrlWord(rd, rd, Operand(32 + shift));
4433  }
4434 }
4435 #endif
4436 
4437 void MacroAssembler::TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(Register result,
4438  DoubleRegister double_input,
4439  Label* done) {
4440  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4441  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4442  // if scratch == 1, exception happens during truncation
4443  Trunc_w_d(result, double_input, scratch);
4444  // If we had no exceptions (i.e., scratch==1) we are done.
4445  Branch(done, eq, scratch, Operand(1));
4446 }
4447 
4448 void MacroAssembler::TruncateDoubleToI(Isolate* isolate, Zone* zone,
4449  Register result,
4450  DoubleRegister double_input,
4451  StubCallMode stub_mode) {
4452  Label done;
4453 
4454  TryInlineTruncateDoubleToI(result, double_input, &done);
4455 
4456  // If we fell through then inline version didn't succeed - call stub
4457  // instead.
4458  push(ra);
4459  SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleSize)); // Put input on stack.
4460  fsd(double_input, sp, 0);
4461 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4462  if (stub_mode == StubCallMode::kCallWasmRuntimeStub) {
4463  Call(static_cast<Address>(Builtin::kDoubleToI), RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL);
4464 #else
4465  // For balance.
4466  if (false) {
4467 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
4468  } else {
4469  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kDoubleToI);
4470  }
4471  LoadWord(result, MemOperand(sp, 0));
4472 
4473  AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(kDoubleSize));
4474  pop(ra);
4475 
4476  bind(&done);
4477 }

4479 // BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK checks that conditional jump arguments are correct.
4480 #define BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt) \
4481  DCHECK((cond == cc_always && rs == zero_reg && rt.rm() == zero_reg) || \
4482  (cond != cc_always && (rs != zero_reg || rt.rm() != zero_reg)))
4483

4496 void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L) {
4497  if (L->is_bound()) {
4498  if (is_near(L)) {
4499  BranchShort(L);
4500  } else {
4501  BranchLong(L);
4502  }
4503  } else {
4504  if (is_trampoline_emitted()) {
4505  BranchLong(L);
4506  } else {
4507  BranchShort(L);
4508  }
4509  }
4510 }
4511 
4512 void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4513  const Operand& rt, Label::Distance distance) {
4514  if (L->is_bound()) {
4515  if (!BranchShortCheck(0, L, cond, rs, rt)) {
4516  if (cond != cc_always) {
4517  Label skip;
4518  Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4519  BlockPoolsScope block_pools(this, 3 * kInstrSize);
4520  BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4521  BranchLong(L);
4522  bind(&skip);
4523  } else {
4524  BranchLong(L);
4525  EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4526  }
4527  }
4528  } else {
4529  DEBUG_PRINTF("\t Branch is_trampoline_emitted %d\n",
4530  is_trampoline_emitted());
4531  if (is_trampoline_emitted()) {
4532  if (cond != cc_always) {
4533  Label skip;
4534  Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4535  BlockPoolsScope block_pools(this, 3 * kInstrSize);
4536  BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4537  BranchLong(L);
4538  bind(&skip);
4539  } else {
4540  BranchLong(L);
4541  EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4542  }
4543  } else {
4544  BranchShort(L, cond, rs, rt);
4545  }
4546  }
4547 }
4548 
4549 void MacroAssembler::Branch(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4550  RootIndex index, Label::Distance distance) {
4551  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4552  Register right = temps.Acquire();
4553  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4554  Register left = rs;
4555  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index) &&
4556  is_int12(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index))) {
4557  left = temps.Acquire();
4558  Sll32(left, rs, 0);
4559  }
4560  LoadTaggedRoot(right, index);
4561  Branch(L, cond, left, Operand(right));
4562  } else {
4563  LoadRoot(right, index);
4564  Branch(L, cond, rs, Operand(right));
4565  }
4566 }

4568 void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedAndBranch(Label* label, Condition cond,
4569  Register r1, const Operand& r2,
4570  bool need_link) {
4571  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
4572  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4573  Register scratch0 = temps.Acquire();
4574  Sll32(scratch0, r1, 0);
4575  if (IsZero(r2)) {
4576  Branch(label, cond, scratch0, Operand(zero_reg));
4577  } else {
4578  Register scratch1 = temps.Acquire();
4579  if (r2.is_reg()) {
4580  Sll32(scratch1, r2.rm(), 0);
4581  } else {
4582  li(scratch1, r2);
4583  Sll32(scratch1, scratch1, 0);
4584  }
4585  Branch(label, cond, scratch0, Operand(scratch1));
4586  }
4587  } else {
4588  Branch(label, cond, r1, r2);
4589  }
4590 }

4641 
4642 bool MacroAssembler::BranchShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L, Condition cond,
4643  Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
4644  DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4645  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4646  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4647  Register scratch = no_reg;
4648  if (!rt.is_reg()) {
4649  if (rt.immediate() == 0) {
4650  scratch = zero_reg;
4651  } else {
4652  scratch = temps.Acquire();
4653  li(scratch, rt);
4654  }
4655  } else {
4656  scratch = rt.rm();
4657  }
4658  {
4659  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4660  switch (cond) {
4661  case cc_always:
4662  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4663  j(offset);
4664  EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
4665  break;
4666  case eq:
4667  // rs == rt
4668  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4669  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4670  j(offset);
4671  } else {
4672  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4673  beq(rs, scratch, offset);
4674  }
4675  break;
4676  case ne:
4677  // rs != rt
4678  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4679  break; // No code needs to be emitted
4680  } else {
4681  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4682  bne(rs, scratch, offset);
4683  }
4684  break;
4685 
4686  // Signed comparison.
4687  case greater:
4688  // rs > rt
4689  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4690  break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4691  } else {
4692  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4693  bgt(rs, scratch, offset);
4694  }
4695  break;
4696  case greater_equal:
4697  // rs >= rt
4698  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4699  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4700  j(offset);
4701  } else {
4702  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4703  bge(rs, scratch, offset);
4704  }
4705  break;
4706  case less:
4707  // rs < rt
4708  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4709  break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4710  } else {
4711  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4712  blt(rs, scratch, offset);
4713  }
4714  break;
4715  case less_equal:
4716  // rs <= rt
4717  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4718  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4719  j(offset);
4720  } else {
4721  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4722  ble(rs, scratch, offset);
4723  }
4724  break;
4725 
4726  // Unsigned comparison.
4727  case Ugreater:
4728  // rs > rt
4729  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4730  break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4731  } else {
4732  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4733  bgtu(rs, scratch, offset);
4734  }
4735  break;
4736  case Ugreater_equal:
4737  // rs >= rt
4738  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4739  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4740  j(offset);
4741  } else {
4742  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4743  bgeu(rs, scratch, offset);
4744  }
4745  break;
4746  case Uless:
4747  // rs < rt
4748  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4749  break; // No code needs to be emitted.
4750  } else {
4751  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4752  bltu(rs, scratch, offset);
4753  }
4754  break;
4755  case Uless_equal:
4756  // rs <= rt
4757  if (rt.is_reg() && rs == rt.rm()) {
4758  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4759  j(offset);
4760  } else {
4761  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4762  bleu(rs, scratch, offset);
4763  }
4764  break;
4765  case Condition::overflow:
4766  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4767  bnez(rs, offset);
4768  break;
4769  case Condition::no_overflow:
4770  if (!CalculateOffset(L, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset13)) return false;
4771  beqz(rs, offset);
4772  break;
4773  default:
4774  UNREACHABLE();
4775  }
4776  }
4777 
4778  CheckTrampolinePoolQuick(1);
4779  return true;
4780 }

4784  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4785 
4786  if (!L) {
4787  DCHECK(is_int13(offset));
4788  return BranchShortHelper(offset, nullptr, cond, rs, rt);
4789  } else {
4790  DCHECK_EQ(offset, 0);
4791  return BranchShortHelper(0, L, cond, rs, rt);
4792  }
4793 }

4832 void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLink(Label* L, Condition cond, Register rs,
4833  const Operand& rt) {

4838  BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4839  BranchAndLinkLong(L);
4840  bind(&skip);
4841  }
4842  } else {
4843  if (is_trampoline_emitted()) {
4844  Label skip;
4845  Condition neg_cond = NegateCondition(cond);
4846  BranchShort(&skip, neg_cond, rs, rt);
4847  BranchAndLinkLong(L);
4848  bind(&skip);
4849  } else {
4850  BranchAndLinkShortCheck(0, L, cond, rs, rt);
4851  }
4852  }

4865 
4866 void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShort(Label* L) {
4867  BranchAndLinkShortHelper(0, L);
4868 }
4869 
4870 // Pre r6 we need to use a bgezal or bltzal, but they can't be used directly
4871 // with the slt instructions. We could use sub or add instead but we would miss
4872 // overflow cases, so we keep slt and add an intermediate third instruction.
4873 bool MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShortHelper(int32_t offset, Label* L,
4874  Condition cond, Register rs,
4875  const Operand& rt) {
4876  DCHECK(L == nullptr || offset == 0);
4877  if (!is_near(L, OffsetSize::kOffset21)) return false;
4878 
4879  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
4880  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
4881  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4882 
4883  if (cond == cc_always) {
4884  offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4885  jal(offset);
4886  } else {
4887  Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs,
4888  Operand(GetRtAsRegisterHelper(rt, scratch)));
4889  offset = GetOffset(offset, L, OffsetSize::kOffset21);
4890  jal(offset);
4891  }
4892 
4893  return true;
4894 }
4895 
4896 bool MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkShortCheck(int32_t offset, Label* L,
4897  Condition cond, Register rs,
4898  const Operand& rt) {
4899  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4900 
4901  if (!L) {
4902  DCHECK(is_int21(offset));
4903  return BranchAndLinkShortHelper(offset, nullptr, cond, rs, rt);
4904  } else {
4905  DCHECK_EQ(offset, 0);
4906  return BranchAndLinkShortHelper(0, L, cond, rs, rt);
4907  }
4908 }

4926 
4927 MemOperand MacroAssembler::ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
4928  ExternalReference reference, Register scratch) {
4929  if (root_array_available()) {
4930  if (reference.IsIsolateFieldId()) {
4931  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, reference.offset_from_root_register());
4932  }
4933  if (options().enable_root_relative_access) {
4934  int64_t offset =
4935  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4936  if (is_int32(offset)) {
4937  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4938  }
4939  }
4940  if (root_array_available_ && options().isolate_independent_code) {
4941  if (IsAddressableThroughRootRegister(isolate(), reference)) {
4942  // Some external references can be efficiently loaded as an offset from
4943  // kRootRegister.
4944  intptr_t offset =
4945  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReference(isolate(), reference);
4946  CHECK(is_int32(offset));
4947  return MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset));
4948  } else {
4949  // Otherwise, do a memory load from the external reference table.
4950  DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4951  LoadWord(scratch,
4952  MemOperand(kRootRegister,
4953  RootRegisterOffsetForExternalReferenceTableEntry(
4954  isolate(), reference)));
4955  return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4956  }
4957  }
4958  }
4959  DCHECK(scratch.is_valid());
4960  li(scratch, reference);
4961  return MemOperand(scratch, 0);
4962 }
4963 
4964 void MacroAssembler::LoadRootRegisterOffset(Register destination,
4965  intptr_t offset) {
4966  if (offset == 0) {
4967  Move(destination, kRootRegister);
4968  } else {
4969  AddWord(destination, kRootRegister, Operand(offset));
4970  }
4971 }
4972 
4973 void MacroAssembler::Jump(Register target, Condition cond, Register rs,
4974  const Operand& rt) {
4975  DCHECK_WITH_MSG(t0 != target,
4976  "don't use x5 as target for jumps to avoid RAS pollution");
4977  if (cond == cc_always) {
4978  jr(target);
4979  DEBUG_PRINTF("\tCheckTrampolinePool pc_offset:%d %d\n", pc_offset(),
4980  next_buffer_check() - ConstpoolComputesize());
4981  if (!is_trampoline_emitted() && v8_flags.debug_code &&
4982  pc_offset() >= (next_buffer_check() - ConstpoolComputesize())) {
4983  // Debug mode will emit more instrs than Release mode.
4984  // so we need to check trampoline pool before Constant pool.
4985  // Here need to emit trampoline first.
4986  // Jump(ra, al) will block trampoline pool for 1 instr.
4987  nop();
4988  CheckTrampolinePool();
4989  }
4990  ForceConstantPoolEmissionWithoutJump();
4991  } else {
4992  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
4993  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
4994  Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
4995  jr(target);
4996  }
4997 }
4998 
4999 void MacroAssembler::Jump(intptr_t target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
5000  Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5001  Label skip;
5002  if (cond != cc_always) {
5003  Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
5004  }
5005  {
5006  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5007  li(t6, Operand(target, rmode));
5008  Jump(t6, al, zero_reg, Operand(zero_reg));
5009  EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
5010  bind(&skip);
5011  }
5012 }
5013 
5014 void MacroAssembler::Jump(Address target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode, Condition cond,
5015  Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5016  DCHECK(!RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
5017  Jump(static_cast<intptr_t>(target), rmode, cond, rs, rt);
5018 }
5019 
5020 void MacroAssembler::Jump(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
5021  Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5022  DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
5023  DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
5024  Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
5025 
5026  Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
5027  if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
5028  // Inline the trampoline.
5029  Label skip;
5030  if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
5031  TailCallBuiltin(builtin);
5032  bind(&skip);
5033  return;
5034  }
5035  DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
5036  if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
5037  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
5038  DCHECK(is_int32(index));
5039  Label skip;
5040  if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
5041  RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
5042  static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5043  GenPCRelativeJump(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5044  bind(&skip);
5045  } else {
5046  Jump(code.address(), rmode, cond);
5047  }
5048 }
5049 
5050 void MacroAssembler::Jump(const ExternalReference& reference) {
5051  li(t6, reference);
5052  Jump(t6);
5053 }
5054 
5055 // Note: To call gcc-compiled C code on riscv64, you must call through t6.
5056 void MacroAssembler::Call(Register target, Condition cond, Register rs,
5057  const Operand& rt) {
5058  DCHECK_WITH_MSG(t0 != target,
5059  "don't use x5 as target for calls to avoid RAS pollution");
5060  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5061  if (cond == cc_always) {
5062  jalr(ra, target, 0);
5063  } else {
5064  BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK(cond, rs, rt);
5065  Branch(kInstrSize * 2, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
5066  jalr(ra, target, 0);
5067  }
5068 }
5069 
5070 void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRootAndBranch(const Register& obj,
5071  RootIndex index, Condition cc,
5072  Label* target) {
5073  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5074  AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(obj);
5075  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5076  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index)) {
5077  CompareTaggedAndBranch(target, cc, obj, Operand(ReadOnlyRootPtr(index)));
5078  return;
5079  }
5080  // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5081  DCHECK(base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5082  RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot));
5083  Register temp = temps.Acquire();
5084  DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
5085  LoadRoot(temp, index);
5086  CompareTaggedAndBranch(target, cc, obj, Operand(temp));
5087 }
5088 // Compare the object in a register to a value from the root list.
5089 void MacroAssembler::CompareRootAndBranch(const Register& obj, RootIndex index,
5090  Condition cc, Label* target,
5091  ComparisonMode mode) {
5092  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5093  if (mode == ComparisonMode::kFullPointer ||
5094  !base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5095  RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
5096  // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5097  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5098  Register temp = temps.Acquire();
5099  DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
5100  LoadRoot(temp, index);
5101  Branch(target, cc, obj, Operand(temp));
5102  return;
5103  }
5104  CompareTaggedRootAndBranch(obj, index, cc, target);
5105 }
5106 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5107 // Compare the tagged object in a register to a value from the root list
5108 // and put 0 into result if equal or 1 otherwise.
5109 void MacroAssembler::CompareTaggedRoot(const Register& with, RootIndex index,
5110  const Register& result) {
5111  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5112  AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(with);
5113  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL && RootsTable::IsReadOnly(index)) {
5114  Li(result, ReadOnlyRootPtr(index));
5115  MacroAssembler::CmpTagged(result, with, result);
5116  return;
5117  }
5118  // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5119  DCHECK(base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5120  RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot));
5121  LoadRoot(result, index);
5122  MacroAssembler::CmpTagged(result, with, result);
5123 }
5124 
5125 void MacroAssembler::CompareRoot(const Register& obj, RootIndex index,
5126  const Register& result, ComparisonMode mode) {
5127  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5128  if (mode == ComparisonMode::kFullPointer ||
5129  !base::IsInRange(index, RootIndex::kFirstStrongOrReadOnlyRoot,
5130  RootIndex::kLastStrongOrReadOnlyRoot)) {
5131  // Some smi roots contain system pointer size values like stack limits.
5132  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5133  Register temp = temps.Acquire();
5134  DCHECK(!AreAliased(obj, temp));
5135  LoadRoot(temp, index);
5136  CompareI(result, obj, Operand(temp),
5137  Condition::ne); // result is 0 if equal or 1 otherwise
5138  return;
5139  }
5140  // FIXME: check that 0/1 in result is expected for all CompareRoot callers
5141  CompareTaggedRoot(obj, index, result);
5142 }
5143 #endif

5145 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfIsInRange(Register value, unsigned lower_limit,
5146  unsigned higher_limit,
5147  Label* on_in_range) {
5148  if (lower_limit != 0) {
5149  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5150  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5151  SubWord(scratch, value, Operand(lower_limit));
5152  Branch(on_in_range, Uless_equal, scratch,
5153  Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
5154  } else {
5155  Branch(on_in_range, Uless_equal, value,
5156  Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit));
5157  }
5158 }
5159 
5160 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfMarking(Label* is_marking,
5161  Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
5162  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5163  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5164  LoadWord(scratch,
5165  MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::is_marking_flag_offset()));
5166  Branch(is_marking, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5167 }
5168 
5169 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfNotMarking(Label* not_marking,
5170  Label::Distance condition_met_distance) {
5171  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5172  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5173  LoadWord(scratch,
5174  MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::is_marking_flag_offset()));
5175  Branch(not_marking, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5176 }

5178 // The calculated offset is either:
5179 // * the 'target' input unmodified if this is a Wasm call, or
5180 // * the offset of the target from the current PC, in instructions, for any
5181 // other type of call.
5182 int64_t MacroAssembler::CalculateTargetOffset(Address target,
5183  RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
5184  uint8_t* pc) {
5185  int64_t offset = static_cast<int64_t>(target);
5186  if (rmode == RelocInfo::WASM_CALL || rmode == RelocInfo::WASM_STUB_CALL) {
5187  // The target of WebAssembly calls is still an index instead of an actual
5188  // address at this point, and needs to be encoded as-is.
5189  return offset;
5190  }
5191  offset -= reinterpret_cast<int64_t>(pc);
5192  DCHECK_EQ(offset % kInstrSize, 0);
5193  return offset;
5194 }
5195 
5196 void MacroAssembler::Call(Address target, RelocInfo::Mode rmode, Condition cond,
5197  Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5198  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5199  if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
5200  int64_t offset = CalculateTargetOffset(target, rmode, pc_);
5201  DCHECK(is_int32(offset));
5202  near_call(static_cast<int>(offset), rmode);
5203  } else {
5204  li(t6, Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(target), rmode), ADDRESS_LOAD);
5205  Call(t6, cond, rs, rt);
5206  }
5207 }
5208 
5209 void MacroAssembler::Call(Handle<Code> code, RelocInfo::Mode rmode,
5210  Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5211  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5212  DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
5213  DCHECK_IMPLIES(options().isolate_independent_code,
5214  Builtins::IsIsolateIndependentBuiltin(*code));
5215 
5216  Builtin builtin = Builtin::kNoBuiltinId;
5217  if (isolate()->builtins()->IsBuiltinHandle(code, &builtin)) {
5218  // Inline the trampoline.
5219  CHECK_EQ(cond, Condition::al); // Implement if necessary.
5220  CallBuiltin(builtin);
5221  return;
5222  }
5223 
5224  DCHECK(RelocInfo::IsCodeTarget(rmode));
5225 
5226  if (CanUseNearCallOrJump(rmode)) {
5227  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
5228  DCHECK(is_int32(index));
5229  Label skip;
5230  if (cond != al) Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), rs, rt);
5231  RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
5232  static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5233  GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5234  bind(&skip);
5235  } else {
5236  Call(code.address(), rmode);
5237  }
5238 }
5239 
5240 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(Register builtin_index,
5241  Register target) {
5242 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5243  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 8);
5244 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5245  static_assert(kSystemPointerSize == 4);
5246 #endif
5247  static_assert(kSmiTagSize == 1);
5248  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
5249 
5250  // The builtin register contains the builtin index as a Smi.
5251  SmiUntag(target, builtin_index);
5252  CalcScaledAddress(target, kRootRegister, target, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5253  LoadWord(target,
5254  MemOperand(target, IsolateData::builtin_entry_table_offset()));
5255 }
5256 
5257 void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltinByIndex(Register builtin_index,
5258  Register target) {
5259  LoadEntryFromBuiltinIndex(builtin_index, target);
5260  Call(target);
5261 }
5262 
5263 void MacroAssembler::CallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
5264  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this, CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("call", builtin));
5265  switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
5266  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
5267  li(t6, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
5268  Call(t6);
5269  break;
5270  }
5271  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
5272  near_call(static_cast<int>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
5273  break;
5274  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect: {
5275  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5276  Call(t6);
5277  break;
5278  }
5279  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
5280  if (options().use_pc_relative_calls_and_jumps_for_mksnapshot) {
5281  Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
5282  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
5283  DCHECK(is_int32(index));
5284  RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
5285  static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5286  GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5287  } else {
5288  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5289  Call(t6);
5290  }
5291  break;
5292  }
5293  }
5294 }
5295 
5296 void MacroAssembler::TailCallBuiltin(Builtin builtin, Condition cond,
5297  Register type, Operand range) {
5298  Label done;
5299  Branch(&done, NegateCondition(cond), type, range);
5300  TailCallBuiltin(builtin);
5301  bind(&done);
5302 }
5303 
5304 void MacroAssembler::TailCallBuiltin(Builtin builtin) {
5305  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(this,
5306  CommentForOffHeapTrampoline("tail call", builtin));
5307  switch (options().builtin_call_jump_mode) {
5308  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kAbsolute: {
5309  li(t6, Operand(BuiltinEntry(builtin), RelocInfo::OFF_HEAP_TARGET));
5310  Jump(t6);
5311  break;
5312  }
5313  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kPCRelative:
5314  near_jump(static_cast<int>(builtin), RelocInfo::NEAR_BUILTIN_ENTRY);
5315  break;
5316  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kIndirect: {
5317  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5318  Jump(t6);
5319  break;
5320  }
5321  case BuiltinCallJumpMode::kForMksnapshot: {
5322  if (options().use_pc_relative_calls_and_jumps_for_mksnapshot) {
5323  Handle<Code> code = isolate()->builtins()->code_handle(builtin);
5324  EmbeddedObjectIndex index = AddEmbeddedObject(code);
5325  DCHECK(is_int32(index));
5326  RecordRelocInfo(RelocInfo::RELATIVE_CODE_TARGET,
5327  static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5328  GenPCRelativeJump(t6, static_cast<int32_t>(index));
5329  } else {
5330  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(builtin, t6);
5331  Jump(t6);
5332  }
5333  break;
5334  }
5335  }
5336 }

5338 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin builtin,
5339  Register destination) {
5340  LoadWord(destination, EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(builtin));
5341 }

5343 MemOperand MacroAssembler::EntryFromBuiltinAsOperand(Builtin builtin) {

5346  IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(builtin));

5349 void MacroAssembler::PatchAndJump(Address target) {
5350  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5351  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5352  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5353  auipc(scratch, 0); // Load PC into scratch
5354  LoadWord(t6, MemOperand(scratch, kInstrSize * 4));
5355  jr(t6);
5356  nop(); // For alignment
5357 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
5358  DCHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uint64_t>(pc_) % 8, 0);
5359 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5360  DCHECK_EQ(reinterpret_cast<uint32_t>(pc_) % 4, 0);
5361 #endif
5362  *reinterpret_cast<uintptr_t*>(pc_) = target; // pc_ should be align.
5363  pc_ += sizeof(uintptr_t);
5364 }
5365 
5366 void MacroAssembler::StoreReturnAddressAndCall(Register target) {
5367  // This generates the final instruction sequence for calls to C functions
5368  // once an exit frame has been constructed.
5369  //
5370  // Note that this assumes the caller code (i.e. the InstructionStream object
5371  // currently being generated) is immovable or that the callee function cannot
5372  // trigger GC, since the callee function will return to it.
5373  //
5374  // Compute the return address in lr to return to after the jump below. The
5375  // pc is already at '+ 8' from the current instruction; but return is after
5376  // three instructions, so add another 4 to pc to get the return address.
5377  //
5378  Assembler::BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5379  int kNumInstructionsToJump = 5;
5380  if (v8_flags.riscv_c_extension) kNumInstructionsToJump = 4;
5381  Label find_ra;
5382  // Adjust the value in ra to point to the correct return location, one
5383  // instruction past the real call into C code (the jalr(t6)), and push it.
5384  // This is the return address of the exit frame.
5385  auipc(ra, 0); // Set ra the current PC
5386  bind(&find_ra);
5387  AddWord(ra, ra,
5388  (kNumInstructionsToJump + 1) *
5389  kInstrSize); // Set ra to insn after the call
5390 
5391  // This spot was reserved in EnterExitFrame.
5392  StoreWord(ra, MemOperand(sp));
5393  AddWord(sp, sp, -kCArgsSlotsSize);
5394  // Stack is still aligned.
5395 
5396  // Call the C routine.
5397  Mv(t6,
5398  target); // Function pointer to t6 to conform to ABI for PIC.
5399  jalr(t6);
5400  // Make sure the stored 'ra' points to this position.
5401  DCHECK_EQ(kNumInstructionsToJump, InstructionsGeneratedSince(&find_ra));
5402 }
5403 
5404 void MacroAssembler::Ret(Condition cond, Register rs, const Operand& rt) {
5405  Jump(ra, cond, rs, rt);
5406 }
5407 
5408 void MacroAssembler::BranchLong(Label* L) {
5409  // Generate position independent long branch.
5410  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5411  int32_t imm;
5412  imm = branch_long_offset(L);
5413  if (L->is_bound() && is_intn(imm, Assembler::kJumpOffsetBits) &&
5414  (imm & 1) == 0) {
5415  j(imm);
5416  NOP();
5417  EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
5418  return;
5419  }
5420  GenPCRelativeJump(t6, imm);
5421  EmitConstPoolWithJumpIfNeeded();
5422 }
5423 
5424 void MacroAssembler::BranchAndLinkLong(Label* L) {
5425  // Generate position independent long branch and link.
5426  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5427  int32_t imm;
5428  imm = branch_long_offset(L);
5429  if (L->is_bound() && is_intn(imm, Assembler::kJumpOffsetBits) &&
5430  (imm & 1) == 0) {
5431  jal(t6, imm);
5432  NOP();
5433  return;
5434  }
5435  GenPCRelativeJumpAndLink(t6, imm);
5436 }

5438 void MacroAssembler::DropAndRet(int drop) {
5439  AddWord(sp, sp, drop * kSystemPointerSize);
5440  Ret();
5441 }

5443 void MacroAssembler::DropAndRet(int drop, Condition cond, Register r1,
5444  const Operand& r2) {
5445  // Both Drop and Ret need to be conditional.
5446  Label skip;
5447  if (cond != cc_always) {
5448  Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), r1, r2);
5449  }
5450 
5451  Drop(drop);
5452  Ret();
5453 
5454  if (cond != cc_always) {
5455  bind(&skip);
5456  }
5457 }
5458 
5459 void MacroAssembler::Drop(int count, Condition cond, Register reg,
5460  const Operand& op) {
5461  if (count <= 0) {
5462  return;
5463  }
5464 
5465  Label skip;
5466 
5467  if (cond != al) {
5468  Branch(&skip, NegateCondition(cond), reg, op);
5469  }
5470 
5471  AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(count * kSystemPointerSize));
5472 
5473  if (cond != al) {
5474  bind(&skip);
5475  }
5476 }

5478 void MacroAssembler::Swap(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register scratch) {
5479  if (scratch == no_reg) {
5480  Xor(reg1, reg1, Operand(reg2));
5481  Xor(reg2, reg2, Operand(reg1));
5482  Xor(reg1, reg1, Operand(reg2));
5483  } else {
5484  Mv(scratch, reg1);
5485  Mv(reg1, reg2);
5486  Mv(reg2, scratch);
5487  }
5488 }

5490 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
5491 // Enforce alignment of sp.
5492 void MacroAssembler::EnforceStackAlignment() {
5493  int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
5494  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
5495 
5496  uint64_t frame_alignment_mask = ~(static_cast<uint64_t>(frame_alignment) - 1);
5497  And(sp, sp, Operand(frame_alignment_mask));
5498 }
5499 #endif

5503 void MacroAssembler::LoadAddress(Register dst, Label* target,
5504  RelocInfo::Mode rmode) {
5505  int32_t offset;
5506  if (CalculateOffset(target, &offset, OffsetSize::kOffset32)) {
5507  CHECK(is_int32(offset + 0x800));
5508  int32_t Hi20 = (((int32_t)offset + 0x800) >> 12);
5509  int32_t Lo12 = (int32_t)offset << 20 >> 20;
5510  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
5511  auipc(dst, Hi20);
5512  AddWord(dst, dst, Lo12);
5513  } else {
5514  uintptr_t address = jump_address(target);
5515  li(dst, Operand(address, rmode), ADDRESS_LOAD);
5516  }
5517 }

5520  int case_value_base, Label** labels,
5521  int num_labels) {
5522  GenerateSwitchTable(
5523  value, num_labels, [&labels](auto i) { return labels[i]; },
5524  case_value_base, scratch);
5525 }

5541 void MacroAssembler::PushArray(Register array, Register size,
5542  PushArrayOrder order) {
5543  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5544  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5545  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
5546  Label loop, entry;
5547  if (order == PushArrayOrder::kReverse) {
5548  Mv(scratch, zero_reg);
5549  jmp(&entry);
5550  bind(&loop);
5551  CalcScaledAddress(scratch2, array, scratch, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5552  LoadWord(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
5553  push(scratch2);
5554  AddWord(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
5555  bind(&entry);
5556  Branch(&loop, less, scratch, Operand(size));
5557  } else {
5558  Mv(scratch, size);
5559  jmp(&entry);
5560  bind(&loop);
5561  CalcScaledAddress(scratch2, array, scratch, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5562  LoadWord(scratch2, MemOperand(scratch2));
5563  push(scratch2);
5564  bind(&entry);
5565  AddWord(scratch, scratch, Operand(-1));
5566  Branch(&loop, greater_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5567  }
5568 }
5569 
5570 void MacroAssembler::Push(Handle<HeapObject> handle) {
5571  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5572  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5573  li(scratch, Operand(handle));
5574  push(scratch);
5575 }
5576 
5577 // ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
5578 // Exception handling.
5579 
5580 void MacroAssembler::PushStackHandler() {
5581  // Adjust this code if not the case.
5582  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kSize == 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
5583  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0 * kSystemPointerSize);
5584 
5585  Push(Smi::zero()); // Padding.
5586 
5587  // Link the current handler as the next handler.
5588  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5589  Register handler_address = temps.Acquire();
5590  li(handler_address,
5591  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
5592  Register handler = temps.Acquire();
5593  LoadWord(handler, MemOperand(handler_address));
5594  push(handler);
5595 
5596  // Set this new handler as the current one.
5597  StoreWord(sp, MemOperand(handler_address));
5598 }
5599 
5600 void MacroAssembler::PopStackHandler() {
5601  static_assert(StackHandlerConstants::kNextOffset == 0);
5602  pop(a1);
5603  AddWord(sp, sp,
5604  Operand(static_cast<intptr_t>(StackHandlerConstants::kSize -
5605  kSystemPointerSize)));
5606  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5607  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
5608  li(scratch,
5609  ExternalReference::Create(IsolateAddressId::kHandlerAddress, isolate()));
5610  StoreWord(a1, MemOperand(scratch));
5611 }
5612 
5613 void MacroAssembler::FPUCanonicalizeNaN(const DoubleRegister dst,
5614  const DoubleRegister src) {
5615  // Subtracting 0.0 preserves all inputs except for signalling NaNs, which
5616  // become quiet NaNs. We use fsub rather than fadd because fsub preserves -0.0
5617  // inputs: -0.0 + 0.0 = 0.0, but -0.0 - 0.0 = -0.0.
5618  if (!IsDoubleZeroRegSet()) {
5619  LoadFPRImmediate(kDoubleRegZero, 0.0);
5620  }
5621  fsub_d(dst, src, kDoubleRegZero);
5622 }

5624 void MacroAssembler::MovFromFloatResult(const DoubleRegister dst) {
5625  Move(dst, fa0); // Reg fa0 is FP return value.
5626 }
5627 
5628 void MacroAssembler::MovFromFloatParameter(const DoubleRegister dst) {
5629  Move(dst, fa0); // Reg fa0 is FP first argument value.
5630 }

5632 void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameter(DoubleRegister src) { Move(fa0, src); }
5633 
5634 void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatResult(DoubleRegister src) { Move(fa0, src); }
5635 
5636 void MacroAssembler::MovToFloatParameters(DoubleRegister src1,
5637  DoubleRegister src2) {
5638  const DoubleRegister fparg2 = fa1;
5639  if (src2 == fa0) {
5640  DCHECK(src1 != fparg2);
5641  Move(fparg2, src2);
5642  Move(fa0, src1);
5643  } else {
5644  Move(fa0, src1);
5645  Move(fparg2, src2);
5646  }
5647 }
