5652 void MacroAssembler::LoadStackLimit(Register destination, StackLimitKind kind) {
5653  DCHECK(root_array_available());
5654  intptr_t offset = kind == StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit
5655  ? IsolateData::real_jslimit_offset()
5656  : IsolateData::jslimit_offset();
5657  LoadWord(destination,
5658  MemOperand(kRootRegister, static_cast<int32_t>(offset)));
5659 }
5660 
5661 void MacroAssembler::StackOverflowCheck(Register num_args, Register scratch1,
5662  Register scratch2,
5663  Label* stack_overflow, Label* done) {
5664  // Check the stack for overflow. We are not trying to catch
5665  // interruptions (e.g. debug break and preemption) here, so the "real stack
5666  // limit" is checked.
5667  DCHECK(stack_overflow != nullptr || done != nullptr);
5668  LoadStackLimit(scratch1, StackLimitKind::kRealStackLimit);
5669  // Make scratch1 the space we have left. The stack might already be overflowed
5670  // here which will cause scratch1 to become negative.
5671  SubWord(scratch1, sp, scratch1);
5672  // Check if the arguments will overflow the stack.
5673  SllWord(scratch2, num_args, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5674  // Signed comparison.
5675  if (stack_overflow != nullptr) {
5676  Branch(stack_overflow, le, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
5677  } else if (done != nullptr) {
5678  Branch(done, gt, scratch1, Operand(scratch2));
5679  } else {
5680  UNREACHABLE();
5681  }
5682 }
5683 
5684 void MacroAssembler::InvokePrologue(Register expected_parameter_count,
5685  Register actual_parameter_count,
5686  InvokeType type) {
5687  Label regular_invoke;
5688 
5689  // a0: actual arguments count
5690  // a1: function (passed through to callee)
5691  // a2: expected arguments count
5692 
5693  DCHECK_EQ(actual_parameter_count, a0);
5694  DCHECK_EQ(expected_parameter_count, a2);
5695 
5696  // If overapplication or if the actual argument count is equal to the
5697  // formal parameter count, no need to push extra undefined values.
5698  SubWord(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count,
5699  actual_parameter_count);
5700  Branch(&regular_invoke, le, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
5701 
5702  Label stack_overflow;
5703  {
5704  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5705  temps.Include(t0, t1);
5706  StackOverflowCheck(expected_parameter_count, temps.Acquire(),
5707  temps.Acquire(), &stack_overflow);
5708  }
5709  // Underapplication. Move the arguments already in the stack, including the
5710  // receiver and the return address.
5711  {
5712  Label copy;
5713  Register src = a6, dest = a7;
5714  Move(src, sp);
5715  SllWord(t0, expected_parameter_count, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
5716  SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(t0));
5717  // Update stack pointer.
5718  Move(dest, sp);
5719  Move(t0, actual_parameter_count);
5720  bind(&copy);
5721  LoadWord(t1, MemOperand(src, 0));
5722  StoreWord(t1, MemOperand(dest, 0));
5723  SubWord(t0, t0, Operand(1));
5724  AddWord(src, src, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5725  AddWord(dest, dest, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5726  Branch(&copy, gt, t0, Operand(zero_reg));
5727  }
5728 
5729  // Fill remaining expected arguments with undefined values.
5730  LoadRoot(t0, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5731  {
5732  Label loop;
5733  bind(&loop);
5734  StoreWord(t0, MemOperand(a7, 0));
5735  SubWord(expected_parameter_count, expected_parameter_count, Operand(1));
5736  AddWord(a7, a7, Operand(kSystemPointerSize));
5737  Branch(&loop, gt, expected_parameter_count, Operand(zero_reg));
5738  }
5739  Branch(&regular_invoke);
5740 
5741  bind(&stack_overflow);
5742  {
5743  FrameScope frame(
5744  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5745  CallRuntime(Runtime::kThrowStackOverflow);
5746  break_(0xCC);
5747  }
5748  bind(&regular_invoke);
5749 }
5750 
5751 void MacroAssembler::CallDebugOnFunctionCall(
5752  Register fun, Register new_target,
5753  Register expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
5754  Register actual_parameter_count) {
5755  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5756  DCHECK(!AreAliased(t0, fun, new_target,
5757  expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle,
5758  actual_parameter_count));
5759 
5760  // Load receiver to pass it later to DebugOnFunctionCall hook.
5761  LoadReceiver(t0);
5762  FrameScope frame(
5763  this, has_frame() ? StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE : StackFrame::INTERNAL);
5764 
5765  SmiTag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
5766  SmiTag(actual_parameter_count);
5767  Push(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle, actual_parameter_count);
5768 
5769  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5770  Push(new_target);
5771  }
5772  Push(fun, fun, t0);
5773  CallRuntime(Runtime::kDebugOnFunctionCall);
5774  Pop(fun);
5775  if (new_target.is_valid()) {
5776  Pop(new_target);
5777  }
5778 
5779  Pop(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle, actual_parameter_count);
5780  SmiUntag(actual_parameter_count);
5781  SmiUntag(expected_parameter_count_or_dispatch_handle);
5782 }
5783 
5784 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING) && defined(V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64)
5785 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(
5786  Register function, Register actual_parameter_count, InvokeType type,
5787  ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
5788  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5789  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5790  DCHECK(type == InvokeType::kJump || has_frame());
5791 
5792  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5793  // (See FullCodeGenerator::Generate().)
5794  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5795 
5796  // Set up the context.
5797  LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5798 
5799  InvokeFunctionCode(function, no_reg, actual_parameter_count, type,
5800  argument_adaption_mode);
5801 }
5802 
5803 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionWithNewTarget(
5804  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
5805  InvokeType type) {
5806  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5807  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5808  DCHECK(type == InvokeType::kJump || has_frame());
5809 
5810  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5811  // (See FullCodeGenerator::Generate().)
5812  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5813 
5814  LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5815 
5816  InvokeFunctionCode(function, new_target, actual_parameter_count, type);
5817 }
5818 
5819 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(
5820  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
5821  InvokeType type, ArgumentAdaptionMode argument_adaption_mode) {
5822  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5823  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5824  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5825  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5826  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
5827 
5828  Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
5829  Lw(dispatch_handle,
5830  FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
5831 
5832  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
5833  Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
5834  Register scratch = s1;
5835  {
5836  li(scratch,
5837  ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
5838  Lb(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
5839  BranchShort(&debug_hook, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5840  }
5841  bind(&continue_after_hook);
5842 
5843  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
5844  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
5845  LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5846  }
5847 
5848  if (argument_adaption_mode == ArgumentAdaptionMode::kAdapt) {
5849  Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
5850  LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(expected_parameter_count,
5851  dispatch_handle, scratch);
5852  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
5853  }
5854 
5855  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
5856  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
5857  // call sites.
5858  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister,
5859  dispatch_handle, scratch);
5860  switch (type) {
5861  case InvokeType::kCall:
5862  Call(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
5863  break;
5864  case InvokeType::kJump:
5865  Jump(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister);
5866  break;
5867  }
5868  Label done;
5869  Branch(&done);
5870 
5871  // Deferred debug hook.
5872  bind(&debug_hook);
5873  CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, dispatch_handle,
5874  actual_parameter_count);
5875  Branch(&continue_after_hook);
5876 
5877  bind(&done);
5878 }
5879 #else // !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5880 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunction(Register function,
5881  Register expected_parameter_count,
5882  Register actual_parameter_count,
5883  InvokeType type) {
5884  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5885  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5886 
5887  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5888  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5889 
5890  // Get the function and setup the context.
5891  LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(a1, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5892 
5893  InvokeFunctionCode(a1, no_reg, expected_parameter_count,
5894  actual_parameter_count, type);
5895 }
5896 
5897 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionWithNewTarget(
5898  Register function, Register new_target, Register actual_parameter_count,
5899  InvokeType type) {
5900  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5901  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5902  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5903 
5904  // Contract with called JS functions requires that function is passed in a1.
5905  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5906  Register expected_parameter_count = a2;
5907  {
5908  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
5909  Register temp_reg = temps.Acquire();
5910  LoadTaggedField(
5911  temp_reg,
5912  FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kSharedFunctionInfoOffset));
5913  LoadTaggedField(cp, FieldMemOperand(function, JSFunction::kContextOffset));
5914  // The argument count is stored as uint16_t
5915  Lhu(expected_parameter_count,
5916  FieldMemOperand(temp_reg,
5917  SharedFunctionInfo::kFormalParameterCountOffset));
5918  }
5919  InvokeFunctionCode(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5920  actual_parameter_count, type);
5921 }
5922 
5923 void MacroAssembler::InvokeFunctionCode(Register function, Register new_target,
5924  Register expected_parameter_count,
5925  Register actual_parameter_count,
5926  InvokeType type) {
5927  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
5928  // You can't call a function without a valid frame.
5929  DCHECK_IMPLIES(type == InvokeType::kCall, has_frame());
5930  DCHECK_EQ(function, a1);
5931  DCHECK_IMPLIES(new_target.is_valid(), new_target == a3);
5932 
5933  // On function call, call into the debugger if necessary.
5934  Label debug_hook, continue_after_hook;
5935  Register scratch = s1;
5936  {
5937  li(scratch,
5938  ExternalReference::debug_hook_on_function_call_address(isolate()));
5939  Lb(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
5940  BranchShort(&debug_hook, ne, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
5941  }
5942  bind(&continue_after_hook);
5943 
5944  // Clear the new.target register if not given.
5945  if (!new_target.is_valid()) {
5946  LoadRoot(a3, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
5947  }
5948 
5949  InvokePrologue(expected_parameter_count, actual_parameter_count, type);
5950 
5951  // We call indirectly through the code field in the function to
5952  // allow recompilation to take effect without changing any of the
5953  // call sites.
5954  constexpr int unused_argument_count = 0;
5955  switch (type) {
5956  case InvokeType::kCall:
5957  CallJSFunction(function, unused_argument_count);
5958  break;
5959  case InvokeType::kJump:
5960  JumpJSFunction(function);
5961  break;
5962  }
5963 
5964  Label done;
5965  Branch(&done);
5966 
5967  // Deferred debug hook.
5968  bind(&debug_hook);
5969  CallDebugOnFunctionCall(function, new_target, expected_parameter_count,
5970  actual_parameter_count);
5971  Branch(&continue_after_hook);
5972 
5973  // Continue here if InvokePrologue does handle the invocation due to
5974  // mismatched parameter counts.
5975  bind(&done);
5976 }
5977 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING

5991  SubWord(range, type_reg, Operand(lower_limit));
5992 }

6049 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
6050 void MacroAssembler::WasmRvvS128const(VRegister dst, const uint8_t imms[16]) {
6051  uint64_t vals[2];
6052  memcpy(vals, imms, sizeof(vals));
6053  VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
6054  li(kScratchReg, vals[1]);
6055  vmv_sx(kSimd128ScratchReg, kScratchReg);
6056  vslideup_vi(dst, kSimd128ScratchReg, 1);
6057  li(kScratchReg, vals[0]);
6058  vmv_sx(dst, kScratchReg);
6059 }
6060 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
6061 void MacroAssembler::WasmRvvS128const(VRegister dst, const uint8_t imms[16]) {
6062  uint32_t vals[4];
6063  memcpy(vals, imms, sizeof(vals));
6064  VU.set(kScratchReg, VSew::E32, Vlmul::m1);
6065  li(kScratchReg, vals[3]);
6066  vmv_vx(kSimd128ScratchReg, kScratchReg);
6067  li(kScratchReg, vals[2]);
6068  vmv_sx(kSimd128ScratchReg, kScratchReg);
6069  li(kScratchReg, vals[1]);
6070  vmv_vx(dst, kScratchReg);
6071  li(kScratchReg, vals[0]);
6072  vmv_sx(dst, kScratchReg);
6073  vslideup_vi(dst, kSimd128ScratchReg, 2);
6074 }

6076 
6077 void MacroAssembler::LoadLane(int ts, VRegister dst, uint8_t laneidx,
6078  MemOperand src, Trapper&& trapper) {
6079  DCHECK_NE(kScratchReg, src.rm());
6080  if (ts == 8) {
6081  Lbu(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6082  VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
6083  li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
6084  vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
6085  VU.set(kScratchReg, E8, m1);
6086  vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
6087  } else if (ts == 16) {
6088  Lhu(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6089  VU.set(kScratchReg, E16, m1);
6090  li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
6091  vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
6092  vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
6093  } else if (ts == 32) {
6094  Load32U(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6095  VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
6096  li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
6097  vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
6098  vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
6099  } else if (ts == 64) {
6100 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
6101  LoadWord(kScratchReg2, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6102  VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
6103  li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
6104  vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
6105  vmerge_vx(dst, kScratchReg2, dst);
6106 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
6107  LoadDouble(kScratchDoubleReg, src, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6108  VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
6109  li(kScratchReg, 0x1 << laneidx);
6110  vmv_sx(v0, kScratchReg);
6111  vfmerge_vf(dst, kScratchDoubleReg, dst);
6112 #endif
6113  } else {
6114  UNREACHABLE();
6115  }
6116 }
6117 
6118 void MacroAssembler::StoreLane(int sz, VRegister src, uint8_t laneidx,
6119  MemOperand dst, Trapper&& trapper) {
6120  DCHECK_NE(kScratchReg, dst.rm());
6121  if (sz == 8) {
6122  VU.set(kScratchReg, E8, m1);
6123  vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
6124  vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
6125  trapper(pc_offset());
6126  Sb(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6127  } else if (sz == 16) {
6128  VU.set(kScratchReg, E16, m1);
6129  vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
6130  vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
6131  trapper(pc_offset());
6132  Sh(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6133  } else if (sz == 32) {
6134  VU.set(kScratchReg, E32, m1);
6135  vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
6136  vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
6137  trapper(pc_offset());
6138  Sw(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6139  } else {
6140  DCHECK_EQ(sz, 64);
6141  VU.set(kScratchReg, E64, m1);
6142  vslidedown_vi(kSimd128ScratchReg, src, laneidx);
6143 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
6144  vmv_xs(kScratchReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
6145  trapper(pc_offset());
6146  StoreWord(kScratchReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6147 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
6148  vfmv_fs(kScratchDoubleReg, kSimd128ScratchReg);
6149  trapper(pc_offset());
6150  StoreDouble(kScratchDoubleReg, dst, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
6151 #endif
6152  }
6153 }
6154 // -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
6155 // Runtime calls.
6156 void MacroAssembler::AddOverflowWord(Register dst, Register left,
6157  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6158  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6159  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6160  Register right_reg = no_reg;
6161  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6162  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6163  if (!right.is_reg()) {
6164  li(scratch, Operand(right));
6165  right_reg = scratch;
6166  } else {
6167  right_reg = right.rm();
6168  }
6169  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6170  overflow != scratch2);
6171  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6172  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6173  AddWord(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6174  Xor(overflow, scratch2, left);
6175  Xor(scratch, scratch2, right_reg);
6176  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6177  Mv(dst, scratch2);
6178  } else {
6179  AddWord(dst, left, right_reg);
6180  Xor(overflow, dst, left);
6181  Xor(scratch, dst, right_reg);
6182  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6183  }
6184 }
6185 
6186 void MacroAssembler::SubOverflowWord(Register dst, Register left,
6187  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6188  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6189  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6190  Register right_reg = no_reg;
6191  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6192  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6193  if (!right.is_reg()) {
6194  li(scratch, Operand(right));
6195  right_reg = scratch;
6196  } else {
6197  right_reg = right.rm();
6198  }
6199 
6200  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6201  overflow != scratch2);
6202  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6203 
6204  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6205  SubWord(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6206  Xor(overflow, left, scratch2);
6207  Xor(scratch, left, right_reg);
6208  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6209  Mv(dst, scratch2);
6210  } else {
6211  SubWord(dst, left, right_reg);
6212  Xor(overflow, left, dst);
6213  Xor(scratch, left, right_reg);
6214  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6215  }
6216 }
6217 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
6218 void MacroAssembler::AddOverflow32(Register dst, Register left,
6219  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6220  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6221  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6222  Register right_reg = no_reg;
6223  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6224  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6225  if (!right.is_reg()) {
6226  li(scratch, Operand(right));
6227  right_reg = scratch;
6228  } else {
6229  right_reg = right.rm();
6230  }
6231  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6232  overflow != scratch2);
6233  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6234  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6235  Add32(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6236  Xor(overflow, scratch2, left);
6237  Xor(scratch, scratch2, right_reg);
6238  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6239  sext_w(overflow, overflow);
6240  Mv(dst, scratch2);
6241  } else {
6242  Add32(dst, left, right_reg);
6243  Xor(overflow, dst, left);
6244  Xor(scratch, dst, right_reg);
6245  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6246  sext_w(overflow, overflow);
6247  }
6248 }

6250 void MacroAssembler::SubOverflow32(Register dst, Register left,
6251  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6252  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6253  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6254  Register right_reg = no_reg;
6255  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6256  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6257  if (!right.is_reg()) {
6258  li(scratch, Operand(right));
6259  right_reg = scratch;
6260  } else {
6261  right_reg = right.rm();
6262  }
6263 
6264  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6265  overflow != scratch2);
6266  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6267 
6268  if (dst == left || dst == right_reg) {
6269  Sub32(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6270  Xor(overflow, left, scratch2);

6272  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6273  sext_w(overflow, overflow);
6274  Mv(dst, scratch2);
6275  } else {
6276  Sub32(dst, left, right_reg);
6277  Xor(overflow, left, dst);

6279  And(overflow, overflow, scratch);
6280  sext_w(overflow, overflow);
6281  }

6283 
6284 void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow32(Register dst, Register left,
6285  const Operand& right, Register overflow,
6286  bool sign_extend_inputs) {
6287  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6288  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6289  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6290  Register right_reg = no_reg;
6291  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6292  if (!right.is_reg()) {
6293  if (!right.IsHeapNumberRequest()) {
6294  // emulate sext.w behavior for imm input
6295  int64_t imm;
6296  imm = static_cast<int32_t>(right.immediate() & 0xFFFFFFFFU);
6297  li(scratch, Operand(imm));
6298  } else {
6299  li(scratch, Operand(right));
6300  }
6301  right_reg = scratch;
6302  } else {
6303  right_reg = right.rm();
6304  }
6305  Register rs1 = no_reg;
6306  Register rs2 = no_reg;
6307  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6308  if (sign_extend_inputs) {
6309  sext_w(overflow, left);
6310  if (right.is_reg()) {
6311  sext_w(scratch, right_reg);
6312  }
6313  rs1 = overflow;
6314  rs2 = scratch;
6315  } else {
6316  // we can skip sext_w on register inputs if not requested
6317  rs1 = left;
6318  rs2 = right_reg;
6319  // no need in assert if input was imm
6320  if (right.is_reg()) {
6321  AssertSignExtended(rs2);
6322  }
6323  AssertSignExtended(rs1);
6324  }
6325  mul(overflow, rs1, rs2);
6326  sext_w(dst, overflow);
6327  Xor(overflow, overflow, dst);
6328 }
6329 
6330 void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow64(Register dst, Register left,
6331  const Operand& right, Register overflow) {
6332  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6333  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6334  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6335  Register right_reg = no_reg;
6336  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6337  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6338  if (!right.is_reg()) {
6339  li(scratch, Operand(right));
6340  right_reg = scratch;
6341  } else {
6342  right_reg = right.rm();
6343  }
6344 
6345  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6346  overflow != scratch2);
6347  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6348  // Use this sequence of "mulh/mul" according to recommendation of ISA
6349  // Spec 7.1.
6350  // Upper part.
6351  mulh(scratch2, left, right_reg);
6352  // Lower part.
6353  mul(dst, left, right_reg);
6354  // Expand the sign of the lower part to 64bit.
6355  SraWord(overflow, dst, 63);
6356  // If the upper part is not equal to the expanded sign bit of the lower part,
6357  // overflow happens.
6358  Xor(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
6359 }
6360 
6361 #elif V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
6362 void MacroAssembler::MulOverflow32(Register dst, Register left,
6363  const Operand& right, Register overflow,
6364  bool sign_extend_inputs) {
6365  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6366  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6367  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6368  Register right_reg = no_reg;
6369  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6370  Register scratch2 = temps.Acquire();
6371  if (!right.is_reg()) {
6372  li(scratch, Operand(right));
6373  right_reg = scratch;
6374  } else {
6375  right_reg = right.rm();
6376  }
6377 
6378  DCHECK(left != scratch2 && right_reg != scratch2 && dst != scratch2 &&
6379  overflow != scratch2);
6380  DCHECK(overflow != left && overflow != right_reg);
6381  mulh(overflow, left, right_reg);
6382  mul(dst, left, right_reg);
6383  SraWord(scratch2, dst, 31);
6384  Xor(overflow, overflow, scratch2);
6385 }
6386 #endif

6388 void MacroAssembler::CallRuntime(const Runtime::Function* f,
6389  int num_arguments) {
6390  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6391  // All parameters are on the stack. a0 has the return value after call.
6392 
6393  // If the expected number of arguments of the runtime function is
6394  // constant, we check that the actual number of arguments match the
6395  // expectation.
6396  CHECK(f->nargs < 0 || f->nargs == num_arguments);
6397 
6398  // TODO(1236192): Most runtime routines don't need the number of
6399  // arguments passed in because it is constant. At some point we
6400  // should remove this need and make the runtime routine entry code
6401  // smarter.
6402  PrepareCEntryArgs(num_arguments);
6403  PrepareCEntryFunction(ExternalReference::Create(f));
6404  bool switch_to_central = options().is_wasm;
6405  CallBuiltin(Builtins::RuntimeCEntry(f->result_size, switch_to_central));
6406 }
6407 
6408 void MacroAssembler::TailCallRuntime(Runtime::FunctionId fid) {
6409  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6410  const Runtime::Function* function = Runtime::FunctionForId(fid);
6411  DCHECK_EQ(1, function->result_size);
6412  if (function->nargs >= 0) {
6413  PrepareCEntryArgs(function->nargs);
6414  }
6415  JumpToExternalReference(ExternalReference::Create(fid));
6416 }
6417 
6418 void MacroAssembler::JumpToExternalReference(const ExternalReference& builtin,
6419  bool builtin_exit_frame) {
6420  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6421  PrepareCEntryFunction(builtin);
6422  TailCallBuiltin(Builtins::CEntry(1, ArgvMode::kStack, builtin_exit_frame));
6423 }

6425 void MacroAssembler::LoadWeakValue(Register out, Register in,
6426  Label* target_if_cleared) {
6427  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6428  CompareTaggedAndBranch(target_if_cleared, eq, in,
6429  Operand(kClearedWeakHeapObjectLower32));
6430  And(out, in, Operand(~kWeakHeapObjectMask));
6431 }

6433 void MacroAssembler::EmitIncrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
6434  Register scratch1,
6435  Register scratch2) {
6436  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
6437  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
6438  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6439  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
6440  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t
6441  // dummy_stats_counter_ field.
6442  li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
6443  Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6444  Add32(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
6445  Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6446  }
6447 }
6448 
6449 void MacroAssembler::EmitDecrementCounter(StatsCounter* counter, int value,
6450  Register scratch1,
6451  Register scratch2) {
6452  DCHECK_GT(value, 0);
6453  if (v8_flags.native_code_counters && counter->Enabled()) {
6454  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6455  // This operation has to be exactly 32-bit wide in case the external
6456  // reference table redirects the counter to a uint32_t
6457  // dummy_stats_counter_ field.
6458  li(scratch2, ExternalReference::Create(counter));
6459  Lw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6460  Sub32(scratch1, scratch1, Operand(value));
6461  Sw(scratch1, MemOperand(scratch2));
6462  }
6463 }

6476 void MacroAssembler::AssertJSAny(Register object, Register map_tmp,
6477  Register tmp, AbortReason abort_reason) {
6478  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
6479 
6480  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6481  DCHECK(!AreAliased(object, map_tmp, tmp));
6482  Label ok;
6483 
6484  JumpIfSmi(object, &ok);
6485 
6486  GetObjectType(object, map_tmp, tmp);
6487 
6488  Branch(&ok, kUnsignedLessThanEqual, tmp, Operand(LAST_NAME_TYPE));
6489 
6490  Branch(&ok, kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual, tmp, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6491 
6492  Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kHeapNumberMap);
6493 
6494  Branch(&ok, kEqual, map_tmp, RootIndex::kBigIntMap);
6495 
6496  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
6497 
6498  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kTrueValue);
6499 
6500  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kFalseValue);
6501 
6502  Branch(&ok, kEqual, object, RootIndex::kNullValue);
6503 
6504  Abort(abort_reason);
6505  bind(&ok);
6506 }

6551 
6552 void MacroAssembler::Abort(AbortReason reason) {
6553  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6554  if (v8_flags.code_comments) {
6555  RecordComment("Abort message:", SourceLocation{});
6556  RecordComment(GetAbortReason(reason), SourceLocation{});
6557  }
6558 
6559  // Without debug code, save the code size and just trap.
6560  if (!v8_flags.debug_code || v8_flags.trap_on_abort) {
6561  ebreak();
6562  return;
6563  }
6564 
6565  if (should_abort_hard()) {
6566  // We don't care if we constructed a frame. Just pretend we did.
6567  FrameScope assume_frame(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
6568  PrepareCallCFunction(1, a0);
6569  li(a0, Operand(static_cast<int>(reason)));
6570  li(a1, ExternalReference::abort_with_reason());
6571  // Use Call directly to avoid any unneeded overhead. The function won't
6572  // return anyway.
6573  Call(a1);
6574  return;
6575  }
6576 
6577  Label abort_start;
6578  bind(&abort_start);
6579 
6580  Move(a0, Smi::FromInt(static_cast<int>(reason)));
6581 
6582  {
6583  // We don't actually want to generate a pile of code for this, so just
6584  // claim there is a stack frame, without generating one.
6585  FrameScope scope(this, StackFrame::NO_FRAME_TYPE);
6586  if (root_array_available()) {
6587  // Generate an indirect call via builtins entry table here in order to
6588  // ensure that the interpreter_entry_return_pc_offset is the same for
6589  // InterpreterEntryTrampoline and InterpreterEntryTrampolineForProfiling
6590  // when v8_flags.debug_code is enabled.
6591  LoadEntryFromBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort, t6);
6592  Call(t6);
6593  } else {
6594  CallBuiltin(Builtin::kAbort);
6595  }
6596  }
6597  // Will not return here.
6598  if (is_trampoline_pool_blocked()) {
6599  // If the calling code cares about the exact number of
6600  // instructions generated, we insert padding here to keep the size
6601  // of the Abort macro constant.
6602  // Currently in debug mode with debug_code enabled the number of
6603  // generated instructions is 10, so we use this as a maximum value.
6604  static const int kExpectedAbortInstructions = 10;
6605  int abort_instructions = InstructionsGeneratedSince(&abort_start);
6606  DCHECK_LE(abort_instructions, kExpectedAbortInstructions);
6607  while (abort_instructions++ < kExpectedAbortInstructions) {
6608  NOP();
6609  }
6610  }
6611 }
6612 
6613 // Sets condition flags based on comparison, and returns type in type_reg.
6614 void MacroAssembler::CompareObjectTypeAndJump(Register object, Register map,
6615  Register type_reg,
6616  InstanceType type, Condition cond,
6617  Label* target,
6618  Label::Distance distance) {
6619  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6620  LoadMap(map, object);
6621  // Borrowed from BaselineAssembler
6622  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6623  AssertNotSmi(map);
6624  Register temp_type_reg = type_reg;
6625  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6626  if (map == temp_type_reg) {
6627  // GetObjectType clobbers 2nd and 3rd args, can't be same registers as
6628  // first one
6629  temp_type_reg = temps.Acquire();
6630  }
6631  GetObjectType(map, temp_type_reg, temp_type_reg);
6632  Assert(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedValue, temp_type_reg, Operand(MAP_TYPE));
6633  }
6634  Lhu(type_reg, FieldMemOperand(map, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
6635  Branch(target, cond, type_reg, Operand(type), distance);
6636 }

6640  LoadTaggedField(destination, FieldMemOperand(object, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
6641 }

6648 void MacroAssembler::LoadNativeContextSlot(Register dst, int index) {
6649  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6650  LoadMap(dst, cp);

6656 
6657 void MacroAssembler::TryLoadOptimizedOsrCode(Register scratch_and_result,
6658  CodeKind min_opt_level,
6659  Register feedback_vector,
6660  FeedbackSlot slot,
6661  Label* on_result,
6662  Label::Distance distance) {
6663  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6664  Label fallthrough, clear_slot;
6665  LoadTaggedField(
6666  scratch_and_result,
6667  FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6668  FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6669  LoadWeakValue(scratch_and_result, scratch_and_result, &fallthrough);
6670 
6671  // Is it marked_for_deoptimization? If yes, clear the slot.
6672  {
6673  // The entry references a CodeWrapper object. Unwrap it now.
6674  LoadCodePointerField(
6675  scratch_and_result,
6676  FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, CodeWrapper::kCodeOffset));
6677 
6678  // marked for deoptimization?
6679  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6680  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6681  Load32U(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6682  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
6683 
6684  if (min_opt_level == CodeKind::TURBOFAN_JS) {
6685  Branch(&clear_slot, not_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg),
6686  Label::Distance::kNear);
6687 
6688  // is code "turbofanned"?
6689  Load32U(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch_and_result, Code::kFlagsOffset));
6690  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kIsTurbofannedBit));
6691  Branch(on_result, not_equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg), distance);
6692 
6693  Branch(&fallthrough);
6694  } else {
6695  DCHECK_EQ(min_opt_level, CodeKind::MAGLEV);
6696  Branch(on_result, equal, scratch, Operand(zero_reg), distance);
6697  }
6698 
6699  bind(&clear_slot);
6700  li(scratch_and_result, ClearedValue());
6701  StoreTaggedField(
6702  scratch_and_result,
6703  FieldMemOperand(feedback_vector,
6704  FeedbackVector::OffsetOfElementAt(slot.ToInt())));
6705  }
6706 
6707  bind(&fallthrough);
6708  Move(scratch_and_result, zero_reg);
6709 }
6710 
6711 void MacroAssembler::StubPrologue(StackFrame::Type type) {
6712  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6713  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6714  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6715  li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
6716  PushCommonFrame(scratch);
6717 }
6718 
6719 void MacroAssembler::Prologue() { PushStandardFrame(a1); }

6721 void MacroAssembler::EnterFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
6722  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6723  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6724  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6725  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6726  Push(ra, fp);
6727  Move(fp, sp);
6728  if (!StackFrame::IsJavaScript(type)) {
6729  li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(type)));
6730  Push(scratch);
6731  }
6732 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6733  if (type == StackFrame::WASM || type == StackFrame::WASM_LIFTOFF_SETUP) {
6734  Push(kWasmImplicitArgRegister);
6735  }
6736 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
6737 }
6738 
6739 void MacroAssembler::LeaveFrame(StackFrame::Type type) {
6740  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6741  AddWord(sp, fp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
6742  LoadWord(ra, MemOperand(fp, 1 * kSystemPointerSize));
6743  LoadWord(fp, MemOperand(fp, 0 * kSystemPointerSize));
6744 }
6745 
6746 void MacroAssembler::EnterExitFrame(Register scratch, int stack_space,
6747  StackFrame::Type frame_type) {
6748  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6749  DCHECK(frame_type == StackFrame::EXIT ||
6750  frame_type == StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT ||
6751  frame_type == StackFrame::API_ACCESSOR_EXIT ||
6752  frame_type == StackFrame::API_CALLBACK_EXIT);
6753 
6754  // Set up the frame structure on the stack.
6755  static_assert(2 * kSystemPointerSize ==
6756  ExitFrameConstants::kCallerSPDisplacement);
6757  static_assert(1 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset);
6758  static_assert(0 * kSystemPointerSize == ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset);
6759 
6760  // This is how the stack will look:
6761  // fp + 2 (==kCallerSPDisplacement) - old stack's end
6762  // [fp + 1 (==kCallerPCOffset)] - saved old ra
6763  // [fp + 0 (==kCallerFPOffset)] - saved old fp
6764  // [fp - 1 StackFrame::EXIT Smi
6765  // [fp - 2 (==kSPOffset)] - sp of the called function
6766  // fp - (2 + stack_space + alignment) == sp == [fp - kSPOffset] - top of the
6767  // new stack (will contain saved ra)
6768 
6769  using ER = ExternalReference;
6770 
6771  // Save registers and reserve room for saved entry sp.
6772  AddWord(sp, sp,
6773  -2 * kSystemPointerSize - ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
6774  StoreWord(ra, MemOperand(sp, 3 * kSystemPointerSize));
6775  StoreWord(fp, MemOperand(sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize));
6776 
6777  li(scratch, Operand(StackFrame::TypeToMarker(frame_type)));
6778  StoreWord(scratch, MemOperand(sp, 1 * kSystemPointerSize));
6779  // Set up new frame pointer.
6780  AddWord(fp, sp, ExitFrameConstants::kFixedFrameSizeFromFp);
6781 
6782  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6783  StoreWord(zero_reg, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
6784  }
6785 
6786  // Save the frame pointer and the context in top.
6787  ER c_entry_fp_address =
6788  ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
6789  StoreWord(fp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
6790  ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
6791  StoreWord(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
6792 
6793  const int frame_alignment = MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6794 
6795  // Reserve place for the return address, stack space and an optional slot
6796  // (used by DirectCEntry to hold the return value if a struct is
6797  // returned) and align the frame preparing for calling the runtime function.
6798  DCHECK_GE(stack_space, 0);
6799  SubWord(sp, sp, Operand((stack_space + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
6800  if (frame_alignment > 0) {
6801  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6802  And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment)); // Align stack.
6803  }
6804 
6805  // Set the exit frame sp value to point just before the return address
6806  // location.
6807  AddWord(scratch, sp, kSystemPointerSize);
6808  StoreWord(scratch, MemOperand(fp, ExitFrameConstants::kSPOffset));
6809 }
6810 
6811 void MacroAssembler::LeaveExitFrame(Register scratch) {
6812  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6813  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
6814  using ER = ExternalReference;
6815  // Clear top frame.
6816  // Restore current context from top and clear it in debug mode.
6817  ER context_address = ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kContextAddress, isolate());
6818  LoadWord(cp, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
6819 
6820  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6821  li(scratch, Operand(Context::kNoContext));
6822  StoreWord(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(context_address, no_reg));
6823  }
6824 
6825  // Clear the top frame.
6826  ER c_entry_fp_address =
6827  ER::Create(IsolateAddressId::kCEntryFPAddress, isolate());
6828  StoreWord(zero_reg, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(c_entry_fp_address, no_reg));
6829 
6830  // Pop the arguments, restore registers, and return.
6831  Mv(sp, fp); // Respect ABI stack constraint.
6832  LoadWord(fp, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerFPOffset));
6833  LoadWord(ra, MemOperand(sp, ExitFrameConstants::kCallerPCOffset));
6834 
6835  AddWord(sp, sp, 2 * kSystemPointerSize);
6836 }
6837 
6838 int MacroAssembler::ActivationFrameAlignment() {
6839 #if V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6840  // Running on the real platform. Use the alignment as mandated by the local
6841  // environment.
6842  // Note: This will break if we ever start generating snapshots on one RISC-V
6843  // platform for another RISC-V platform with a different alignment.
6844  return base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
6845 #else // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6846  // If we are using the simulator then we should always align to the expected
6847  // alignment. As the simulator is used to generate snapshots we do not know
6848  // if the target platform will need alignment, so this is controlled from a
6849  // flag.
6850  return v8_flags.sim_stack_alignment;
6851 #endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
6852 }
6853 
6854 void MacroAssembler::AssertStackIsAligned() {
6855  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
6856  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6857  const int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
6858  const int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
6859 
6860  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
6861  Label alignment_as_expected;
6862  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
6863  {
6864  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6865  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
6866  And(scratch, sp, frame_alignment_mask);
6867  BranchShort(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
6868  }
6869  // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort re-entering here.
6870  ebreak();
6871  bind(&alignment_as_expected);
6872  }
6873  }
6874 }

6876 void MacroAssembler::SmiUntag(Register dst, const MemOperand& src) {
6877  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
6878  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
6879  Lw(dst, MemOperand(src.rm(), SmiWordOffset(src.offset())));
6880  } else {
6881  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
6882  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
6883  Lw(dst, src);
6884  } else {
6885  LoadWord(dst, src);
6886  }
6887  SmiUntag(dst);
6888  }
6889 }

6897  SmiUntag(smi);

6938 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfObjectType(Label* target, Condition cc,
6939  Register object,
6940  InstanceType instance_type,
6941  Register scratch) {
6942  DCHECK(cc == eq || cc == ne);
6943  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
6944  if (scratch == no_reg) {
6945  scratch = temps.Acquire();
6946  }
6947  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
6948  if (std::optional<RootIndex> expected =
6949  InstanceTypeChecker::UniqueMapOfInstanceType(instance_type)) {
6950  Tagged_t ptr = ReadOnlyRootPtr(*expected);
6951  LoadCompressedMap(scratch, object);
6952  Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(ptr));
6953  return;
6954  }
6955  }
6956  GetObjectType(object, scratch, scratch);
6957  Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(instance_type));
6958 }

6960 void MacroAssembler::JumpIfJSAnyIsNotPrimitive(Register heap_object,
6961  Register scratch, Label* target,
6962  Label::Distance distance,
6963  Condition cc) {
6964  CHECK(cc == Condition::kUnsignedLessThan ||
6965  cc == Condition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual);
6966  if (V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL) {
6967 #ifdef DEBUG
6968  Label ok;
6969  LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
6970  GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE, scratch);
6971  Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
6972  Operand(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE - FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6973 
6974  LoadMap(scratch, heap_object);
6975  GetInstanceTypeRange(scratch, scratch, FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE,
6976  scratch);
6977  Branch(&ok, Condition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual, scratch,
6978  Operand(LAST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE -
6979  FIRST_PRIMITIVE_HEAP_OBJECT_TYPE));
6980 
6981  Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidReceiver);
6982  bind(&ok);
6983 #endif // DEBUG
6984 
6985  // All primitive object's maps are allocated at the start of the read only
6986  // heap. Thus JS_RECEIVER's must have maps with larger (compressed)
6987  // addresses.
6988  LoadCompressedMap(scratch, heap_object);
6989  Branch(target, cc, scratch,
6990  Operand(InstanceTypeChecker::kNonJsReceiverMapLimit));
6991  } else {
6992  static_assert(LAST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE == LAST_TYPE);
6993  GetObjectType(heap_object, scratch, scratch);
6994  Branch(target, cc, scratch, Operand(FIRST_JS_RECEIVER_TYPE));
6995  }
6996 }

7002  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7003  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
7004  And(scratch, object, kSmiTagMask);
7005  Check(ne, reason, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
7006  }
7007 }

7020 void MacroAssembler::AssertConstructor(Register object) {
7021  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7022  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7023  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7024  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7025  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
7026  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
7027  SmiTst(object, scratch);
7028  Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAConstructor, scratch,
7029  Operand(zero_reg));
7030 
7031  LoadMap(scratch, object);
7032  Lbu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kBitFieldOffset));
7033  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(Map::Bits1::IsConstructorBit::kMask));
7034  Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAConstructor, scratch,
7035  Operand(zero_reg));
7036  }

7039 void MacroAssembler::AssertFunction(Register object) {
7040  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7041  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7042  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
7043  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7044  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7045  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
7046  SmiTst(object, scratch);
7047  Check(ne, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction, scratch,
7048  Operand(zero_reg));
7049  push(object);
7050  LoadMap(object, object);
7051  Register range = scratch;
7052  GetInstanceTypeRange(object, object, FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, range);
7053  Check(Uless_equal, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAFunction, range,
7054  Operand(LAST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE - FIRST_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE));
7055  pop(object);
7056  }
7057 }

7059 void MacroAssembler::AssertCallableFunction(Register object) {
7060  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
7061  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7062  static_assert(kSmiTag == 0);
7063  AssertNotSmi(object, AbortReason::kOperandIsASmiAndNotAFunction);
7064  push(object);
7065  LoadMap(object, object);
7066  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7067  Register range = temps.Acquire();
7068  GetInstanceTypeRange(object, object, FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE, range);
7069  Check(Uless_equal, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotACallableFunction, range,
7070  Operand(LAST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE -
7071  FIRST_CALLABLE_JS_FUNCTION_TYPE));
7072  pop(object);
7073 }

7091 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE
7092 void MacroAssembler::AssertSmiOrHeapObjectInMainCompressionCage(
7093  Register object) {
7094 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
7095  if (!PointerCompressionIsEnabled()) return;
7096  if (!v8_flags.debug_code) return;
7097  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7098  // We may not have any scratch registers so we preserve our input register.
7099  Push(object, zero_reg);
7100  Label ok;
7101  {
7102  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7103  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7104  SmiTst(object, scratch);
7105  BranchShort(&ok, kEqual, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
7106  }
7107  // Clear the lower 32 bits.
7108  Srl64(object, object, Operand(32));
7109  Sll64(object, object, Operand(32));
7110  // Either the value is now equal to the right-shifted pointer compression
7111  // cage base or it's zero if we got a compressed pointer register as input.
7112  BranchShort(&ok, kEqual, object, Operand(zero_reg));
7113  Check(kEqual, AbortReason::kObjectNotTagged, object,
7114  Operand(kPtrComprCageBaseRegister));
7115  bind(&ok);
7116  Pop(object, zero_reg);
7117 #endif
7118 }
7119 #endif // V8_ENABLE_DEBUG_CODE

7121 void MacroAssembler::AssertGeneratorObject(Register object) {

7125  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);

7134  scratch);
7135  Check(
7136  Uless_equal, AbortReason::kOperandIsNotAGeneratorObject, scratch,
7137  Operand(LAST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE - FIRST_JS_GENERATOR_OBJECT_TYPE));
7138 }

7140 void MacroAssembler::AssertUndefinedOrAllocationSite(Register object,
7141  Register scratch) {
7142  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {

7147  BranchShort(&done_checking, eq, object, Operand(scratch));

7154 
7155 template <typename F_TYPE>
7156 void MacroAssembler::FloatMinMaxHelper(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7157  FPURegister src2, MaxMinKind kind) {
7158  DCHECK((std::is_same_v<F_TYPE, float>) || (std::is_same_v<F_TYPE, double>));
7159 
7160  if (src1 == src2 && dst != src1) {
7161  if (std::is_same_v<float, F_TYPE>) {
7162  fmv_s(dst, src1);
7163  } else {
7164  fmv_d(dst, src1);
7165  }
7166  return;
7167  }
7168 
7169  Label done, nan;
7170 
7171  // For RISCV, fmin_s returns the other non-NaN operand as result if only one
7172  // operand is NaN; but for JS, if any operand is NaN, result is Nan. The
7173  // following handles the discrepancy in the handling of NaN between ISA and
7174  // JS semantics.
7175  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7176  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7177  if (std::is_same_v<float, F_TYPE>) {
7178  CompareIsNotNanF32(scratch, src1, src2);
7179  } else {
7180  CompareIsNotNanF64(scratch, src1, src2);
7181  }
7182  BranchFalseF(scratch, &nan);
7183 
7184  if (kind == MaxMinKind::kMax) {
7185  if (std::is_same_v<float, F_TYPE>) {
7186  fmax_s(dst, src1, src2);
7187  } else {
7188  fmax_d(dst, src1, src2);
7189  }
7190  } else {
7191  if (std::is_same_v<float, F_TYPE>) {
7192  fmin_s(dst, src1, src2);
7193  } else {
7194  fmin_d(dst, src1, src2);
7195  }
7196  }
7197  j(&done);
7198 
7199  bind(&nan);
7200  // if any operand is NaN, return NaN (fadd returns NaN if any operand is NaN)
7201  if (std::is_same_v<float, F_TYPE>) {
7202  fadd_s(dst, src1, src2);
7203  } else {
7204  fadd_d(dst, src1, src2);
7205  }
7206 
7207  bind(&done);
7208 }
7209 
7210 void MacroAssembler::Float32Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7211  FPURegister src2) {
7212  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7213  FloatMinMaxHelper<float>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMax);
7214 }
7215 
7216 void MacroAssembler::Float32Min(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7217  FPURegister src2) {
7218  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7219  FloatMinMaxHelper<float>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMin);
7220 }
7221 
7222 void MacroAssembler::Float64Max(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7223  FPURegister src2) {
7224  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7225  FloatMinMaxHelper<double>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMax);
7226 }
7227 
7228 void MacroAssembler::Float64Min(FPURegister dst, FPURegister src1,
7229  FPURegister src2) {
7230  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7231  FloatMinMaxHelper<double>(dst, src1, src2, MaxMinKind::kMin);
7232 }
7233 
7234 int MacroAssembler::CalculateStackPassedDWords(int num_gp_arguments,
7235  int num_fp_arguments) {
7236  int stack_passed_dwords = 0;
7237 
7238  // Up to eight integer arguments are passed in registers a0..a7 and
7239  // up to eight floating point arguments are passed in registers fa0..fa7
7240  if (num_gp_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
7241  stack_passed_dwords += num_gp_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
7242  }
7243  if (num_fp_arguments > kRegisterPassedArguments) {
7244  stack_passed_dwords += num_fp_arguments - kRegisterPassedArguments;
7245  }
7246  stack_passed_dwords += kCArgSlotCount;
7247  return stack_passed_dwords;
7248 }
7249 
7250 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
7251  int num_double_arguments,
7252  Register scratch) {
7253  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7254  int frame_alignment = ActivationFrameAlignment();
7255 
7256  // Up to eight simple arguments in a0..a7, fa0..fa7.
7257  // Remaining arguments are pushed on the stack (arg slot calculation handled
7258  // by CalculateStackPassedDWords()).
7259  int stack_passed_arguments =
7260  CalculateStackPassedDWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
7261  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
7262  // Make stack end at alignment and make room for stack arguments and the
7263  // original value of sp.
7264  Mv(scratch, sp);
7265  SubWord(sp, sp, Operand((stack_passed_arguments + 1) * kSystemPointerSize));
7266  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
7267  And(sp, sp, Operand(-frame_alignment));
7268  StoreWord(scratch,
7269  MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7270  } else {
7271  SubWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7272  }
7273 }
7274 
7275 void MacroAssembler::PrepareCallCFunction(int num_reg_arguments,
7276  Register scratch) {
7277  PrepareCallCFunction(num_reg_arguments, 0, scratch);
7278 }

7283  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,
7284  Label* return_location) {
7285  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
7286  li(t6, function);
7287  return CallCFunctionHelper(t6, num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments,
7288  set_isolate_data_slots, return_location);
7289 }

7306 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunction(Register function, int num_arguments,
7307  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots,

7312 
7313 int MacroAssembler::CallCFunctionHelper(
7314  Register function, int num_reg_arguments, int num_double_arguments,
7315  SetIsolateDataSlots set_isolate_data_slots, Label* return_location) {
7316  DCHECK_LE(num_reg_arguments + num_double_arguments, kMaxCParameters);
7317  DCHECK(has_frame());
7318  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7319  // Make sure that the stack is aligned before calling a C function unless
7320  // running in the simulator. The simulator has its own alignment check which
7321  // provides more information.
7322  // The argument stots are presumed to have been set up by
7323  // PrepareCallCFunction.
7324 
7325 #if V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
7326  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7327  int frame_alignment = base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment();
7328  int frame_alignment_mask = frame_alignment - 1;
7329  if (frame_alignment > kSystemPointerSize) {
7330  DCHECK(base::bits::IsPowerOfTwo(frame_alignment));
7331  Label alignment_as_expected;
7332  {
7333  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7334  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7335  And(scratch, sp, Operand(frame_alignment_mask));
7336  BranchShort(&alignment_as_expected, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
7337  }
7338  // Don't use Check here, as it will call Runtime_Abort possibly
7339  // re-entering here.
7340  ebreak();
7341  bind(&alignment_as_expected);
7342  }
7343  }
7344 #endif // V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV32 || V8_HOST_ARCH_RISCV64
7345 
7346  // Just call directly. The function called cannot cause a GC, or
7347  // allow preemption, so the return address in the link register
7348  // stays correct.
7349  Label get_pc;
7350  {
7351  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
7352  if (function != t6) {
7353  Mv(t6, function);
7354  function = t6;
7355  }
7356 
7357  // Save the frame pointer and PC so that the stack layout remains
7358  // iterable, even without an ExitFrame which normally exists between JS
7359  // and C frames.
7360  // 't' registers are caller-saved so this is safe as a scratch register.
7361  Register pc_scratch = t1;
7362 
7363  LoadAddress(pc_scratch, &get_pc);
7364  // See x64 code for reasoning about how to address the isolate data
7365  // fields.
7366  CHECK(root_array_available());
7367  StoreWord(pc_scratch,
7368  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerPC));
7369  StoreWord(fp,
7370  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
7371  }
7372  }
7373 
7374  int call_pc_offset;
7375  {
7376  BlockPoolsScope block_const_pool_scope(this);
7377  Call(function);
7378  call_pc_offset = pc_offset();
7379  bind(&get_pc);
7380  if (return_location) bind(return_location);
7381  int before_offset = pc_offset();
7382  // Remove frame bought in PrepareCallCFunction
7383  int stack_passed_arguments =
7384  CalculateStackPassedDWords(num_reg_arguments, num_double_arguments);
7385  if (base::OS::ActivationFrameAlignment() > kSystemPointerSize) {
7386  LoadWord(sp, MemOperand(sp, stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7387  } else {
7388  AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(stack_passed_arguments * kSystemPointerSize));
7389  }
7390  if (kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall > pc_offset() - before_offset) {
7391  nop();
7392  }
7393  // We assume that with the nop padding, the move instruction uses
7394  // kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall bytes. When we patch in the deopt trampoline,
7395  // we patch it in after the move instruction, so that the stack has been
7396  // restored correctly.
7397  CHECK_EQ(kMaxSizeOfMoveAfterFastCall, pc_offset() - before_offset);
7398  }
7399 
7400  if (set_isolate_data_slots == SetIsolateDataSlots::kYes) {
7401  // We don't unset the PC; the FP is the source of truth.
7402  StoreWord(zero_reg,
7403  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kFastCCallCallerFP));
7404  }
7405 
7406  return call_pc_offset;
7407 }
7408 
7409 #undef BRANCH_ARGS_CHECK
7410 
7411 void MacroAssembler::CheckPageFlag(Register object, int mask, Condition cc,
7412  Label* condition_met) {
7413  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7414  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7415  temps.Include(t6);
7416  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7417  And(scratch, object, Operand(~MemoryChunk::GetAlignmentMaskForAssembler()));
7418  LoadWord(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset()));
7419  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(mask));
7420  Branch(condition_met, cc, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
7421 }
7422 
7423 Register GetRegisterThatIsNotOneOf(Register reg1, Register reg2, Register reg3,
7424  Register reg4, Register reg5,
7425  Register reg6) {
7426  RegList regs = {reg1, reg2, reg3, reg4, reg5, reg6};
7427 
7428  const RegisterConfiguration* config = RegisterConfiguration::Default();
7429  for (int i = 0; i < config->num_allocatable_general_registers(); ++i) {
7430  int code = config->GetAllocatableGeneralCode(i);
7431  Register candidate = Register::from_code(code);
7432  if (regs.has(candidate)) continue;
7433  return candidate;
7434  }
7435  UNREACHABLE();
7436 }

7438 void MacroAssembler::ComputeCodeStartAddress(Register dst) {
7439  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7440  auto pc = -pc_offset();
7441  auipc(dst, 0);
7442  if (pc != 0) {
7443  SubWord(dst, dst, pc);
7444  }
7445 }
7446 
7447 // Check if the code object is marked for deoptimization. If it is, then it
7448 // jumps to the CompileLazyDeoptimizedCode builtin. In order to do this we need
7449 // to:
7450 // 1. read from memory the word that contains that bit, which can be found in
7451 // the flags in the referenced {Code} object;
7452 // 2. test kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit in those flags; and
7453 // 3. if it is not zero then it jumps to the builtin.
7454 void MacroAssembler::BailoutIfDeoptimized() {
7455  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7456  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7457  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7458  if (v8_flags.debug_code || !V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING_BOOL) {
7459  int offset =
7460  InstructionStream::kCodeOffset - InstructionStream::kHeaderSize;
7461  LoadProtectedPointerField(
7462  scratch, MemOperand(kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister, offset));
7463  Lw(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Code::kFlagsOffset));
7464  }
7465 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7466  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7467  Label not_deoptimized;
7468  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
7469  Branch(&not_deoptimized, eq, scratch, Operand(zero_reg));
7470  Abort(AbortReason::kInvalidDeoptimizedCode);
7471  bind(&not_deoptimized);
7472  }
7473 #else
7474  And(scratch, scratch, Operand(1 << Code::kMarkedForDeoptimizationBit));
7475  TailCallBuiltin(Builtin::kCompileLazyDeoptimizedCode, ne, scratch,
7476  Operand(zero_reg));
7477 #endif
7478 }
7479 
7480 void MacroAssembler::CallForDeoptimization(Builtin target, int, Label* exit,
7481  DeoptimizeKind kind, Label* ret,
7482  Label*) {
7483  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7484  BlockTrampolinePoolScope block_trampoline_pool(this);
7485  LoadWord(t6, MemOperand(kRootRegister,
7486  IsolateData::BuiltinEntrySlotOffset(target)));
7487  Call(t6);
7488  DCHECK_EQ(SizeOfCodeGeneratedSince(exit),
7489  (kind == DeoptimizeKind::kLazy) ? Deoptimizer::kLazyDeoptExitSize
7490  : Deoptimizer::kEagerDeoptExitSize);
7491 }

7503  FieldMemOperand(code_object, Code::kInstructionStartOffset));
7504 #endif
7505 }

7532 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
7533 void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
7534  [[maybe_unused]] uint16_t argument_count) {
7535  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7536  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
7537 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7538  Register dispatch_handle = kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister;
7539  Register parameter_count = s1;
7540  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7541  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7542  Lw(dispatch_handle,
7543  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
7544  LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(code, parameter_count,
7545  dispatch_handle, scratch);
7546  // Force a safe crash if the parameter count doesn't match.
7547  SbxCheck(le, AbortReason::kJSSignatureMismatch, parameter_count,
7548  Operand(argument_count));
7549  Call(code);
7550 #elif V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7551  // When the sandbox is enabled, we can directly fetch the entrypoint pointer
7552  // from the code pointer table instead of going through the Code object. In
7553  // this way, we avoid one memory load on this code path.
7554  LoadCodeEntrypointViaCodePointer(
7555  code, FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset),
7556  kJSEntrypointTag);
7557  Call(code);
7558 #else
7559  LoadTaggedField(code,
7560  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
7561  CallCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag);
7562 #endif
7563 }
7564 #else
7565 void MacroAssembler::CallJSFunction(Register function_object,
7566  uint16_t argument_count) {
7567  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
7568 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7569  Register dispatch_handle = s1;
7570  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7571  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7572  Lw(dispatch_handle,
7573  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
7574  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
7575  Call(code);
7576 #else
7577  LoadTaggedField(code,
7578  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
7579  CallCodeObject(code);
7580 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7581 }
7582 #endif
7583 
7584 #if V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7585 void MacroAssembler::CallJSDispatchEntry(JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle,
7586  uint16_t argument_count) {
7587  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
7588  Register scratch = s1;
7589  li(kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister,
7590  Operand(dispatch_handle.value(), RelocInfo::JS_DISPATCH_HANDLE));
7591  // WARNING: This entrypoint load is only safe because we are storing a
7592  // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle in the li above (thus keeping the
7593  // dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not compactable
7594  // (thus meaning that the calculation in the entrypoint load is not
7595  // invalidated by a compaction).
7596  // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
7597  static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
7598  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
7599  CHECK_EQ(argument_count,
7600  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->GetParameterCount(
7601  dispatch_handle));
7602  Call(code);
7603 }
7604 #endif

7606 void MacroAssembler::JumpJSFunction(Register function_object,
7607  JumpMode jump_mode) {
7608  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7609  CHECK(!V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
7610  Register code = kJavaScriptCallCodeStartRegister;
7611 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7612  Register dispatch_handle = s1;
7613  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7614  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7615  Lw(dispatch_handle,
7616  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kDispatchHandleOffset));
7617  LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(code, dispatch_handle, scratch);
7618  Jump(code);
7619 #else
7620  LoadTaggedField(code,
7621  FieldMemOperand(function_object, JSFunction::kCodeOffset));
7622  JumpCodeObject(code, kJSEntrypointTag, jump_mode);
7623 #endif
7624 }

7626 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
7627 void MacroAssembler::ResolveWasmCodePointer(Register target,
7628  uint64_t signature_hash) {
7629  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7630  ExternalReference global_jump_table =
7631  ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
7632  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7633  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7634  li(scratch, global_jump_table);
7635 
7636 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7637  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == 16);
7638  CalcScaledAddress(target, scratch, target, 4);
7639  LoadWord(
7640  scratch,
7641  MemOperand(target, wasm::WasmCodePointerTable::kOffsetOfSignatureHash));
7642  // bool has_second_tmp = temps.CanAcquire();
7643  // Register signature_hash_register = has_second_tmp ? temps.Acquire() :
7644  // target; if (!has_second_tmp) {
7645  // Push(signature_hash_register);
7646  // }
7647  // li(signature_hash_register, Operand(signature_hash));
7648  SbxCheck(Condition::kEqual, AbortReason::kWasmSignatureMismatch, scratch,
7649  Operand(signature_hash));
7650 #else
7651  static_assert(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry) == kSystemPointerSize);
7652  CalcScaledAddress(target, scratch, target, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
7653 #endif
7654  LoadWord(target, MemOperand(target, 0));
7655 }
7656 
7657 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointer(Register target,
7658  uint64_t signature_hash,
7659  CallJumpMode call_jump_mode) {
7660  ResolveWasmCodePointer(target, signature_hash);
7661  if (call_jump_mode == CallJumpMode::kTailCall) {
7662  Jump(target);
7663  } else {
7664  Call(target);
7665  }
7666 }
7667 
7668 void MacroAssembler::CallWasmCodePointerNoSignatureCheck(Register target) {
7669  ExternalReference global_jump_table =
7670  ExternalReference::wasm_code_pointer_table();
7671  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7672  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7673  li(scratch, global_jump_table);
7674  constexpr unsigned int kEntrySizeLog2 =
7675  std::bit_width(sizeof(wasm::WasmCodePointerTableEntry)) - 1;
7676  CalcScaledAddress(target, scratch, target, kEntrySizeLog2);
7677  LoadWord(target, MemOperand(target));
7678  Call(target);
7679 }

7687 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
7688 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(Register destination,
7689  Register dispatch_handle,
7690  Register scratch) {
7691  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
7692  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7693  Register index = destination;
7694  LoadWord(scratch,
7695  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
7696 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV32
7697  static_assert(kJSDispatchHandleShift == 0);
7698  SllWord(index, dispatch_handle, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
7699 #else
7700  SrlWord(index, dispatch_handle, kJSDispatchHandleShift);
7701  SllWord(index, index, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
7702 #endif
7703  AddWord(scratch, scratch, index);
7704  LoadWord(destination,
7705  MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
7706 }
7707 
7708 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointFromJSDispatchTable(
7709  Register destination, JSDispatchHandle dispatch_handle, Register scratch) {
7710  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
7711  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7712  LoadWord(scratch,
7713  ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
7714  // WARNING: This offset calculation is only safe if we have already stored a
7715  // RelocInfo for the dispatch handle, e.g. in CallJSDispatchEntry, (thus
7716  // keeping the dispatch entry alive) _and_ because the entrypoints are not
7717  // compatible (thus meaning that the offset calculation is not invalidated by
7718  // a compaction).
7719  // TODO(leszeks): Make this less of a footgun.
7720  static_assert(!JSDispatchTable::kSupportsCompaction);
7721  int offset = JSDispatchTable::OffsetOfEntry(dispatch_handle) +
7722  JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset;
7723  LoadWord(destination, MemOperand(scratch, offset));
7724 }
7725 
7726 #ifdef V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
7727 void MacroAssembler::LoadParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
7728  Register destination, Register dispatch_handle, Register scratch) {
7729  DCHECK(!AreAliased(destination, scratch));
7730  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7731  Register index = destination;
7732  SrlWord(index, dispatch_handle, kJSDispatchHandleShift);
7733  SllWord(index, index, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
7734  Ld(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
7735  AddWord(scratch, scratch, index);
7736  static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
7737  Lhu(destination, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
7738 }
7739 
7740 void MacroAssembler::LoadEntrypointAndParameterCountFromJSDispatchTable(
7741  Register entrypoint, Register parameter_count, Register dispatch_handle,
7742  Register scratch) {
7743  DCHECK(!AreAliased(entrypoint, parameter_count, scratch));
7744  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7745  Register index = parameter_count;
7746  Ld(scratch, ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kJSDispatchTable));
7747  SrlWord(index, dispatch_handle, kJSDispatchHandleShift);
7748  SllWord(index, index, kJSDispatchTableEntrySizeLog2);
7749  AddWord(scratch, scratch, index);
7750  LoadWord(entrypoint, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kEntrypointOffset));
7751  static_assert(JSDispatchEntry::kParameterCountMask == 0xffff);
7752  Lhu(parameter_count, MemOperand(scratch, JSDispatchEntry::kCodeObjectOffset));
7753 }
7754 #endif // V8_TARGET_ARCH_RISCV64
7755 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING

7791 void MacroAssembler::StoreTaggedField(const Register& value,
7792  const MemOperand& dst_field_operand,
7793  Trapper&& trapper) {
7794  trapper(pc_offset());

7801 
7802 void MacroAssembler::AtomicStoreTaggedField(Register src, const MemOperand& dst,
7803  Trapper&& trapper) {
7804  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7805  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7806  AddWord(scratch, dst.rm(), dst.offset());
7807  trapper(pc_offset());
7808  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
7809  amoswap_w(true, true, zero_reg, scratch, src);
7810  } else {
7811  amoswap_d(true, true, zero_reg, scratch, src);
7812  }
7813 }

7815 void MacroAssembler::DecompressTaggedSigned(const Register& destination,
7816  const MemOperand& field_operand,
7817  Trapper&& trapper) {
7818  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7819  Lwu(destination, field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7820  if (v8_flags.slow_debug_code) {
7821  // Corrupt the top 32 bits. Made up of 16 fixed bits and 16 pc offset bits.
7822  AddWord(destination, destination,
7823  Operand(((kDebugZapValue << 16) | (pc_offset() & 0xffff)) << 32));
7824  }
7825 }

7832  AddWord(destination, kPtrComprCageBaseRegister, destination);
7833 }

7847 void MacroAssembler::DecompressProtected(const Register& destination,
7848  const MemOperand& field_operand,
7849  Trapper&& trapper) {
7850 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7851  CHECK(V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL);
7852  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
7853  UseScratchRegisterScope temps(this);
7854  Register scratch = temps.Acquire();
7855  Lw(destination, field_operand, std::forward<Trapper>(trapper));
7856  LoadWord(scratch,
7857  MemOperand(kRootRegister, IsolateData::trusted_cage_base_offset()));
7858  Or(destination, destination, scratch);

7860  UNREACHABLE();
7861 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
7862 }

7898 
7899 // Calls an API function. Allocates HandleScope, extracts returned value
7900 // from handle and propagates exceptions. Clobbers C argument registers
7901 // and C caller-saved registers. Restores context. On return removes
7902 // (*argc_operand + slots_to_drop_on_return) * kSystemPointerSize
7903 // (GCed, includes the call JS arguments space and the additional space
7904 // allocated for the fast call).
7905 void CallApiFunctionAndReturn(MacroAssembler* masm, bool with_profiling,
7906  Register function_address,
7907  ExternalReference thunk_ref, Register thunk_arg,
7908  int slots_to_drop_on_return,
7909  MemOperand* argc_operand,
7910  MemOperand return_value_operand) {
7911  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(masm);
7912  using ER = ExternalReference;
7913 
7914  Isolate* isolate = masm->isolate();
7915  MemOperand next_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7916  ER::handle_scope_next_address(isolate), no_reg);
7917  MemOperand limit_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7918  ER::handle_scope_limit_address(isolate), no_reg);
7919  MemOperand level_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
7920  ER::handle_scope_level_address(isolate), no_reg);
7921 
7922  Register return_value = a0;
7923  Register scratch = a4;
7924  Register scratch2 = a5;
7925 
7926  // Allocate HandleScope in callee-saved registers.
7927  // We will need to restore the HandleScope after the call to the API function,
7928  // by allocating it in callee-saved registers it'll be preserved by C code.
7929  Register prev_next_address_reg = kScratchReg;
7930  Register prev_limit_reg = s1;
7931  Register prev_level_reg = s2;
7932 
7933  // C arguments (kCArgRegs[0/1]) are expected to be initialized outside, so
7934  // this function must not corrupt them (return_value overlaps with
7935  // kCArgRegs[0] but that's ok because we start using it only after the C
7936  // call).
7937  DCHECK(!AreAliased(kCArgRegs[0], kCArgRegs[1], // C args
7938  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7939  // function_address and thunk_arg might overlap but this function must not
7940  // corrupted them until the call is made (i.e. overlap with return_value is
7941  // fine).
7942  DCHECK(!AreAliased(function_address, // incoming parameters
7943  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7944  DCHECK(!AreAliased(thunk_arg, // incoming parameters
7945  scratch, scratch2, prev_next_address_reg, prev_limit_reg));
7946  {
7947  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
7948  "Allocate HandleScope in callee-save registers.");
7949  __ LoadWord(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
7950  __ LoadWord(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
7951  __ Lw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
7952  __ Add32(scratch, prev_level_reg, Operand(1));
7953  __ Sw(scratch, level_mem_op);
7954  }
7955 
7956  Label profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, done_api_call;
7957  if (with_profiling) {
7958  __ RecordComment("Check if profiler or side effects check is enabled");
7959  __ Lb(scratch,
7960  __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(IsolateFieldId::kExecutionMode));
7961  __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
7962  Operand(zero_reg));
7963 #ifdef V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
7964  __ RecordComment("Check if RCS is enabled");
7965  __ li(scratch, ER::address_of_runtime_stats_flag());
7966  __ Lw(scratch, MemOperand(scratch, 0));
7967  __ Branch(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled, ne, scratch,
7968  Operand(zero_reg));
7969 #endif // V8_RUNTIME_CALL_STATS
7970  }
7971 
7972  __ RecordComment("Call the api function directly.");
7973  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(function_address);
7974  __ bind(&done_api_call);
7975 
7976  Label propagate_exception;
7977  Label delete_allocated_handles;
7978  Label leave_exit_frame;
7979 
7980  __ RecordComment("Load the value from ReturnValue");
7981  __ LoadWord(return_value, return_value_operand);
7982 
7983  {
7984  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
7985  masm,
7986  "No more valid handles (the result handle was the last one)."
7987  "Restore previous handle scope.");
7988  __ StoreWord(prev_next_address_reg, next_mem_op);
7989  if (v8_flags.debug_code) {
7990  __ Lw(scratch, level_mem_op);
7991  __ Sub32(scratch, scratch, Operand(1));
7992  __ Check(eq, AbortReason::kUnexpectedLevelAfterReturnFromApiCall, scratch,
7993  Operand(prev_level_reg));
7994  }
7995  __ Sw(prev_level_reg, level_mem_op);
7996  __ LoadWord(scratch, limit_mem_op);
7997  __ Branch(&delete_allocated_handles, ne, prev_limit_reg, Operand(scratch));
7998  }
7999  __ RecordComment("Leave the API exit frame.");
8000  __ bind(&leave_exit_frame);
8001 
8002  Register argc_reg = prev_limit_reg;
8003  if (argc_operand != nullptr) {
8004  // Load the number of stack slots to drop before LeaveExitFrame modifies sp.
8005  __ LoadWord(argc_reg, *argc_operand);
8006  }
8007 
8008  __ LeaveExitFrame(scratch);
8009 
8010  {
8011  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm,
8012  "Check if the function scheduled an exception.");
8013  __ LoadRoot(scratch, RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
8014  __ LoadWord(scratch2, __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
8015  ER::exception_address(isolate), no_reg));
8016  __ Branch(&propagate_exception, ne, scratch, Operand(scratch2));
8017  }
8018 
8019  __ AssertJSAny(return_value, scratch, scratch2,
8020  AbortReason::kAPICallReturnedInvalidObject);
8021 
8022  if (argc_operand == nullptr) {
8023  DCHECK_NE(slots_to_drop_on_return, 0);
8024  __ AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
8025  } else {
8026  // {argc_operand} was loaded into {argc_reg} above.
8027  if (slots_to_drop_on_return != 0) {
8028  __ AddWord(sp, sp, Operand(slots_to_drop_on_return * kSystemPointerSize));
8029  }
8030  __ CalcScaledAddress(sp, sp, argc_reg, kSystemPointerSizeLog2);
8031  }
8032 
8033  __ Ret();
8034 
8035  if (with_profiling) {
8036  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(masm, "Call the api function via thunk wrapper.");
8037  __ bind(&profiler_or_side_effects_check_enabled);
8038  // Additional parameter is the address of the actual callback function.
8039  if (thunk_arg.is_valid()) {
8040  MemOperand thunk_arg_mem_op = __ ExternalReferenceAsOperand(
8041  IsolateFieldId::kApiCallbackThunkArgument);
8042  __ StoreWord(thunk_arg, thunk_arg_mem_op);
8043  }
8044  __ li(scratch, thunk_ref);
8045  __ StoreReturnAddressAndCall(scratch);
8046  __ Branch(&done_api_call);
8047  }
8048 
8049  __ RecordComment("An exception was thrown. Propagate it.");
8050  __ bind(&propagate_exception);
8051  __ TailCallRuntime(Runtime::kPropagateException);
8052 
8053  {
8054  ASM_CODE_COMMENT_STRING(
8055  masm, "HandleScope limit has changed. Delete allocated extensions.");
8056  __ bind(&delete_allocated_handles);
8057  __ StoreWord(prev_limit_reg, limit_mem_op);
8058  // Save the return value in a callee-save register.
8059  Register saved_result = prev_limit_reg;
8060  __ Move(saved_result, a0);
8061  __ PrepareCallCFunction(1, prev_level_reg);
8062  __ li(kCArgRegs[0], ER::isolate_address(isolate));
8063  __ CallCFunction(ER::delete_handle_scope_extensions(), 1);
8064  __ Move(kCArgRegs[0], saved_result);
8065  __ Branch(&leave_exit_frame);
8066  }
8067 }
8068 
8069 void MacroAssembler::LoadFeedbackVector(Register dst, Register closure,
8070  Register scratch, Label* fbv_undef) {
8071  Label done;
8072  // Load the feedback vector from the closure.
8073  LoadTaggedField(dst,
8074  FieldMemOperand(closure, JSFunction::kFeedbackCellOffset));
8075  LoadTaggedField(dst, FieldMemOperand(dst, FeedbackCell::kValueOffset));
8076 
8077  // Check if feedback vector is valid.
8078  LoadTaggedField(scratch, FieldMemOperand(dst, HeapObject::kMapOffset));
8079  Lhu(scratch, FieldMemOperand(scratch, Map::kInstanceTypeOffset));
8080  Branch(&done, eq, scratch, Operand(FEEDBACK_VECTOR_TYPE));
8081 
8082  // Not valid, load undefined.
8083  LoadRoot(dst, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue);
8084  Branch(fbv_undef);
8085 
8086  bind(&done);
8087 }
8088 
8089 void MacroAssembler::BranchRange(Label* L, Condition cond, Register value,
8090  Register scratch, unsigned lower_limit,
8091  unsigned higher_limit,
8092  Label::Distance distance) {
8093  ASM_CODE_COMMENT(this);
8094  DCHECK_LT(lower_limit, higher_limit);
8095  if (lower_limit != 0) {
8096  SubWord(scratch, value, Operand(lower_limit));
8097  Branch(L, cond, scratch, Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit), distance);
8098  } else {
8099  Branch(L, cond, scratch, Operand(higher_limit - lower_limit), distance);
8100  }
8101 }
